            "number": 3135,
            "text": "and they will say, 'Shall we be respited?'",
            "numberInSurah": 203,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 375,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3136,
            "text": "What, do they seek to hasten Our chastisement?",
            "numberInSurah": 204,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 375,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3137,
            "text": "What thinkest thou? If We give them enjoyment of days for many years,",
            "numberInSurah": 205,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 375,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3138,
            "text": "then there comes on them that they were promised,",
            "numberInSurah": 206,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 375,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3139,
            "text": "what will it then avail them, the enjoyment of days they were given?",
            "numberInSurah": 207,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3140,
            "text": "Never a city We destroyed, but it had warners",
            "numberInSurah": 208,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3141,
            "text": "for a reminder; and never did We wrong.",
            "numberInSurah": 209,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3142,
            "text": "Not by the Satans has it been brought down;",
            "numberInSurah": 210,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3143,
            "text": "it behoves them not, neither are they able.",
            "numberInSurah": 211,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3144,
            "text": "Truly, they are expelled from hearing.",
            "numberInSurah": 212,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3145,
            "text": "So call thou not upon another god with God, lest thou shouldst be one of those that are chastised.",
            "numberInSurah": 213,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3146,
            "text": "And warn thy clan, thy nearest kin.",
            "numberInSurah": 214,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3147,
            "text": "Lower thy wing to those who follow thee, being believers;",
            "numberInSurah": 215,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3148,
            "text": "then, if they disobey thee, say, 'I am quit of that you do.'",
            "numberInSurah": 216,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3149,
            "text": "Put thy trust in the All-mighty, the All-compassionate",
            "numberInSurah": 217,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3150,
            "text": "who sees thee when thou standest",
            "numberInSurah": 218,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3151,
            "text": "and when thou turnest about among those who bow.",
            "numberInSurah": 219,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3152,
            "text": "Surely He is the All-hearing, the All-knowing.",
            "numberInSurah": 220,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3153,
            "text": "Shall I tell you on whom the Satans come down?",
            "numberInSurah": 221,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3154,
            "text": "They come down on every guilty impostor.",
            "numberInSurah": 222,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3155,
            "text": "They give ear, but most of them are liars.",
            "numberInSurah": 223,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3156,
            "text": "And the poets -- the perverse follow them;",
            "numberInSurah": 224,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3157,
            "text": "hast thou not seen how they wander in every valley",
            "numberInSurah": 225,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3158,
            "text": "and how they say that which they do not?",
            "numberInSurah": 226,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3159,
            "text": "Save those that believe, and do righteous deeds, and remember God oft, and help themselves after being wronged; and those who do wrong shall surely know by what overturning they will he overturned.",
            "numberInSurah": 227,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 27,
        "name": "سُورَةُ النَّمۡلِ",
        "englishName": "An-Naml",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Ant",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3160,
            "text": "Ta Sin. Those are the signs of the Koran and a Manifest Book,",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3161,
            "text": "a guidance, and good tidings unto the believers",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3162,
            "text": "who perform the prayer, and pay the alms, and have sure faith in the Hereafter.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3163,
            "text": "Those who believe not in the Hereafter, We have decked out fair for them their works, and they wander blindly;",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3164,
            "text": "those are they whom an evil chastisement awaits, and they will be the greatest losers in the Hereafter.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3165,
            "text": "Thou receivest the Koran from One All-wise, All-knowing.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3166,
            "text": "When Moses said to his people 'I observe a fire, and will bring you news of it, or I will bring you a flaming brand, that haply you shall warm yourselves.'",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3167,
            "text": "So, when he came to it, he was called: 'Blessed is he who is in the fire, and he who is about it. Glory be to God, the Lord of all Being!",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3168,
            "text": "Moses, behold, it is I, God, the All-mighty, the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3169,
            "text": "Cast down thy staff.' And when he saw it quivering like a serpent he turned about, retreating, and turned not back. 'Moses, fear not; surely the Envoys do not fear in My presence,",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3170,
            "text": "save him who has done evil, then; after evil, has changed into good; All-forgiving am I, All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3171,
            "text": "Thrust thy hand in thy bosom and it will come forth white without evil-among nine signs to Pharaoh and his people; they are an ungodly people.'",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3172,
            "text": "But when Our signs came to them visibly, they said, 'This is a manifest sorcery';",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3173,
            "text": "and they denied them, though their souls acknowledged them, wrongfully and out of pride. Behold, how was the end of the workers of corruption!",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 378,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3174,
            "text": "And We gave David and Solomon knowledge and they said, 'Praise belongs to God who has preferred us over many of His believing servants.'",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 378,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3175,
            "text": "And Solomon was David's heir, and he said, 'Men, we have been taught the speech of the birds, and we have been given of everything; surely this is indeed the manifest bounty.'",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 378,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3176,
            "text": "And his hosts were mustered to Solomon, jinn, men and birds, duly disposed;",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 378,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3177,
            "text": "till, when they came on the Valley of Ants, an ant said, 'Ants, enter your dwelling-places, lest Solomon and his hosts crush you, being unaware!'",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 378,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3178,
            "text": "But he smiled, laughing at its words, and he said, 'My Lord, dispose me that I may be thankful for Thy blessing wherewith Thou hast blessed me and my father and mother, and that I may do righteousness well-pleasing to Thee; and do Thou admit me, by Thy mercy, amongst Thy righteous servants.'",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 378,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3179,
            "text": "And he reviewed the birds; then he said, 'How is it with me, that I do not see the hoopoe? Or is he among the absent?",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 378,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3180,
            "text": "Assuredly I will chastise him with a terrible chastisement, or I will slaughter him, or he bring me a clear authority.'",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 378,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3181,
            "text": "But he tarried not long, and said, 'I have comprehended that which thou hast not comprehended, and I have come from Sheba to thee with a sure tiding.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 378,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3182,
            "text": "I found a woman ruling over them, and she has been given of everything, and she possesses a mighty throne.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3183,
            "text": "I found her and her people prostrating to the sun, apart from God; Satan has decked out fair their deeds to them and he has barred them from the way, and therefore they are not guided,",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3184,
            "text": "so that they prostrate not themselves to God, who brings forth what is hidden in the heavens and earth; and He knows what you conceal and what you publish.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3185,
            "text": "God: there is no god but He, the Lord of the Mighty Throne.'",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": {
              "id": 9,
              "recommended": true,
              "obligatory": false
            }
          },
          {
            "number": 3186,
            "text": "Said he, 'Now We will see whether thou hast spoken truly, or whether thou art amongst those that lie.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3187,
            "text": "Take this letter of mine, and cast it unto them, then turn back from them and see what they shall return '",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3188,
            "text": "She said, 'O Council, see, a letter honourable has been cast unto me.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3189,
            "text": "It is from Solomon, and it is 'In the Name of God, the Merciful, the Compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3190,
            "text": "Rise not up against me, but come to me in surrender.' '",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3191,
            "text": "She said, 'O Council, pronounce to me concerning my affair; I am not used to decide an affair until you bear me witness.'",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3192,
            "text": "They said, 'We possess force and we possess great might. The affair rests with thee; so consider what thou wilt command.'",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3193,
            "text": "She said, 'Kings, when they enter a city, disorder it and make the mighty ones of its inhabitants abased. Even so they too will do.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3194,
            "text": "Now I will send them a present, and see what the envoys bring back.'",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3195,
            "text": "But when he came to Solomon he said, 'What, would you succour me with wealth, and what God gave me is better than what He has given you? Nay, but instead you rejoice in your gift!",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 380,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3196,
            "text": "Return thou to them; we shall assuredly come against them with hosts they have not power to resist, and we shall expel them from there, abased and utterly humbled.'",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 380,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3197,
            "text": "He said, 'O Council, which one of you will bring me her throne, before they come to me in surrender?'",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 380,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3198,
            "text": "An efreet of the jinns said, 'I will bring it to thee, before thou risest from thy place; I have strength for it",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 380,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3199,
            "text": "and I am trusty.' Said he who possessed knowledge of the Book, 'I will bring it to thee, before ever thy glance returns to thee.' Then, when he saw it settled before him, he said, 'This is of my Lord's bounty that He may try me, whether I am thankful or ungrateful. Whosoever gives thanks gives thanks only for his own soul's good, and whosoever is ungrateful -- my Lord is surely All-sufficient, All-generous.'",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 380,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3200,
            "text": "He said, 'Disguise her throne for her, and we shall behold whether she is guided or if she is of those that are not guided.'",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 380,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3201,
            "text": "So, when she came, it was said, 'Is thy throne like this?' She said, 'It seems the same.' 'And we were given the knowledge before her, and we were in surrender,",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 380,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3202,
            "text": "but that she served, apart from God, barred her, for she was of a people of unbelievers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 380,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3203,
            "text": "It was said to her, 'Enter the pavilion.' But when she saw it, she supposed it was a spreading water, and she bared her legs. He said, 'It is a pavilion smoothed of crystal. She said, 'My Lord, indeed I have wronged myself, and I surrender with Solomon to God, the Lord of all Being.'",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 380,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3204,
            "text": "And We sent to Thamood their brother Salih: 'Serve you God!' And behold, they were two parties, that were disputing one with another.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3205,
            "text": "He said, 'O my people, why do you seek to hasten evil before good? Why do you not ask forgiveness of God? Haply so you will find mercy.'",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3206,
            "text": "They said, 'We augur ill of thee and of those that are with thee.' He said, 'Your augury is with God; nay, but you are a people being proved.'",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3207,
            "text": "Now in the city there were nine persons who did corruption in the land, and put not things right;",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3208,
            "text": "they said, 'Swear you, one to another, by God, 'We will attack him and his family by night, then we will tell his protector, We were not witnesses of the destruction of his family; and assuredly we are truthful men.''",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3209,
            "text": "And they devised a device, and We likewise devised a device, while they were not aware;",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3210,
            "text": "and behold, how was the end of their device! For We destroyed them and their people all together.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3211,
            "text": "Those are their houses, all fallen down because of the evil they committed; surely in that is a sign for a people who have knowledge.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3212,
            "text": "And We delivered those who believed and were godfearing.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3213,
            "text": "And Lot, when he said to his people, 'What, do you commit indecency with your eyes open?",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3214,
            "text": "What, do you approach men lustfully instead of women? No, you are a people that are ignorant.'",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3215,
            "text": "And the only answer of his people was that they said, 'Expel the folk of Lot from your city; they are men that keep themselves clean!'",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 382,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3216,
            "text": "So We delivered him and his family, except his wife; We decreed she should be of those that tarried.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 382,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3217,
            "text": "And We rained on them a rain; and evil indeed is the rain of them that are warned.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 382,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3218,
            "text": "Say: 'Praise belongs to God, and peace be on His servants whom He has chosen.' What, is God better, or that they associate?",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 382,
            "ruku": 331,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3219,
            "text": "He who created the heavens and earth, and sent down for you out of heaven water; and We caused to grow therewith gardens full of loveliness whose trees you could never grow. Is there a god with God? Nay, but they are a people who assign to Him equals!",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 382,
            "ruku": 331,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3220,
            "text": "He who made the earth a fixed place and set amidst it rivers and appointed for it firm mountains and placed a partition between the two seas. Is there a god with God? Nay, but the most of them have no knowledge.",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 382,
            "ruku": 331,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3221,
            "text": "He who answers the constrained, when he calls unto Him, and removes the evil and appoints you to be successors in the earth. Is there a god with God? Little indeed do you remember.",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 382,
            "ruku": 331,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3222,
            "text": "He who guides you in the shadows of the land and the sea and looses the winds, bearing good tidings before His mercy. Is there a god with God? High exalted be God, above that which they associate!",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 382,
            "ruku": 331,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3223,
            "text": "Who originates creation, then brings it back again, and provides you out of heaven and earth. Is there a god with God? Say: 'Produce your proof, if you speak truly.'",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 331,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3224,
            "text": "Say: 'None knows the Unseen in the heavens and earth except God. And they are not aware when they shall be raised;",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 331,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3225,
            "text": "nay, but their knowledge fails as to the Hereafter; nay, they are in doubt of it; nay, they are blind to it.",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 331,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3226,
            "text": "The unbelievers say, 'What, when we are dust, and our fathers, shall we indeed be brought forth?",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3227,
            "text": "We have been promised this, and our fathers before; this is naught but the fairy-tales of the ancients.'",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3228,
            "text": "Say: 'Journey in the land, then behold how was the end of the sinners.'",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3229,
            "text": "Do not sorrow for them, nor be thou straitened for what they devise.",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3230,
            "text": "They say, 'When shall this promise come to pass, if you speak the truth?'",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3231,
            "text": "Say: 'It may be that riding behind you already is some part of that you seek to hasten on.",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3232,
            "text": "Surely thy Lord is bountiful to men; but most of them are not thankful.",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3233,
            "text": "Surely thy Lord knows what their hearts conceal, and what they publish.",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3234,
            "text": "And not a thing is there hidden in heaven and earth but it is in a Manifest Book.",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3235,
            "text": "Surely this Koran relates to the Children of Israel most of that concerning which they are at variance;",
            "numberInSurah": 76,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3236,
            "text": "it is a guidance, and a mercy unto the believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 77,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3237,
            "text": "Surely thy Lord will decide between them by His Judgment; He is the All-mighty, the All-knowing.",
            "numberInSurah": 78,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3238,
            "text": "So put thy trust in God; thou art upon the manifest truth.",
            "numberInSurah": 79,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3239,
            "text": "Thou shalt not make the dead to hear, neither shalt thou make the deaf to hear the call when they turn about, retreating.",
            "numberInSurah": 80,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3240,
            "text": "Thou shalt not guide the blind out of their error neither shalt thou make any to hear, save such as believe in Our signs, and so surrender.",
            "numberInSurah": 81,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3241,
            "text": "When the Word falls on them, We shall bring forth for them out of the earth a beast that shall speak unto them: 'Mankind had no faith in Our signs.'",
            "numberInSurah": 82,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3242,
            "text": "Upon the day when We shall muster out of every nation a troop of those that cried lies to Our signs, duly disposed,",
            "numberInSurah": 83,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3243,
            "text": "till, when they are come, He shall say, 'Did you cry lies to My signs, not comprehending them in knowledge, or what have you been doing?'",
            "numberInSurah": 84,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3244,
            "text": "And the Word shall fall upon them because of the evil they committed, while they speak naught.",
            "numberInSurah": 85,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3245,
            "text": "Have they not seen how We made the night for them, to repose in it, and the day, to see? Surely in that is a sign for a people who are believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 86,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3246,
            "text": "On the day the Trumpet is blown, and terrified is whosoever is in the heavens and earth, excepting whom God wills, and every one shall come to Him, all utterly abject;",
            "numberInSurah": 87,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3247,
            "text": "and thou shalt see the mountains, that thou supposest fixed, passing by like clouds -- God's handiwork, who has created everything very well. He is aware of the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 88,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3248,
            "text": "Whosoever comes with a good deed, he shall have better than it; and they shall be secure from terror that day.",
            "numberInSurah": 89,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3249,
            "text": "And whosoever comes with an evil deed, their faces shall be thrust into the Fire: 'Are you recompensed but for what you did?'",
            "numberInSurah": 90,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3250,
            "text": "I have only been commanded to serve the Lord of this territory which He has made sacred; to Him belongs everything. And I have been commanded to be of those that surrender,",
            "numberInSurah": 91,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3251,
            "text": "and to recite the Koran. So whosoever is guided, is only guided to his own gain; and whosoever goes astray, say: 'I am naught but a warner.",
            "numberInSurah": 92,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3252,
            "text": "And say: 'Praise belongs to God. He shall show you His signs and you will recognise them. Thy Lord is not heedless of the things you do.'",
            "numberInSurah": 93,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 28,
        "name": "سُورَةُ القَصَصِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Qasas",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Stories",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3253,
            "text": "Ta Sin Mim",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3254,
            "text": "Those are the signs of the Manifest Book.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3255,
            "text": "We will recite to thee something of the tiding of Moses and Pharaoh truthfully, for a people who believe.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3256,
            "text": "Now Pharaoh had exalted himself in the land and had divided its inhabitants into sects, abasing one party of them, slaughtering their sons, and sparing their women; for he was of the workers of corruption.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3257,
            "text": "Yet We desired to be gracious to those that were abased in the land, and to make them leaders, and to make them the inheritors,",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3258,
            "text": "and to establish them in the land, and to show Pharaoh and Ha man, and their hosts, what they were dreading from them.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 386,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3259,
            "text": "So We revealed to Moses' mother, 'Suckle him, then, when thou fearest for him, cast him into the sea, and do not fear, neither sorrow, for We shall return him to thee, and shall appoint him one of the Envoys.'",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 386,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3260,
            "text": "So then the folk of Pharaoh picked him out to be an enemy and a sorrow to them; certainly Pharaoh and Haman, and their hosts, were of the sinners.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 386,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3261,
            "text": "Said Pharaoh's wife, 'He will be a comfort to me and thee. Slay him not; perchance he will profit us, or we will take him for a son.' And they were not aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 386,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3262,
            "text": "On the morrow the heart of Moses' mother became empty, and she wellnigh disclosed him had We not strengthened her heart, that she might be among the believers;",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 386,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3263,
            "text": "and she said to his sister, 'Follow him,' and she perceived him from afar, even while they were not aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 386,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3264,
            "text": "Now We had forbidden to him aforetime to be suckled by any foster-mother; therefore she said, 'Shall I direct you to the people of a household who will take charge of him for you and look after him?'",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 386,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3265,
            "text": "So We returned him to his mother, that she might be comforted and not sorrow, and that she might know that the promise of God is true; but most of them do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 386,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3266,
            "text": "And when he was fully grown and in the perfection of his strength, We gave him judgment and knowledge; even so do We recompense the good-doers.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 387,
            "ruku": 335,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3267,
            "text": "And he entered the city, at a time when its people were unheeding, and found there two men fighting; the one was of his own party, and the other was of his enemies. Then the one that was of his party cried to him to aid him against the other that was of his enemies; so Moses struck him, and despatched him, and said, 'This is of Satan's doing; he is surely an enemy misleading, manifest.'",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 387,
            "ruku": 335,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3268,
            "text": "He said, 'My Lord, I have wronged myself. Forgive me!' So God forgave him, for He is the All-forgiving, the All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 387,
            "ruku": 335,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3269,
            "text": "He said, 'My Lord, forasmuch as Thou hast blessed me, I will never be a partisan of the sinners.'",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 387,
            "ruku": 335,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3270,
            "text": "Now in the morning he was in the city, fearful and vigilant; and behold, the man who had sought his, succour on the day before cried out to him again. Moses said to him, 'Clearly thou art, a quarreller.'",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 387,
            "ruku": 335,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3271,
            "text": "But when he would have assaulted the man who was an enemy to them both, the man said, 'Moses, dost thou' desire to slay me, even as thou slewest a living 'soul yesterday? Thou only desirest to be a tyrant in the land; thou desirest not to be of them that put things right.'",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 387,
            "ruku": 335,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3272,
            "text": "Then came a man from the furthest part of the city, running; he said, 'Moses, the Council are conspiring to slay thee. Depart; I am one of thy sincere advisers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 387,
            "ruku": 335,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3273,
            "text": "So he departed therefrom, fearful and vigilant; he said, 'My Lord, deliver me from the people of the evildoers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 387,
            "ruku": 335,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3274,
            "text": "And when he turned his face towards Midian he said, 'It may be that my Lord will guide me",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 388,
            "ruku": 336,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3275,
            "text": "On the right way. And when he came to the waters of Midian he found a company of the people there drawing water, and he found, apart from them, two women holding back their flocks. He said, 'What is your business?' They said, 'We may not draw water until the shepherds drive off; and our father is passing old.'",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 388,
            "ruku": 336,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3276,
            "text": "So he drew water for them; then he turned away to the shade, and he said, 'O my Lord, surely I have need of whatever good Thou shalt have sent down upon me.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 388,
            "ruku": 336,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3277,
            "text": "Then came one of the two women to him, walking modestly, and said, 'My father invites thee, that he may recompense thee with the wage of thy drawing water for us.' So when he came to him and had related to him the story, he said, 'Be not afraid; thou hast escaped from the people of the evildoers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 388,
            "ruku": 336,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3278,
            "text": "Said one of the two women, 'Father, hire him; surely the best man thou canst hire is the one strong and trusty.'",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 388,
            "ruku": 336,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3279,
            "text": "He said, 'I desire to marry thee to one of these my two daughters, on condition that thou hirest thyself to me for eight years. If thou completest ten, that shall be of thy own accord; I do not desire to' press hard 'upon thee. Thou shalt assuredly find me, if God wills, one of the righteous.'",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 388,
            "ruku": 336,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3280,
            "text": "Said he, 'So let it be between me and thee. Whichever of the two' terms I fulfil, it shall be no Injustice to me; and God is guardian of what we say.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 388,
            "ruku": 336,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3281,
            "text": "So when Moses had accomplished the term and departed with his household, he observed on the side of the Mount a fire. He said to his household, 'Tarry you here; I observe a fire. Perhaps I shall bring you news of it, or a faggot from the fire, that haply you shall warm yourselves.'",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 389,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3282,
            "text": "When he came to it, a voice cried from the right of the watercourse, in the sacred hollow, coming from the tree: 'Moses, I am God, the Lord of all Being.'",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 389,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3283,
            "text": "'Cast down thy staff.' And when he saw it quivering like a serpent, he turned about retreating, and turned not back. 'Moses, come forward, and fear not; for surely thou art in security.'",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 389,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3284,
            "text": "Insert thy hand into thy bosom, and it will come forth white without evil; and press to thee thy arm, that thou be not afraid. So these shall be two proofs from thy Lord to Pharaoh and his Council; for surely they are an ungodly people.'",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 389,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3285,
            "text": "Said he, 'My Lord, I have indeed slain a living soul among them, and I fear that they will slay me.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 389,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3286,
            "text": "Moreover my brother Aaron is more eloquent than I. Send him with me as a helper and to confirm I speak truly, for' I fear they will cry me lies.'",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 389,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3287,
            "text": "Said He, 'We will strengthen thy arm by means of thy brother, and We shall appoint. to you an authority, so that they shall not reach you because of Our signs; you, and whoso follows you, shall be the victors.'",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 389,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3288,
            "text": "So when Moses came to them with Our signs, clear signs, they said, 'This is nothing but a forged sorcery. We never heard of this among our fathers, the ancients.'",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 390,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3289,
            "text": "But Moses said, 'My Lord knows very well who comes with the guidance from Him, and shall possess the Ultimate Abode; surely the evildoers will not prosper.'",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 390,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3290,
            "text": "And Pharaoh said, 'Council, I know not that you have any god but me. Kindle me, Haman, a fire upon the clay, and make me a tower, that I may mount up to Moses' god; for I think that he is one of the liars.'",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 390,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3291,
            "text": "And he waxed proud in the land, he and his hosts, wrongfully; and they thought they should not be returned to Us.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 390,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3292,
            "text": "Therefore We seized him and his hosts, and cast their into the sea; so behold how was the end of the evildoers!",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 390,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3293,
            "text": "And We appointed them leaders, calling to the Fire; and on the Day of Resurrection they shall not be helped;",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 390,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3294,
            "text": "and We pursued them in this world with a curse, and on the Day of Resurrection they shall be among the spurned.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 390,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3295,
            "text": "And We gave Moses the Book, after that We had destroyed the former generations, to be examples and a guidance and a mercy, that haply so they might remember.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 390,
            "ruku": 338,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3296,
            "text": "Thou wast not upon the western side when We decreed to Moses the commandment, nor wast thou of those witnessing;",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 391,
            "ruku": 338,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3297,
            "text": "but We raised up generations, and long their lives continued. Neither wast thou a dweller among the Midianites, reciting to them Our signs; but We were sending Messengers.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 391,
            "ruku": 338,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3298,
            "text": "Thou wast not upon the side of the Mount when We called; but for a mercy from thy Lord, that thou mayest warn a people to whom no warner came before thee, and that haply they may remember.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 391,
            "ruku": 338,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3299,
            "text": "Else, did an affliction visit them for that their own hands have forwarded then they might say, 'Our Lord, why didst Thou not send a Messenger to us that we might follow Thy signs and so be among the believers?'",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 391,
            "ruku": 338,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3300,
            "text": "Yet when the truth came to them 'from Ourselves, they said, 'Why has he not been given the like' of that Moses was given?' But they, did they not disbelieve also in what Moses was given aforetime? They said, 'A pair of sorceries mutually supporting each other.' They said, 'We disbelieve both.'",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 391,
            "ruku": 338,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3301,
            "text": "Say: 'Bring a Book from God that gives better guidance than these, and follow it, if you speak truly.'",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 391,
            "ruku": 338,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3302,
            "text": "Then if they do not answer thee, know that they are only following their caprices; and who is further astray than he who follows his caprice without guidance from God? Surely God guides not the people of the evildoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 391,
            "ruku": 338,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3303,
            "text": "Now We have brought them the Word; haply they may remember.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 392,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3304,
            "text": "Those to whom We gave the Book before this believe in it",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 392,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3305,
            "text": "and, when it is recited to them, they say, 'We believe in it; surely it is the truth from our Lord. Indeed, even before' it we had surrendered.'",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 392,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3306,
            "text": "These shall be given their wage twice over for that they patiently endured, and avert evil with good, and expend of that We have provided them.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 392,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3307,
            "text": "When they hear idle talk, they turn away from it and say, 'We have our deeds, and you your deeds. Peace be upon your We desire not the ignorant.'",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 392,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3308,
            "text": "Thou guidest not whom thou likest, but God guides whom He wills, and knows very well those that are guided.",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 392,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3309,
            "text": "They say, 'Should we follow the guidance with thee, we shall be snatched from our land.' Have We not established for them a sanctuary secure, to which are collected the fruits of everything, as a provision from Us? But most of them know not.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 392,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3310,
            "text": "How many a city We have destroyed that flourished in insolent ease! Those are their dwelling-places, undwelt in after them, except a little; Ourselves are the inheritors.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 392,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3311,
            "text": "Yet thy Lord never destroyed the cities until He sent in their mother-city a Messenger, to recite Our signs unto them; and We never destroyed the cities, save that their inhabitants were evildoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 392,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3312,
            "text": "Whatever thing you have been given is the enjoyment of the present life and its adornment; and what is with God is better and more enduring.",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3313,
            "text": "Will you not understand? What, is he to whom We have promised a fair promise, and he receives it, like him to whom We have given the enjoyment of the present life, then he on the Resurrection Day shall be of those that are arraigned?",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3314,
            "text": "Upon the day when He shall call to them, and He shall say, 'Where now are My associates whom you were asserting?'",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3315,
            "text": "Those against whom the Word is realized they shall say, 'Our Lord, those whom we perverted, we perverted them even as we ourselves erred. We declare our innocence unto Thee; it was not us that they were serving.'",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3316,
            "text": "It shall be said, 'Call you now upon your associates!' And they will call upon them, but they shall not answer them, and they shall see the chastisement-ah, if they had been guided!",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3317,
            "text": "Upon the day when He shall call to them, and He shall say, 'What answer gave you to the Envoys?'",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3318,
            "text": "Upon that day the tidings will be darkened for them, nor will they ask each other.",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3319,
            "text": "But as for him who repents, and believes, and works righteousness, haply he shall be among the prosperers.",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3320,
            "text": "Thy Lord creates whatsoever He will and He chooses; they have not the choice. Glory be to God! High be He exalted above that they associate!",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3321,
            "text": "And thy Lord knows what their breasts conceal and what they publish.",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3322,
            "text": "And He is God; there is no god but He. His is the praise in the former as in the latter; His too is the Judgment, and unto Him you shall be returned.",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3323,
            "text": "Say: 'What think you? If God should make the night unceasing over you, until the Day of Resurrection, what god other than God shall bring you illumination? Will you not hear?'",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 394,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3324,
            "text": "Say: 'What think you? If God should make the day unceasing over you, until the Day of Resurrection, what god other than God shall bring you night to repose in? Will you not see?",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 394,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3325,
            "text": "Of His mercy He has appointed for you night and day, for you to repose in and seek after His bounty, that haply you will be thankful.'",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 394,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3326,
            "text": "Upon the day when He shall call. to them, and He shall say, 'Where now are My associates whom you were asserting?'",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 394,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3327,
            "text": "And We shall draw out from every nation a witness, and say, 'Produce your proof!' Then will they know that Truth is God's, and there shall go astray from them that they were forging.",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 394,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3328,
            "text": "Now Korah was of the people of Moses; he became insolent to them, for We had given him treasures such that the very keys of them were too heavy a burden for a company of men endowed with strength. When his people said to him, 'Do not exult; God loves not those that exult;",
            "numberInSurah": 76,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 394,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3329,
            "text": "but seek, amidst that which God has given thee, the Last Abode, and forget not thy portion of the present world; and do good, as God has been good to thee.' And seek not to work corruption in the earth; surely God loves not the workers of corruption.'",
            "numberInSurah": 77,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 394,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3330,
            "text": "He said, 'What I have been given is only because of a knowledge that is in me.' What, did he not know that God bad destroyed before him generations of men stronger than he ill might, and more numerous in multitude? And yet the sinners shall not be questioned concerning their sins.",
            "numberInSurah": 78,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 395,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3331,
            "text": "So he went forth unto his people in his adornment. Those who desired the present life said, 'Would that we possessed the like of that Korah has been given! Surely he is a man of mighty fortune.",
            "numberInSurah": 79,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 395,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3332,
            "text": "But those to whom knowledge had been given said, 'Woe upon you! The reward of God is better for him who believes, and works righteousness; and none shall receive it except the steadfast.'",
            "numberInSurah": 80,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 395,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3333,
            "text": "So We made the earth to swallow him and his dwelling and there was no host to help him, apart from God, and he was helpless;",
            "numberInSurah": 81,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 395,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3334,
            "text": "and in the morning those who had longed to be in his place the day before were saying, 'Ah, God outspreads and straitens His provision to whomsoever He will of His servants. Had God not been gracious to us, He would have made us to be swallowed too. Ah, the unbelievers do not prosper,",
            "numberInSurah": 82,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 395,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3335,
            "text": "That is the Last Abode; We appoint it for those who desire not exorbitance in the earth, nor corruption. The issue ultimate is to the godfearing.",
            "numberInSurah": 83,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 395,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3336,
            "text": "Whoso brings a good deed shall have better than it; and whoso brings an evil deed those who have done evil deeds shall only be recompensed for that they were doing.",
            "numberInSurah": 84,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 395,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3337,
            "text": "He who imposed 'the Recitation upon thee. shall surely restore thee to a place of homing. Say: 'My Lord' knows very well who comes with guidance, and who is in manifest error.",
            "numberInSurah": 85,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3338,
            "text": "Thou didst not hope that the Book should be cast unto thee, except it be as a mercy from thy Lord; so be thou not a partisan of the unbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 86,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3339,
            "text": "Let them not bar thee from the signs of God, after that they have been sent down to thee. And call upon thy Lord, and be thou' not of the idolaters.",
            "numberInSurah": 87,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3340,
            "text": "And call not upon another god with God; there is no god but He. All things perish, except His Face. His is the Judgment, and unto Him you shall be returned.",
            "numberInSurah": 88,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 29,
        "name": "سُورَةُ العَنكَبُوتِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Ankaboot",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Spider",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3341,
            "text": "Alif Lam Mim",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3342,
            "text": "Do the people reckon that they will be left to say 'We believe,' and will not be tried?",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3343,
            "text": "We certainly tried those that were before them, and assuredly God knows those who speak truly, and assuredly He knows the liars.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3344,
            "text": "Or do they reckon, those who do evil deeds, that they will outstrip Us? Ill they judge!",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3345,
            "text": "Whoso looks to encounter God, God's term is coming; He is the All-hearing, the All-knowing.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3346,
            "text": "Whosoever struggles, struggles only to his own gain; surely God is All-sufficient nor needs any being.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3347,
            "text": "And those who believe, and do righteous deeds, We shall surely acquit them of their evil deeds, and shall recompense them the best of what they were doing.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 397,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3348,
            "text": "We have charged man, that he be kind to his parents; but if they strive with thee to make thee associate with Me that whereof thou hast no knowledge, then do not obey them; unto Me you shall return, and I shall tell you what you were doing.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 397,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3349,
            "text": "And those who believe, and do righteous deeds assuredly We shall admit them among the righteous.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 397,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3350,
            "text": "Some men there are who say, 'We believe in God,' but when such a man is hurt in God's cause, he makes the persecution of men as it were God's chastisement; then if help comes from thy Lord, he will say 'We were with you.' What, does not God know very well what is in the breasts of all beings?",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 397,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3351,
            "text": "God surely knows the believers, and He knows the hypocrites.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 397,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3352,
            "text": "The unbelievers say to the believers, 'Follow our path, and let us carry your offences'; yet they cannot carry anything, even of their own offences; they are truly liars.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 397,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3353,
            "text": "They shall certainly carry their loads, and other loads along with their loads, and upon the Day of Resurrection they shall surely be questioned concerning that they were forging.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 397,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3354,
            "text": "Indeed, We sent Noah to his people, and he tarried among them a thousand years, all but fifty; so the Flood seized them, while they were evildoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 397,
            "ruku": 343,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3355,
            "text": "Yet We delivered him, and those who were in the ship, and appointed it for a sign unto all beings.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 398,
            "ruku": 343,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3356,
            "text": "And Abraham, when he said to his people, 'Serve God, and fear Him; that is better for you, did you know.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 398,
            "ruku": 343,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3357,
            "text": "You only serve, apart from God, idols and you create a calumny; those you serve, apart from God, have no power to provide for you. So seek after your provision with God, and serve Him, and be thankful to Him; unto Him you shall be returned.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 398,
            "ruku": 343,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3358,
            "text": "'But if you cry me lies, nations cried lies before you; and it is only for the Messenger to deliver the Manifest Message.'",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 398,
            "ruku": 343,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3359,
            "text": "(Have they not seen how God originates creation, then brings it back again? Surely that is an easy matter for God.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 398,
            "ruku": 343,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3360,
            "text": "Say: Journey in the land, then behold how He originated creation; then God causes the second growth to grow; God is powerful over everything,",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 398,
            "ruku": 343,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3361,
            "text": "chastising whom He will, and having mercy on whomsoever He will, and unto Him you shall be turned.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 398,
            "ruku": 343,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3362,
            "text": "You are not able to frustrate Him either in the earth or in heaven; and you have not, apart from God, either protector or helper.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 398,
            "ruku": 343,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3363,
            "text": "And those who disbelieve in God's signs and the encounter with Him -- they despair of My mercy, and there awaits them a painful chastisement.)",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 398,
            "ruku": 344,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3364,
            "text": "But the only answer of his people was that they said, 'Slay him, or burn him!' Then God delivered him from the fire; surely in that are signs for a people who believe.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 399,
            "ruku": 344,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3365,
            "text": "And he said, 'You have only taken to yourselves idols, apart from God, as a mark of mutual love between you in the present life; then upon the Day of Resurrection you will deny one another, and you will curse one another, and your refuge will be the Fire, and you will have no helpers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 399,
            "ruku": 344,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3366,
            "text": "But Lot believed him; and he said, 'I will flee to my Lord; He is the All-mighty, the All-wise.'",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 399,
            "ruku": 344,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3367,
            "text": "And We gave him Isaac and Jacob, and We appointed the Prophecy and the Book to be among his seed; We gave him his wage in this world, and in the world to come he shall be among the righteous.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 399,
            "ruku": 344,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3368,
            "text": "And Lot, when he said to his people 'Surely you commit such indecency as never any being in all the world committed before you.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 399,
            "ruku": 344,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3369,
            "text": "What, do you approach men, and cut the way, and commit in your assembly dishonour?' But the only answer of his people was that they said, 'Then bring us the chastisement of God, if thou speakest truly.'",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 399,
            "ruku": 344,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3370,
            "text": "He said, 'My Lord, help me against the people that work corruption.'",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 399,
            "ruku": 344,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3371,
            "text": "And when Our messengers came to Abraham with the good tidings, they said, 'We shall destroy the people of this city, for its people are evildoers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 400,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3372,
            "text": "He said, 'Lot is in it.' They said, 'We know very well who is in it; assuredly We shall deliver him and his family, except his wife; she has become of those that tarry.'",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 400,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3373,
            "text": "When that Our messengers came to Lot he was troubled on their account and distressed for them; but they said, 'Fear not, neither sorrow, for surely we shall deliver thee and thy family, except thy wife; she has become of those that tarry.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 400,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3374,
            "text": "We shall send down upon the people of this city wrath out of heaven for their ungodliness.'",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 400,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3375,
            "text": "And indeed, We have left thereof a sign, a clear sign? unto a people who understand.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 400,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3376,
            "text": "And to Midian their brother Shuaib; he said, 'O my people, serve God, and look you for the Last Day; and do not mischief in the land, working corruption.'",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 400,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3377,
            "text": "But they cried lies to him; so the earthquake seized them, and morning found them in their habitation fallen prostrate.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 400,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3378,
            "text": "And Ad, and Thamood -- it has become clear to you from their dwelling-places; and Satan decked out fair to them their works, and barred them from the way, though they saw clearly.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 400,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3379,
            "text": "And Korah, and Pharaoh, and Haman; Moses came to them with the clear signs, but they waxed proud in the earth, yet they outstripped Us not.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 401,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3380,
            "text": "Each We seized for his sin; and of them against some We loosed a squall of pebbles and some were seized by the Cry, and some We made the earth to swallow, and some We drowned; God would never wrong them, but they wronged themselves.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 401,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3381,
            "text": "The likeness of those who have taken to them protectors, apart from God, is as the likeness of the spider that takes to itself a house; and surely the frailest of houses is the house of the spider, did they but know.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 401,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3382,
            "text": "God knows whatever thing they call upon apart from Him; He is the All-mighty, the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 401,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3383,
            "text": "And those similitudes -- We strike them for the people, but none understands them save those who know.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 401,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3384,
            "text": "God created the heavens and the earth with the truth; surely in that is a sign to the believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 401,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3385,
            "text": "Recite what has been revealed to thee of the Book, and perform the prayer; prayer forbids indecency and dishonour. God's remembrance is greater; and God knows the things you work.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 401,
            "ruku": 346,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3386,
            "text": "Dispute not with the People of the Book save in the fairer manner, except for those of them that do wrong; and say, 'We believe in what has been sent down to us, and what has been sent down to you; our God and your God is One, and to Him we have surrendered.'",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 402,
            "ruku": 346,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3387,
            "text": "Even so We have sent down to thee the Book. Those to whom We have given the Book believe in it; and some of these believe in it; and none denies Our signs but the unbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 402,
            "ruku": 346,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3388,
            "text": "Not before this didst thou recite any Book, or inscribe it with thy right hand, for then those who follow falsehood would have doubted.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 402,
            "ruku": 346,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3389,
            "text": "Nay; rather it is signs, clear signs in the breasts of those who have been given knowledge; and none denies Our signs but the evildoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 402,
            "ruku": 346,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3390,
            "text": "They say, 'Why have signs not been gent down upon him from his Lord?' Say: 'The signs are only with God, and I am only a plain warner.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 402,
            "ruku": 346,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3391,
            "text": "What, is it not sufficient for them that We have sent down upon thee the Book that is recited to them? Surely in that is a mercy, and a reminder to a people who believe.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 402,
            "ruku": 346,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3392,
            "text": "Say: 'God suffices as a witness between me and you.' He knows whatsoever is in the heavens and earth. Those who believe in vanity and disbelieve in God -- those, they are the losers.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 402,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3393,
            "text": "And they demand of thee to hasten the chastisement! But for a stated term the chastisement would have come upon them; but it shall come upon them suddenly, when they are not aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3394,
            "text": "They demand of thee to hasten the chastisement! Lo, Gehenna encompasses the unbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3395,
            "text": "Upon the day the chastisement shall overwhelm them from above them and from under their feet, and He shall say, 'Taste now what you were doing!'",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3396,
            "text": "O My servants who believe, surely My earth is wide; therefore Me do you serve!",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3397,
            "text": "Every soul shall taste of death; then unto Us you shall be returned.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3398,
            "text": "And those who believe, and do righteous deeds, We shall surely lodge them in lofty chambers of paradise, underneath which rivers flow, therein dwelling forever; and excellent is the wage of those who labour,",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3399,
            "text": "such men as are patient, and put their trust in their Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3400,
            "text": "How many a beast that bears not its own provision, but God provides for it and you! He is the All-hearer, the All-knower.",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3401,
            "text": "If thou askest them, 'Who created the heavens and the earth and subjected the sun and the moon?' they will say, 'God.' How then are they perverted?",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3402,
            "text": "God outspreads and straitens His provision to whomsoever He will of His servants; God has knowledge of everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3403,
            "text": "If thou askest them, 'Who sends down out of heaven water, and therewith revives the earth after it is dead?' they will say, 'God.' Say: 'Praise belongs to God.' Nay, but most of them have no understanding.",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3404,
            "text": "This present life is naught but a diversion and a sport; surely the Last Abode is Life, did they but know.",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 348,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3405,
            "text": "When they embark in the ships, they call on God, making their religion sincerely His; but when He has delivered them to the land, they associate others with Him,",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 348,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3406,
            "text": "that they may be ungrateful for what We have given them, and take their enjoyment; they will soon know!",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 348,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3407,
            "text": "Have they not seen that We have appointed a sanctuary secure, while all about them the people are snatched away? What, do they believe in vanity, and do they disbelieve in God's blessing?",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 348,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3408,
            "text": "And who does greater evil than he who forges against God a lie, or cries lies to the truth when it comes to him? What, is there not in Gehenna a lodging for the unbelievers?",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 348,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3409,
            "text": "But those who struggle in Our cause, surely We shall guide them in Our ways; and God is with the good-doers.",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 348,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 30,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الرُّومِ",
        "englishName": "Ar-Room",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Romans",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3410,
            "text": "Alif Lam Mim",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3411,
            "text": "The Greeks have been vanquished",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3412,
            "text": "in the nearer part of the land; and, after their vanquishing, they shall be the victors",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3413,
            "text": "in a few years. To God belongs the Command before and after, and on that day the believers shall rejoice",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3414,
            "text": "in God's help; God helps whomsoever He will; and He is the All-mighty, the All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3415,
            "text": "The promise of God! God fails not His promise, but most men do not know it.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3416,
            "text": "They know an outward part of the present life, but of the Hereafter they are heedless.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3417,
            "text": "What, have they not considered within themselves? God created not the heavens and the earth, and what between them is, save with the truth and a stated term; yet most men disbelieve in the encounter with their Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3418,
            "text": "What, have they not journeyed in the land and beheld how was the end of those before them? They were stronger than themselves in might, and they ploughed up the earth and cultivated it more than they themselves have cultivated it; and their Messengers came to them with the clear signs; and God would never wrong them, but themselves they wronged.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3419,
            "text": "Then the end of those that did evil was evil, for that they cried lies to the signs of God and mocked at them.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3420,
            "text": "God originates creation, then brings it back again, then unto Him you shall be returned.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 350,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3421,
            "text": "Upon the day when the Hour is come, the sinners shall be confounded",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 350,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3422,
            "text": "no intercessors shall they have amongst their associates, and they shall disbelieve in their associates.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 350,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3423,
            "text": "Upon the day when the Hour is come, that day they shall be divided;",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 350,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3424,
            "text": "as for those who believed, and did deeds of righteousness, they shall walk with joy in a green meadow,",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 350,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3425,
            "text": "but as for those who disbelieved, and cried lies to Our signs and the encounter of the Hereafter, they shall be arraigned into the chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 406,
            "ruku": 350,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3426,
            "text": "So glory be to God both in your evening hour and in your morning hour.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 406,
            "ruku": 350,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3427,
            "text": "His is the praise in the heavens and earth, alike at the setting sun and in your noontide hour.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 406,
            "ruku": 350,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3428,
            "text": "He brings forth the living from the dead, and brings forth the dead from the living, and He revives the earth after it is dead; even so you shall be brought forth.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 406,
            "ruku": 350,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3429,
            "text": "And of His signs is that He created you of dust; then lo, you are mortals, all scattered abroad.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 406,
            "ruku": 351,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3430,
            "text": "And of His signs is that He created for you, of yourselves, spouses, that you might repose in them, and He has set between you love and mercy. Surely in that are signs for a people who consider.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 406,
            "ruku": 351,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3431,
            "text": "And of His signs is the creation of the heavens and earth and the variety of your tongues and hues. Surely in that are signs for all living beings.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 406,
            "ruku": 351,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3432,
            "text": "And of His signs is your slumbering by night and day, and your seeking after His bounty. Surely in that are signs for a people who hear.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 406,
            "ruku": 351,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3433,
            "text": "And of His signs He shows you lightning, for fear and hope, and that He sends down out of heaven water and He revives the earth after it is dead. Surely in that are signs for a people who understand.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 406,
            "ruku": 351,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3434,
            "text": "And of His signs is that the heaven and earth stand firm by His command; then, when He calls you once and suddenly, out of the earth, lo you shall come forth.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 407,
            "ruku": 351,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3435,
            "text": "To Him belongs whosoever is in the heavens and the earth; all obey His will.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 407,
            "ruku": 351,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3436,
            "text": "And it is He who originates creation, then brings it back again, and it is very easy for Him. His is the loftiest likeness in the heavens and the earth; He is the All-mighty, the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 407,
            "ruku": 351,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3437,
            "text": "He has struck for you a similitude from yourselves; do you have, among that your right hands own, associates in what We have provided for you so that you are equal in regard to it, you fearing them as you fear each other? So We distinguish the signs for a people who understand.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 407,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3438,
            "text": "Nay, but the evildoers follow their own caprices, without knowledge; so who shall guide those whom God has led astray? They have no helpers.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 407,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3439,
            "text": "So set thy face to the religion, a man of pure faith -- God's original upon which He originated mankind. There is no changing God's creation. That is the right religion; but most men know it not --",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 407,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3440,
            "text": "turning to Him. And fear you Him, and perform the prayer, and be not of the idolaters,",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 407,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3441,
            "text": "even of those who have divided up their religion, and become sects, each several party rejoicing in what is theirs.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 407,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3442,
            "text": "When some affliction visits mankind, they call unto their Lord, turning to Him; then, when He lets them taste mercy from Him, lo, a party of them assign associates to their Lord,",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 408,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3443,
            "text": "that they may be ungrateful for what We have given them. 'Take your enjoyment; certainly you will soon know.'",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 408,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3444,
            "text": "Or have We sent down any authority upon them, such as speaks of that they associate with Him?",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 408,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3445,
            "text": "And when We let men taste mercy, they rejoice in it; but if some evil befalls them for that their own hands have forwarded, behold, they despair.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 408,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3446,
            "text": "Have they not seen that God outspreads and straitens His provision to whom He will? Surely in that are signs for a people who believe.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 408,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3447,
            "text": "And give the kinsman his right, and the needy, and the traveller; that is better for those who desire God's Face; those they are the prosperers.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 408,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3448,
            "text": "And what you give in usury, that it may increase upon the people's wealth, increases not with God; but what you give in alms, desiring God's Face, those -- they receive recompense manifold.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 408,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3449,
            "text": "God is He that created you, then He provided for you, then He shall make you dead, then He shall give you life; is there any of your associates does aught of that? Glory be to Him! High be He exalted above that they associate!",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 408,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3450,
            "text": "Corruption has appeared in the land and sea, for that men's own hands have earned, that He may let them taste some part of that which they have done, that haply so they may return.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 408,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3451,
            "text": "Say: 'Journey in the land, then behold how was the end of those that were before; most of them were idolaters.'",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 409,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3452,
            "text": "So set thy face to the true religion before there comes a day from God that cannot be turned back; on that day they shall be sundered apart.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 409,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3453,
            "text": "Whoso disbelieves, his unbelief shall be charged against him; and whosoever does righteousness for themselves they are making provision,",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 409,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3454,
            "text": "that He may recompense those who believe and do righteous deeds of His bounty; He loves not the unbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 409,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3455,
            "text": "And of His signs is that He looses the winds, bearing good tidings and that He may let you taste of His mercy, and that the ships may run at His commandment, and that you may seek His bounty; haply so you will be thankful.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 409,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3456,
            "text": "Indeed, We sent before thee Messengers unto their people, and they brought them the clear signs; then We took vengeance upon those who sinned; and it was ever a duty incumbent upon Us, to help the believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 409,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3457,
            "text": "God is He that looses the winds, that stir up clouds; and He spreads them in heaven how He will, and shatters them; then thou seest the rain issuing out of the midst of them, and when He smites with it whomsoever of His servants He will, lo, they rejoice,",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 409,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3458,
            "text": "although before it was sent down on them before that they had been in despair.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 409,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3459,
            "text": "So behold the marks of God's mercy, how He quickens the earth after it was dead; surely He is the quickener of the dead, and He is powerful over everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 409,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3460,
            "text": "But if We loose a wind, and they see it growing yellow, they remain after that unbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3461,
            "text": "Thou shalt not make the dead to hear, neither shalt thou make the deaf to hear the call when they turn about, retreating.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3462,
            "text": "Thou shalt not guide the blind out of their error neither shalt thou make any to hear except for such as believe in Our signs, and so surrender.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3463,
            "text": "God is He that created you of weakness, then He appointed after weakness strength, then after strength He appointed weakness and grey hairs; He creates what He will, and He is the All-knowing, the All-powerful.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 354,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3464,
            "text": "Upon the day when the Hour is come, the sinners shall swear they have not tarried above an hour; so they were perverted.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 354,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3465,
            "text": "But those who have been given knowledge and faith shall say, 'You have tarried in God's Book till the Day of the Upraising, This is the Day of the Upraising, but you did not know.'",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 354,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3466,
            "text": "So that day their excuses will not profit the evildoers, nor will they be suffered to make amends.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 354,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3467,
            "text": "Indeed, We have struck for the people in this Koran every manner of similitude; and if thou bringest them a sign, those who are unbelievers will certainly say, 'You do nothing but follow falsehood.'",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 354,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3468,
            "text": "Even so God seals the hearts of those that know not.",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 354,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3469,
            "text": "So be thou patient; surely God's promise is true; and let not those who have not sure faith make thee unsteady.",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 354,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 31,
        "name": "سُورَةُ لُقۡمَانَ",
        "englishName": "Luqman",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Luqman",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3470,
            "text": "Alif Lam Mim",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3471,
            "text": "Those are the signs of the Wise Book",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3472,
            "text": "for a guidance and a mercy to the good-doers",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3473,
            "text": "who perform the prayer, and pay the alms, and have sure faith in the Hereafter.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3474,
            "text": "Those are upon guidance from their Lord; those are the prosperers.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3475,
            "text": "Some men there are who buy diverting talk to lead astray from the way of God without knowledge, and to take it in mockery; those -- there awaits them a humbling chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3476,
            "text": "And when Our signs are recited to such a man he turns away, waxing proud, as though he heard them not, and in his ears were heaviness; so give him good tidings of a painful chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3477,
            "text": "Surely those who believe, and do deeds of righteousness, there awaits them Gardens of Bliss",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3478,
            "text": "therein to dwell forever -- God's promise in truth; and He is the All-mighty, the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3479,
            "text": "He created the heavens without pillars you can see, and He cast on the earth firm mountains, lest it shake with you, and He scattered abroad in it all manner of crawling thing. And We sent down out of heaven water, and caused to grow in it of every generous kind.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3480,
            "text": "This is God's creation; now show me what those have created that are apart from Him! Nay, but the evildoers are in manifest error.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3481,
            "text": "Indeed, We gave Lokman wisdom: 'Give thanks to God. Whosoever gives thanks gives thanks only for his own soul's good, and whosoever is ungrateful -- surely God is All-sufficient, All-laudable.'",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 412,
            "ruku": 356,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3482,
            "text": "And when Lokman said to his son, admonishing him, 'O my son, do not associate others with God; to associate others with God is a mighty wrong.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 412,
            "ruku": 356,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3483,
            "text": "(And We have charged man concerning his parents -- his mother bore him in weakness upon weakness, and his weaning was in two years -- 'Be thankful to Me, and to thy parents; to Me is the homecoming.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 412,
            "ruku": 356,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3484,
            "text": "But if they strive with thee to make thee associate with Me that whereof thou hast no knowledge, then do not obey them. Keep them company honourable in this world; but follow the way of him who turns to Me. Then unto Me you shall return, and I shall tell you what you were doing.')",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 412,
            "ruku": 356,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3485,
            "text": "'O my son, if it should be but the weight of one grain of mustard-seed, and though it be in a rock, or in the heavens, or in the earth, God shall bring it forth; surely God is All-subtle, All-aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 412,
            "ruku": 356,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3486,
            "text": "O my son, perform the prayer, and bid unto honour, and forbid dishonour. And bear patiently whatever may befall thee; surely that is true constancy.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 412,
            "ruku": 356,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3487,
            "text": "Turn not thy cheek away from men in scorn, and walk not in the earth exultantly; God loves not any man proud and boastful.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 412,
            "ruku": 356,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3488,
            "text": "Be modest in thy walk, and lower thy voice; the most hideous of voices is the ass's.'",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 412,
            "ruku": 356,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3489,
            "text": "Have you not seen how that God has subjected to you whatsoever is in the heavens and earth, and He has lavished on you His blessings, outward and inward? And among men there is such a one that disputes concerning God without knowledge or guidance, or an illuminating Book;",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 413,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3490,
            "text": "and when it is said to them, 'Follow what God has sent down,' they say, 'No; but we will follow such things as we found our fathers doing.' What? Even though Satan were calling them to the chastisement of the burning?",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 413,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3491,
            "text": "And whosoever submits his will to God, being a good-doer, has laid hold of the most firm handle; and unto God is the issue of all affairs.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 413,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3492,
            "text": "And whoso disbelieves, let not his disbelief grieve thee; unto Us they shall return, and We shall tell them what they did. Surely God knows all the thoughts within the breasts.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 413,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3493,
            "text": "To them We give enjoyment a little, then We compel them to a harsh chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 413,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3494,
            "text": "If thou askest them, 'Who created the heavens and the earth?' they will say, 'God.' Say: 'Praise belongs to God.' Nay, but most of them have no knowledge.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 413,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3495,
            "text": "To God belongs all that is in the heavens and the earth; surely God -- He is the All-sufficient, the All-laudable.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 413,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3496,
            "text": "Though all the trees in the earth were pens, and the sea-seven seas after it to replenish it, yet would the Words of God not be spent. God is All-mighty, All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 413,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3497,
            "text": "Your creation and your upraising are as but as a single soul. God is All-hearing, All-seeing.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 413,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3498,
            "text": "Hast thou not seen how that God makes the night to enter into the day and makes the day to enter into the night. and He has subjected the sun and the moon, each of them running to a stated term, and that God is aware of what you do?",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 414,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3499,
            "text": "That is because God -- He is the Truth, and that they call upon apart from Him -- that is the false; and for that God is the All-high, the All-great.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 414,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3500,
            "text": "Hast thou not seen how that the ships run upon the sea by the blessing of God, that He may show you some of His signs? Surely in that are signs for every man enduring, thankful.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 414,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3501,
            "text": "And when the waves cover them like shadows they call upon God, making their religion sincerely His; but when He has delivered them to the land, some of them are lukewarm. And none denies Our signs, except every ungrateful traitor.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 414,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3502,
            "text": "O men, fear your Lord, and dread a day when no father shall give satisfaction for his child, and no child shall give satisfaction for his father whatever. Surely God's promise is true; so let not the present life delude you, and let not the Deluder delude you concerning God.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 414,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3503,
            "text": "Surely God -- He has knowledge of the Hour; He sends down the rain; He knows what is in the wombs. No soul knows what it shall earn tomorrow, and no soul knows in what land it shall die. Surely God is All-knowing, All-aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 414,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 32,
        "name": "سُورَةُ السَّجۡدَةِ",
        "englishName": "As-Sajda",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Prostration",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3504,
            "text": "Alif Lam Mim",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3505,
            "text": "The sending down of the Book, wherein no doubt is, from the Lord of all Being.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3506,
            "text": "Or do they say, 'He has forged it'? Say: 'Not so; it is the truth from thy Lord that thou mayest warn a people to whom no warner came before thee, that haply so they may be guided.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3507,
            "text": "God is He that created the heavens and the earth, and what between them is, in six days, then seated Himself upon the Throne. Apart from Him, you have no protector neither mediator; will you not remember?",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3508,
            "text": "He directs the affair from heaven to earth, then it goes up to Him in one day, whose measure is a thousand years of your counting.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3509,
            "text": "He is the knower of the Unseen and the Visible, the All-mighty, the All-compassionate,",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3510,
            "text": "who has created all things well. And He originated the creation of man out of clay,",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3511,
            "text": "then He fashioned his progeny of an extraction of mean water,",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3512,
            "text": "then He shaped him, and breathed His spirit in him. And He appointed for you hearing, and sight, and hearts; little thanks you show.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3513,
            "text": "They say, 'What, when we have gone astray in the earth, shall we indeed be in a new creation?' Nay, but they disbelieve in the encounter with their Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3514,
            "text": "Say: 'Death's angel, who has been charged with you, shall gather you, then to your Lord you shall be returned.'",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3515,
            "text": "Ah, if thou couldst see the guilty hanging their heads before their Lord! 'Our Lord, we have seen and heard; now return us, that we may do righteousness, for we have sure faith.'",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 416,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3516,
            "text": "'If We had so willed, We could have given every soul its guidance; but now My Word is realized -- ' Assuredly I shall fill Gehenna with jinn and men all together.'",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 416,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3517,
            "text": "So now taste, for that you forgot the encounter of this your day! We indeed have forgotten you. Taste the chastisement of eternity for that you were doing!'",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 416,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3518,
            "text": "Only those believe in Our signs who, when they are reminded of them, fall down prostrate and proclaim the praise of their Lord, not waxing proud.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 416,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": {
              "id": 10,
              "recommended": false,
              "obligatory": true
            }
          },
          {
            "number": 3519,
            "text": "Their sides shun their couches as they call on their Lord in fear and hope; and they expend of that We have provided them.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 416,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3520,
            "text": "No soul knows what comfort is laid up for them secretly, as a recompense for that they were doing.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 416,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3521,
            "text": "What? Is he who has been a believer like unto him who has been ungodly? They are not equal.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 416,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3522,
            "text": "As for those who believe, and do deeds of righteousness, there await them the Gardens of the Refuge, in hospitality for that they were doing.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 416,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3523,
            "text": "But as for the ungodly, their refuge shall be the Fire; as often as they desire to come forth from it, they shall be restored into it, and it shall be said to them, 'Taste the chastisement of the Fire, which you cried lies to.'",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 416,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3524,
            "text": "And We shall surely let them taste the nearer chastisement, before the greater; haply so they will return.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3525,
            "text": "And who does greater evil than he who is reminded of the signs of his Lord, then turns away from them? We shall take vengeance upon the sinners.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3526,
            "text": "Indeed, We gave Moses the Book; so he not in doubt concerning the encounter with him; and We appointed it for a guidance to the Children of Israel.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 360,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3527,
            "text": "And We appointed from among them leaders guiding by Our command, when they endured patiently, and had sure faith in Our signs.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 360,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3528,
            "text": "Surely thy Lord will distinguish between them on the Resurrection Day, touching that whereon they were at variance.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 360,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3529,
            "text": "Is it not a guidance to them, how many generations We destroyed before them in whose dwelling-places they walk? Surely in that are signs; what, will they not hear?",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 360,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3530,
            "text": "Have they not seen how We drive the water to the dry land and bring forth crops therewith whereof their cattle and themselves eat? What, will they not see?",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 360,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3531,
            "text": "They also say, 'When shall be this Victory, if you speak truly?'",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 360,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3532,
            "text": "Say: 'On the Day of Victory their faith shall not profit the unbelievers, nor shall they be respited.'",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 360,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3533,
            "text": "So turn thou away from them, and wait; they too are waiting.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 360,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 33,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الأَحۡزَابِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Ahzaab",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Clans",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3534,
            "text": "O Prophet, fear God, and obey not the unbelievers and the hypocrites. God is All-knowing, All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 418,
            "ruku": 361,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3535,
            "text": "And follow what is revealed to thee from thy Lord; surely God is aware of the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 418,
            "ruku": 361,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3536,
            "text": "And put thy trust in God; God suffices as a guardian.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 418,
            "ruku": 361,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3537,
            "text": "God has not assigned to any man two hearts within his breast; nor has He made your wives, when you divorce, saying, 'Be as my mother's back,' truly your mothers, neither has He made your adopted sons your sons in fact. That is your own saying, the words of your mouths; but God speaks the truth, and guides on the way.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 418,
            "ruku": 361,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3538,
            "text": "Call them after their true fathers; that is more equitable in the sight of God. If you know not who their fathers were, then they are your brothers in religion, and your clients. There is no fault in you if you make mistakes, but only in what your hearts premeditate. God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 418,
            "ruku": 361,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3539,
            "text": "The Prophet is nearer to the believers than their selves; his wives are their mothers. Those who are bound by blood are nearer to one another in the Book of God than the believers and the emigrants; nevertheless you should act towards your friends honourably; that stands inscribed in the Book.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 418,
            "ruku": 361,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3540,
            "text": "And when We took compact from the Prophets, and from thee, and from Noah, and Abraham, Moses, and Jesus, Mary's son; We took from them a solemn compact,",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 419,
            "ruku": 361,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3541,
            "text": "that He might question the truthful concerning their truthfulness; and He has prepared for the unbelievers a painful chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 419,
            "ruku": 361,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3542,
            "text": "O believers, remember God's blessing upon you when hosts came against you, and We loosed against them a wind, and hosts you saw not; and God sees the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 419,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3543,
            "text": "When they came against you from above you and from below you, and when your eyes swerved and your hearts reached your throats, while you thought thoughts about God;",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 419,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3544,
            "text": "there it was that the believers were tried, and shaken most mightily.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 419,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3545,
            "text": "And when tile hypocrites, and those in whose hearts is sickness, said, 'God and His Messenger promised us only delusion.'",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 419,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3546,
            "text": "And when a party of them said, 'O people of Yathrib, there is no abiding here for you, therefore return!' And a part of them Were asking leave of the Prophet, saying, 'Our houses are exposed'; yet they were not exposed; they desired only to flee.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 419,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3547,
            "text": "And if entrance had been forced against them from those quarters, and then they had been asked to apostatise, they would have done so, and but tarried about it briefly.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 419,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3548,
            "text": "Yet they had made covenant with God before that, that they would not turn their backs; and covenants with God shall be questioned of",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 419,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3549,
            "text": "Say: 'Flight will not profit you, if you flee from death or slaying; you will be given enjoyment of days then but little.'",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 420,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3550,
            "text": "Say: 'Who is he that shall defend you from God, if lie desires evil for you, or desires mercy for you?' They shall find for themselves, apart from God, neither protector nor helper.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 420,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3551,
            "text": "God would surely know those of you who hinder, and those who say to their brothers, 'Come to us,' and come to battle but little,",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 420,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3552,
            "text": "being niggardly towards you. When fear comes upon them, thou seest them looking at thee, their eyes rolling like one who swoons of death; but when the fear departs, they flay you with sharp tongues, being niggardly to possess the good things. Those have never believed; God has made their works to fail; and that is easy for God.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 420,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3553,
            "text": "They think the Confederates have not departed; and if the Confederates come, they will wish that they were desert-dwellers among the Bedoums asking for news of you. If they were among you, they would fight but little.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 420,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3554,
            "text": "You have had a good example in God's Messenger for whosoever hopes for God and the Last Day, and remembers God oft.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 420,
            "ruku": 363,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3555,
            "text": "When the believers saw the Confederates they said, 'This is what God and His Messenger promised us, and God and His Messenger have spoken truly.' And it only increased them in faith and surrender.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 420,
            "ruku": 363,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3556,
            "text": "Among the believers are men who were true to their covenant with God; some of them have fulfilled their vow by death, and some are still awaiting, and they have not changed in the least;",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 421,
            "ruku": 363,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3557,
            "text": "that God may recompense the truthful ones for their truthfulness, and chastise the hypocrites, if He will, or turn again unto them. Surely God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 421,
            "ruku": 363,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3558,
            "text": "And God sent back those that were unbelievers in their rage, and they attained no good; God spared the believers of fighting. Surely God is All-strong, All-mighty.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 421,
            "ruku": 363,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3559,
            "text": "And He brought down those of the People of the Book who supported them from their fortresses and cast terror in their hearts; some you slew, some you made captive.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 421,
            "ruku": 363,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3560,
            "text": "And He bequeathed upon you their lands, their habitations, and their possessions, and a land you never trod. God is powerful over everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 421,
            "ruku": 363,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3561,
            "text": "O Prophet, say to thy wives: 'If you desire the present life and its adornment, come now, I will make you provision, and set you free with kindliness.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 421,
            "ruku": 364,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3562,
            "text": "But if you desire God and His Messenger and the Last Abode, surely God has prepared for those amongst you such as do good a mighty wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 421,
            "ruku": 364,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3563,
            "text": "Wives of the Prophet, whosoever among you commits a flagrant indecency, for her the chastisement shall be doubled; that is easy for God.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 421,
            "ruku": 364,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3564,
            "text": "But whosoever of you is obedient to God and His Messenger, and does righteousness, We shall pay her her wage twice over; We have prepared for her a generous provision.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 422,
            "ruku": 364,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3565,
            "text": "Wives of the Prophet, you are not as other women. If you are godfearing, be not abject in your speech, so that he in whose heart is sickness may be lustful; but speak honourable words.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 422,
            "ruku": 364,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3566,
            "text": "Remain in your houses; and display not your finery, as did the pagans of old. And perform the prayer, and pay the alms, and obey God and His Messenger. People of the House, God only desires to put away from you abomination and to cleanse you.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 422,
            "ruku": 364,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3567,
            "text": "And remember that which is recited in your houses of the signs of God and the Wisdom; God is All-subtle, All-aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 422,
            "ruku": 364,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3568,
            "text": "Men and women who have surrendered, believing men and believing women, obedient men and obedient women, truthful men and truthful women, enduring men and enduring women, humble men and humble women, men and women who give in charity, men who fast and women who fast, men and women who guard their private parts, men and women who remember God oft -- for them God has prepared forgiveness and a mighty wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 422,
            "ruku": 365,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3569,
            "text": "It is not for any believer, man or woman, when God and His Messenger have decreed a matter, to have the choice in the affair. Whosoever disobeys God and His Messenger has gone astray into manifest error.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 423,
            "ruku": 365,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3570,
            "text": "When thou saidst to him whom God had blessed and thou hadst favoured, 'Keep thy wife to thyself, and fear God,' and thou wast concealing within thyself what God should reveal, fearing other men; and God has better right for thee to fear Him. So when Zaid had accomplished what he would of her, then We gave her in marriage to thee, so that there should not be any fault in the believers, touching the wives of their adopted sons, when they have accomplished what they would of them; and God's commandment must be performed.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 423,
            "ruku": 365,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3571,
            "text": "There is no fault in the Prophet, touching what God has ordained for him -- God's wont with those who passed away before; and God's commandment is doom decreed;",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 423,
            "ruku": 365,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3572,
            "text": "who were delivering the Messages of God, and were fearing Him, and fearing not any one except Him; and God suffices as a reckoner.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 423,
            "ruku": 365,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3573,
            "text": "Muhammad is not the father of any one of your men, but the Messenger of God, and the Seal of the Prophets; God has knowledge of everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 423,
            "ruku": 365,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3574,
            "text": "O believers, remember God oft,",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 423,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3575,
            "text": "and give Him glory at the dawn and in the evening.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 423,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3576,
            "text": "It is He who blesses you, and His angels, to bring you forth from the shadows into the light. He is All-compassionate to the believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 423,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3577,
            "text": "Their greeting, on the day when they shall meet Him, will be 'Peace!' And He has prepared for them a generous wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 424,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3578,
            "text": "O Prophet, We have sent thee as a witness, and good tidings to bear and warning,",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 424,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3579,
            "text": "calling unto God by His leave, and as a light-giving lamp.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 424,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3580,
            "text": "Give good tidings to the believers that there awaits them with God great bounty.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 424,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3581,
            "text": "And obey not the unbelievers and the hypocrites; heed not their hurt, but put thy trust in God; God suffices as a guardian.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 424,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3582,
            "text": "O believers, when you marry believing women and then divorce them before you touch them, you have no period to reckon against them; so make provision for them, and set them free with kindliness.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 424,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3583,
            "text": "O Prophet, We have made lawful for thee thy wives whom thou hast given their wages and what thy right hand owns, spoils of war that God has given thee, and the daughters of thy uncles paternal and aunts paternal, thy uncles maternal and aunts maternal, who have emigrated with thee, and any woman believer, if she give herself to the Prophet and if the Prophet desire to take her in marriage, for thee exclusively, apart from the believers -- We know what We have imposed upon them touching their wives and what their right hands own -- that there may be no fault in thee; God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 424,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3584,
            "text": "Thou mayest put off whom thou wilt of them, and whom thou wilt thou mayest take to thee; and if thou seekest any thou hast set aside there is no fault in thee. So it is likelier they will be comforted, and not sorrow, and every one of them will be well-pleased with what thou givest her. God knows what is in your hearts; God is All-knowing, All-clement.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 425,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 170,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3585,
            "text": "Thereafter women are not lawful to thee, neither for thee to take other wives in exchange for them, though their beauty please thee, except what thy right hand owns; God is watchful over everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 425,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 170,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3586,
            "text": "O believers, enter not the houses of the Prophet, except leave is given you for a meal, without watching for its hour. But when you are invited, then enter; and when you have had the meal, disperse, neither lingering for idle talk; that is hurtful to the Prophet, and he is ashamed before you; but God is not ashamed before the truth. And when you ask his wives for any object, ask them from behind a curtain; that is cleaner for your hearts and theirs. It is not for you to hurt God's Messenger, neither to marry his wives after him, ever; surely that would be, in God's sight, a monstrous thing.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 425,
            "ruku": 367,
            "hizbQuarter": 170,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3587,
            "text": "Whether you reveal anything, or whether you conceal it, surely God has knowledge of everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 425,
            "ruku": 367,
            "hizbQuarter": 170,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3588,
            "text": "There is no fault in the Prophet's wives touching their fathers, their sons, their brothers, their brothers' sons, their sisters' sons, their women, and what their right hands own. And fear you God; surely God is witness of everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 426,
            "ruku": 367,
            "hizbQuarter": 170,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3589,
            "text": "God and His angels bless the Prophet. O believers, do you also bless him, and pray him peace.",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 426,
            "ruku": 367,
            "hizbQuarter": 170,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3590,
            "text": "Those who hurt God and His Messenger -- them God has cursed in the present world and the world to come, and has prepared for them a humbling chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 426,
            "ruku": 367,
            "hizbQuarter": 170,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3591,
            "text": "And those who hurt believing men and believing women, without that they have earned it, have laid upon themselves calumny and manifest sin.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 426,
            "ruku": 367,
            "hizbQuarter": 170,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3592,
            "text": "O Prophet, say to thy wives and daughters and the believing women, that they draw their veils close to them; so it is likelier they will be known, and not hurt. God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 426,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 170,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3593,
            "text": "Now; if the hypocrites do not give over, and those in whose hearts there is sickness and they that make commotion in the city, We shall assuredly urge thee against them and then they will be thy neighbours there only a little;",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 426,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3594,
            "text": "cursed they shalt be, and wheresoever they are come upon they shall be seized and slaughtered all --",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 426,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3595,
            "text": "God's wont with those who passed away before; and thou shall find no changing the wont of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 426,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3596,
            "text": "The people will question thee concerning the Hour. Say: 'The knowledge of it is only with God; what shall make thee know? Haply the Hour is nigh.'",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3597,
            "text": "God has cursed the unbelievers, and prepared for them a Blaze,",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3598,
            "text": "therein to dwell for ever; they shall find neither protector nor helper.",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3599,
            "text": "Upon the day when their faces are turned about in the Fire they shall say, 'Ah, would we had obeyed God and the Messenger!",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3600,
            "text": "They shall say, 'Our Lord, we obeyed our chiefs and great ones, and they led us astray from the way.",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3601,
            "text": "Our Lord, give them chastisement twofold, and curse them with a mighty curse!'",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3602,
            "text": "O believers, be not as those who hurt Moses, but God declared him quit of what they said, and he was high honoured with God.",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 369,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3603,
            "text": "O believers, fear God, and speak words hitting the mark,",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 369,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3604,
            "text": "and He will set right your deeds for you and will forgive you your sins. Whosoever obeys God and His Messenger has won a mighty triumph.",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 369,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3605,
            "text": "We offered the trust to the heavens and the earth and the mountains, but they refused to carry it and were afraid of it; and man carried it. Surely he is sinful, very foolish.",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 369,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3606,
            "text": "That God may chastise the hypocrites, men and women alike, and the idolaters, men and women alike; and that God may turn again unto the believers, men and women alike. God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 369,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 34,
        "name": "سُورَةُ سَبَإٍ",
        "englishName": "Saba",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Sheba",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3607,
            "text": "Praise belongs to God to whom belongs whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth. To Him belongs praise also in the Hereafter; He is the All-wise, the All-aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 428,
            "ruku": 370,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3608,
            "text": "He knows what penetrates into the earth, and what comes forth from it, what comes down from heaven, and what goes up to it; He is the All-compassionate, the All-forgiving.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 428,
            "ruku": 370,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3609,
            "text": "The unbelievers say, 'The Hour will never come to us.' Say: 'Yes indeed, by my Lord, it shall come to you, by Him who knows the Unseen; not so much as the weight of an ant in heaven and earth escapes from Him, neither is aught smaller than that, or greater, but it is in a Manifest Book;",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 428,
            "ruku": 370,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3610,
            "text": "that He may recompense those who believe, and do righteous deeds; theirs shall be forgiveness and generous provision.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 428,
            "ruku": 370,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3611,
            "text": "'And those who strive against Our signs to void them -- theirs shall be a chastisement of painful wrath.'",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 428,
            "ruku": 370,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3612,
            "text": "Those who have been given the knowledge see that what has been sent down to thee from thy Lord is the truth, and guides to the path of the All-mighty, the All-laudable.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 428,
            "ruku": 370,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3613,
            "text": "The unbelievers say, 'Shall we point you to a man who will tell you, when you have been utterly torn to pieces, then you shall be in a new creation?'",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 428,
            "ruku": 370,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3614,
            "text": "What, has he forged against God a lie, or is he possessed? Not so; but those who believe not in the Hereafter are in chastisement and far error.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 429,
            "ruku": 370,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3615,
            "text": "Have they not regarded what lies before them and what lies behind them of heaven and earth? Did We will, We would make the earth to swallow them, or We would drop down on them lumps from heaven. Surely in that is a sign to every penitent servant.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 429,
            "ruku": 370,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3616,
            "text": "And We gave David bounty from Us: 'O you mountains, echo God's praises with him, and you birds!' And We softened for him iron:",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 429,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3617,
            "text": "'Fashion wide coats of mail, and measure well the links. ' -- And do ye righteousness, for surely I see the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 429,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3618,
            "text": "And to Solomon the wind; its morning course was a month's journey, and its evening course was a month's journey. And We made the Fount of Molten Brass to flow for him. And of the jinn, some worked before him by the leave of his Lord; and such of them as swerved away from Our commandment, We would let them taste the chastisement of the Blaze;",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 429,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3619,
            "text": "fashioning for him whatsoever he would -- places of worship, statues, porringers like water-troughs, and anchored cooking-pots. 'Labour, O House of David, in thankfulness; for few indeed are those that are thankful among My servants.'",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 429,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3620,
            "text": "And when We decreed that he should die, naught indicated to them that he was dead but the Beast of the Earth devouring his staff; and when he fell down, the jinn saw clearly that, had they only known the Unseen, they would not have continued in the humbling chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 429,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3621,
            "text": "For Sheba also there was a sign in their dwelling-place -- two gardens, one on the right and one on the left: 'Eat of your Lord's provision, and give thanks to Him; a good land, and a Lord All-forgiving.'",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 430,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3622,
            "text": "But they turned away; so We loosed on them the Flood of Arim, and We gave them, in exchange for their two gardens, two gardens bearing bitter produce and tamarisk-bushes, and here and there a few lote-trees.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 430,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3623,
            "text": "Thus We recompensed them for their unbelief; and do 'We ever recompense any hut the unbeliever?",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 430,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3624,
            "text": "And We set, between them and the cities that We have blessed, cities apparent and well We measured the journey between them: 'Journey among them by night and day in security!'",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 430,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3625,
            "text": "But they said, 'Our Lord, prolong the stages of our travel'; and they wronged themselves, so We made them as but tales, and We tore them utterly to pieces. Surely in that are signs for every man enduring, thankful.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 430,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3626,
            "text": "Iblis proved true his opinion of them, and they followed him, except a party of the believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 430,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3627,
            "text": "Yet he had no authority over them, but that We might know him who believed in the Hereafter from him who was in doubt thereof Thy Lord is Guardian over everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 430,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3628,
            "text": "Say: 'Call on those you have asserted apart from God; they possess not so much as the weight of an ant in the heavens nor in the earth; they have no partnership in either of them, nor has He in them any supporter.'",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 430,
            "ruku": 372,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3629,
            "text": "Intercession will not avail with Him save for him to whom He gives leave; till, when terror is lifted from their hearts, they will say, 'What said your Lord?' They will say, 'The truth; and He is the All-high; the All-great.'",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 431,
            "ruku": 372,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3630,
            "text": "Say: 'Who provides for you out of the heavens and the earth?' Say: 'God.' Surely, either we or you are upon right guidance, or in manifest error.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 431,
            "ruku": 372,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3631,
            "text": "Say: 'You will not be questioned concerning our sins, neither shall we be questioned as to what you do.'",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 431,
            "ruku": 372,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3632,
            "text": "Say: 'Our Lord will bring us together, then make deliverance between us by the truth. He is the Deliverer, the All-knowing.'",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 431,
            "ruku": 372,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3633,
            "text": "Say: 'Show me those you have joined to Him as associates. No indeed; rather He is God, the All-mighty, the All-wise.'",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 431,
            "ruku": 372,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3634,
            "text": "We have sent thee not, except to mankind entire, good tidings to bear, and warning; but most men do not know it.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 431,
            "ruku": 372,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3635,
            "text": "They say, 'When shall this promise come to pass, if you speak the truth?'",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 431,
            "ruku": 372,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3636,
            "text": "Say: 'You have the tryst of a day that you shall not put back by a single hour nor put it forward.'",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 431,
            "ruku": 372,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3637,
            "text": "The unbelievers say, 'We will not believe in this Koran, nor in that before it.' Ah, if thou couldst see when the evildoers are stationed before their Lord, bandying argument the one against the other! Those that were abased will say to those that waxed proud, 'Had it not been for you, we would have been believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 431,
            "ruku": 373,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3638,
            "text": "Those that waxed proud will say to those that were abased, 'What, did we bar you from the guidance after it came to you? Nay, rather you were sinners.'",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 432,
            "ruku": 373,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3639,
            "text": "And those that were abased will say to those that waxed proud, 'Nay, but devising night and day, when you were ordering us to disbelieve in God, and to set up compeers to Him.' They will be secretly remorseful when they see the chastisement and We put fetters on the necks of the unbelievers; shall they be recompensed except for what they were doing?",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 432,
            "ruku": 373,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3640,
            "text": "We sent no warner into any city except its men who lived at ease said, 'We disbelieve in the Message you have been sent with.'",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 432,
            "ruku": 373,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3641,
            "text": "They also said, 'We are more abundant in wealth and children, and we shall not be chastised.'",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 432,
            "ruku": 373,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3642,
            "text": "Say: 'My Lord outspreads and straitens His provision to whomsoever He will, but most men do not know it.'",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 432,
            "ruku": 373,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3643,
            "text": "It is not your wealth nor your children that shall bring you nigh in nearness to Us, except for him who believes, and does righteousness; those -- there awaits them the double recompense for that they did, and they shall be in the lofty chambers in security.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 432,
            "ruku": 374,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3644,
            "text": "And those who strive against Our signs to void them -- those shall be arraigned into the chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 432,
            "ruku": 374,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3645,
            "text": "Say: 'My Lord outspreads and straitens His provision to whomsoever He will of His servants; and whatever thing you shall expend, He will replace it. He is the best of providers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 432,
            "ruku": 374,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3646,
            "text": "Upon the day when He shall muster them all together, then He shall say to the angels, 'Was it you these were serving?",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 433,
            "ruku": 374,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3647,
            "text": "They shall say, 'Glory be to Thee'! Thou art our Protector, apart from them; nay rather, they were serving the jinn; most of them believed in them.'",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 433,
            "ruku": 374,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3648,
            "text": "'Therefore today none of you shall have power to profit or hurt another.' And We shall say to the evildoers, 'Taste the chastisement of the Fire, which you cried lies to!'",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 433,
            "ruku": 374,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3649,
            "text": "And when Our signs are recited to them, clear signs, they say, 'This is naught but a man who desires to bar you from that your fathers served'; and they say, 'This is nothing but a forged calumny.' And the unbelievers say to the truth, when it has come to them, 'This is nothing but manifest sorcery.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 433,
            "ruku": 374,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3650,
            "text": "We have not given them any Books to study, nor have We sent them before thee any warner.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 433,
            "ruku": 374,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3651,
            "text": "Those that were before them also cried lies, yet they reached not a tenth of what We gave them; they cried lies to My Messengers, and how was My horror!",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 433,
            "ruku": 374,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3652,
            "text": "Say: 'I give you but one admonition, that you stand unto God, two by two and one by one, and then reflect: no madness is in your comrade. He is naught but a warner unto you, before a terrible chastisement.'",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 433,
            "ruku": 375,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3653,
            "text": "Say: 'I have asked no wage of you; that shall be yours. My wage falls only upon God; and He is witness over everything.'",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 433,
            "ruku": 375,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3654,
            "text": "Say: 'My Lord hurls the truth -- the Knower of the Unseen.'",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 433,
            "ruku": 375,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3655,
            "text": "Say. 'Truth has come; falsehood originates not, nor brings again.'",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 434,
            "ruku": 375,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3656,
            "text": "Say: 'If I go astray, I go astray only to my own loss; if I am guided, it is by what my Lord reveals to me. He is All-hearing, Ever-nigh.'",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 434,
            "ruku": 375,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3657,
            "text": "Ah, if thou couldst see when they are terrified, and there is no escape, and they are seized from a place near at hand,",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 434,
            "ruku": 375,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3658,
            "text": "and they say, 'We believe in it'; but how can they reach from a place far away,",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 434,
            "ruku": 375,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3659,
            "text": "seeing they disbelieved in it before, guessing at the Unseen from a place far away?",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 434,
            "ruku": 375,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3660,
            "text": "And a barrier is set between them and that they desire, as was done with the likes of them aforetime; they were in doubt disquieting.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 434,
            "ruku": 375,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 35,
        "name": "سُورَةُ فَاطِرٍ",
        "englishName": "Faatir",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Originator",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3661,
            "text": "Praise belongs to God, Originator of the heavens and earth, who appointed the angels to be messengers having wings two, three and four, increasing creation as He wills. Surely God is powerful over everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 434,
            "ruku": 376,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3662,
            "text": "Whatsoever mercy God opens to men, none can withhold and whatsoever He withholds, none can loose after Him. He is the All-mighty, the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 434,
            "ruku": 376,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3663,
            "text": "O men, remember God's blessing upon you; is there any creator, apart from God, who provides for you out of heaven and earth? There is no god but He: how then are you perverted?",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 434,
            "ruku": 376,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3664,
            "text": "If they cry lies to thee, Messengers before thee were cried lies to; and unto God all matters are returned.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 435,
            "ruku": 376,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3665,
            "text": "O men, God's promise is true; so let not the present life delude you, and let not the Deluder delude you concerning God.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 435,
            "ruku": 376,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3666,
            "text": "Surely Satan is an enemy to you; so take him for an enemy. He calls his party only that they may be among the inhabitants of the Blaze.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 435,
            "ruku": 376,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3667,
            "text": "Those who disbelieve -- there awaits them a terrible chastisement; but those who believe, and do deeds of righteousness -- theirs shall be forgiveness and a great wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 435,
            "ruku": 376,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3668,
            "text": "And what of him, the evil of whose deeds has been decked out fair to him, so that he thinks it is good? God leads astray whomsoever He will, and whomsoever He will He guides; so let not thy soul be wasted in regrets for them; God has knowledge of the things they work.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 435,
            "ruku": 377,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3669,
            "text": "God is He that looses the winds, that stir up cloud, then We drive it to a dead land and therewith revive the earth, after it is dead. Even so is the Uprising.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 435,
            "ruku": 377,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3670,
            "text": "Whosoever desires glory, the glory altogether belongs to God. To Him good words go up, and the righteous deed -- He uplifts it; but those who devise evil deeds -- theirs shall be a terrible chastisement, and their devising shall come to naught.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 435,
            "ruku": 377,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3671,
            "text": "God created you of dust then of a sperm-drop, then He made you pairs. No female bears or brings forth, save with His knowledge; and none is given long life who is given long life neither is any diminished in his life, but it is in a Book. Surely that is easy for God.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 435,
            "ruku": 377,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3672,
            "text": "Not equal are the two seas; this is sweet, grateful to taste, delicious to drink, and that is salt, bitter to the tongue. Yet of both you eat fresh flesh, and bring forth out of it ornaments for you to wear; and thou mayest see the ships cleaving through it, that you may seek of His bounty, and so haply you will be thankful.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 436,
            "ruku": 377,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3673,
            "text": "He makes the night to enter into the day and makes the day to enter into the night, and He has subjected the sun and the moon, each of them running to a stated term. That is God, your Lord; to Him belongs the Kingdom; and those you call upon, apart from Him, possess not so much as the skin of a date-stone.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 436,
            "ruku": 377,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3674,
            "text": "If you call upon them, they will not hear your prayer, and if they heard, they would not answer you; and on the Day of Resurrection they will disown your partnership. None can tell thee like One who is aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 436,
            "ruku": 377,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3675,
            "text": "O men, you are the ones that have need of God; He is the All-sufficient, the All-laudable.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 436,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3676,
            "text": "If He will, He can put you away and bring a new creation;",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 436,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3677,
            "text": "that is surely no great matter for God.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 436,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3678,
            "text": "No soul laden bears the load of another; and if one heavy-burdened calls for its load to be carried, not a thing of it will be carried, though he be a near kinsman. Thou warnest only those who fear their Lord in the Unseen and perform the prayer; and whosoever purifies himself, purifies himself only for his own soul's good. To God is the homecoming.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 436,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3679,
            "text": "Not equal are the blind and the seeing man,",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3680,
            "text": "the shadows and the light,",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3681,
            "text": "the shade and the torrid heat;",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3682,
            "text": "not equal are the living and the dead. God makes to hear whomsoever He will; thou canst not make those in their tombs to hear -",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3683,
            "text": "thou art naught but a warner.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3684,
            "text": "Surely We have sent thee with the truth good tidings to bear, and warning; not a nation there is, but there has passed away in it a warner.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3685,
            "text": "If they cry thee lies, those before them also cried lies; their Messengers came to them with the clear signs, the Psalms, the Illuminating Book;",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3686,
            "text": "then I seized the unbelievers, and how was My horror!",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3687,
            "text": "Hast thou not seen how that God sends down out of heaven water, and therewith We bring forth fruits of diverse hues? And in the mountains are streaks white and red, of diverse hues, and pitchy black;",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3688,
            "text": "men too, and beasts and cattle -- diverse are their hues. Even so only those of His servants fear God who have knowledge; surely God is All-mighty, All-forgiving.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3689,
            "text": "Surely those who recite the Book of God and perform the prayer, and expend of that We have provided them, secretly and in public, look for a commerce that comes not to naught,",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3690,
            "text": "that He may pay them in full their wages and enrich them of His bounty; surely He is All-forgiving, All-thankful.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3691,
            "text": "And that We have revealed to thee of the Book is the truth, confirming what is before it; God is aware of and sees His servants.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 438,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3692,
            "text": "Then We bequeathed the Book on those of Our servants We chose; but of them some wrong themselves, some of them are lukewarm, and some are outstrippers in good works by the leave of God; that is the great bounty.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 438,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3693,
            "text": "Gardens of Eden they shall enter; therein they shall be adorned with bracelets of gold and with pearls, and their apparel there shall be of silk.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 438,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3694,
            "text": "And they shall say, 'Praise belongs to God who has put away all sorrow from us. Surely our Lord is All-forgiving, All-thankful,",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 438,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3695,
            "text": "who of His bounty has made us to dwell in the abode of everlasting life wherein no weariness assails us neither fatigue.'",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 438,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3696,
            "text": "As for the unbelievers, theirs shall be the fire of Gehenna; they shall neither be done with and die, nor shall its chastisement be lightened for them. Even so We recompense every ungrateful one.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 438,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3697,
            "text": "Therein they shall shout, 'Our Lord, bring us forth, and we will do righteousness, other than what we have done.' 'What, did We not give you long life, enough to remember in for him who would remember? To you the warner came; taste you now! The evildoers shall have no helper.'",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 438,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3698,
            "text": "God knows the Unseen in the heavens and the earth; He knows the thoughts within the breasts.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 438,
            "ruku": 380,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3699,
            "text": "It is He who appointed you viceroys in the earth. So whosoever disbelieves, his unbelief shall be charged against him; their unbelief increases the disbelievers only in hate in God's sight; their unbelief increases the disbelievers only in loss.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 439,
            "ruku": 380,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3700,
            "text": "Say: 'Have you considered your associates on whom you call, apart from God? Show me what they have created in the earth; or have they a partnership in the heavens?' Or have We given them a Book, so that they are upon a clear sign from it? Nay, but the evildoers promise one another naught but delusion.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 439,
            "ruku": 380,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3701,
            "text": "God holds the heavens and the earth, lest they remove; did they remove, none would hold them after Him. Surely He is All-clement, All-forgiving.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 439,
            "ruku": 380,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3702,
            "text": "They have sworn by God the most earnest oaths that if a warner came to them, they would be more rightly guided than any one of the nations; but when a warner came to them, it increased them only in aversion,",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 439,
            "ruku": 380,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3703,
            "text": "waxing proud in the land, and devising evil; but evil devising encompasses only those who do it; So do they expect anything but the wont of the ancients? And thou shalt never find any changing the Wont of God, and thou shalt never find any altering the wont of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 439,
            "ruku": 380,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3704,
            "text": "What, have they not journeyed in the land and beheld how was the end of those before them? They were stronger than themselves in might; but God -- there is naught in the heavens or the earth that can frustrate Him. Surely He is All-knowing, All-powerful.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 439,
            "ruku": 380,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3705,
            "text": "If God should take men to task for what they have earned He would not leave upon the face of the earth one creature that crawls; but He is deferring them to a stated term. But when their term is come -- surely God sees His servants.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 380,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 36,
        "name": "سُورَةُ يسٓ",
        "englishName": "Yaseen",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Yaseen",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3706,
            "text": "Ya Sin",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3707,
            "text": "By the Wise Koran,",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3708,
            "text": "thou art truly among the Envoys",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3709,
            "text": "on a straight path;",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3710,
            "text": "the sending down of the All-mighty, the All-wise,",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3711,
            "text": "that thou mayest warn a people whose fathers were never warned, so they are heedless.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3712,
            "text": "The Word has been realised against most of them, yet they do not believe.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3713,
            "text": "Surely We have put on their necks fetters up to the chin, so their heads are raised;",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3714,
            "text": "and We have put before them a barrier and behind them a barrier; and We have covered them, so they do not see.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3715,
            "text": "Alike it is to them whether thou hast warned them or thou hast not warned them, they do not believe.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3716,
            "text": "Thou only warnest him who follows the Remembrance and who fears the All-merciful in the Unseen; so give him the good tidings of forgiveness and a generous wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3717,
            "text": "Surely it is We who bring the dead to life and write down what they have forwarded and what they have left behind; everything We have numbered in a clear register.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3718,
            "text": "Strike for them a similitude -- the inhabitants of the city, when the Envoys came to it;",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3719,
            "text": "when We sent unto them two men, but they cried them lies, so We sent a third as reinforcement. They said, 'We are assuredly Envoys unto you.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3720,
            "text": "They said, 'You are naught but mortals like us; the All-merciful has not sent down anything. You are speaking only lies.'",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3721,
            "text": "They said, 'Our Lord knows we are Envoys unto you;",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3722,
            "text": "and it is only for us to deliver the Manifest Message.'",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3723,
            "text": "They said, 'We augur ill of you. If you give not over, we will stone you and there shall visit you from us a painful chastisement.'",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3724,
            "text": "They said, 'Your augury is with you; if you are reminded? But you are a prodigal people.'",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3725,
            "text": "Then came a man from the furthest part of the city, running; he said, 'My people, follow the Envoys!",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3726,
            "text": "Follow such as ask no wage of you, that are right-guided.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3727,
            "text": "And why should I not serve Him who originated me, and unto whom you shall be returned?",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3728,
            "text": "What, shall I take, apart from Him, gods whose intercession, if the All-merciful desires affliction for me, shall not avail me anything, and who will never deliver me?",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3729,
            "text": "Surely in that case I should be in manifest error.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3730,
            "text": "Behold, I believe in your Lord; therefore hear me!'",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3731,
            "text": "It was said, 'Enter Paradise!' He said, 'Ah, would that my people had knowledge",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3732,
            "text": "that my Lord has forgiven me and that He has placed me among the honoured.'",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3733,
            "text": "And We sent not down upon his people, after him, any host out of heaven; neither would We send any down.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3734,
            "text": "It was only one Cry and lo, they were silent and still.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3735,
            "text": "Ah, woe for those servants! Never comes unto them a Messenger, but they mock at him.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3736,
            "text": "What, have they not seen how many generations We have destroyed before them, and that it is not unto them that they return?",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3737,
            "text": "They shall every one of them be arraigned before Us.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3738,
            "text": "And a sign for them is the dead land, that We quickened and brought forth from it grain, whereof they eat;",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3739,
            "text": "and We made therein gardens of palms and vines, and therein We caused fountains to gush forth,",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3740,
            "text": "that they might eat of its fruits and their hands' labour. What, will they not be thankful?",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3741,
            "text": "Glory be to Him, who created all the pairs of what the earth produces, and of themselves, and of what they know not.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3742,
            "text": "And a sign for them is the night; We strip it of the day and lo, they are in darkness.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3743,
            "text": "And the sun -- it runs to a fixed resting-place; that is the ordaining of the All-mighty, the All-knowing.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3744,
            "text": "And the moon -- We have determined it by stations, till it returns like an aged palm-bough.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3745,
            "text": "It behoves not the sun to overtake the moon, neither does the night outstrip the day, each swimming in a sky.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3746,
            "text": "And a sign for them is that We carried their seed in the laden ship,",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3747,
            "text": "and We have created for them the like of it whereon they ride;",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3748,
            "text": "and if We will, We drown them, then none have they to cry to, neither are they delivered,",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3749,
            "text": "save as a mercy from Us, and enjoyment for a while.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3750,
            "text": "And when it is said to them, 'Fear what is before you and what is behind you; haply you will find mercy' --",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3751,
            "text": "yet never any sign of the signs of their Lord comes to them, but they are turning away from it.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3752,
            "text": "And when it is said to them, 'Expend of that God has provided you,' the unbelievers say to the believers, 'What, shall we feed such a one whom, if God willed, He would feed? You are only in manifest error!'",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3753,
            "text": "They also say, 'When shall this promise come to pass, if you speak truly?'",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3754,
            "text": "They are awaiting only for one Cry to seize them while they are yet disputing,",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3755,
            "text": "then they will not be able to make any testament, nor will they return to their people.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3756,
            "text": "And the Trumpet shall be blown; then behold, they are sliding down from their tombs unto their Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3757,
            "text": "They say, 'Alas for us! Who roused us out of our sleeping place? This is what the All-merciful promised, and the Envoys spoke truly.'",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3758,
            "text": "'It was only one Cry; then behold, they are all arraigned before Us.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3759,
            "text": "So today no soul shall be wronged anything, and you shall not be recompensed, except according to what you have been doing.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3760,
            "text": "See, the inhabitants of Paradise today are busy in their rejoicing,",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3761,
            "text": "they and their spouses, reclining upon couches in the shade;",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3762,
            "text": "therein they have fruits, and they have all that they call for.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3763,
            "text": "'Peace!' -- such is the greeting, from a Lord All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3764,
            "text": "'Now keep yourselves apart, you sinners, upon this day!",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3765,
            "text": "Made I not covenant with you, Children of Adam, that you should not serve Satan -- surely he is a manifest foe to you --",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3766,
            "text": "and that you should serve Me? This is a straight path.",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3767,
            "text": "He led astray many a throng of you; did you not understand?",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3768,
            "text": "This is Gehenna, then, the same that you were promised;",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3769,
            "text": "roast well in it today, for that you were unbelievers!'",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3770,
            "text": "Today We set a seal on their mouths, and their hands speak to Us, and their feet bear witness as to what they have been earning.",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3771,
            "text": "Did We will, We would have obliterated their eyes, then they would race to the path, but how would they see?",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3772,
            "text": "Did We will, We would have changed them where they were, then they could not go on, nor could they return.",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3773,
            "text": "And to whomsoever We give long life, We bend him over in His constitution; what, do they not understand?",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3774,
            "text": "We have not taught him poetry; it is not seemly for him. It is only a Remembrance and a Clear Koran,",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3775,
            "text": "that he may warn whosoever is living, and that the Word may be realized against the unbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3776,
            "text": "Have they not seen how that We have created for them of that Our hands wrought cattle that they own?",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3777,
            "text": "We have subdued them to them, and some of them they ride, and some they eat;",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3778,
            "text": "other uses also they have in them, and beverages. What, will they not be thankful?",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3779,
            "text": "Yet they have taken, apart from God, gods; haply they might be helped.",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3780,
            "text": "They cannot help them, though they be hosts made ready for them.",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3781,
            "text": "So do not let their saying grieve thee; assuredly We know what they keep secret and what they publish.",
            "numberInSurah": 76,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3782,
            "text": "Has not man regarded how that We created him of a sperm-drop? Then lo, he is a manifest adversary.",
            "numberInSurah": 77,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3783,
            "text": "And he has struck for Us a similitude and forgotten his creation; he says, 'Who shall quicken the bones when they are decayed?'",
            "numberInSurah": 78,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3784,
            "text": "Say: 'He shall quicken them, who originated them the first time; He knows all creation,",
            "numberInSurah": 79,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3785,
            "text": "who has made for you out of the green tree fire and lo, from it you kindle.'",
            "numberInSurah": 80,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3786,
            "text": "Is not He, who created the heavens and earth, able to create the like of them? Yes indeed; He is the All-creator, the All-knowing.",
            "numberInSurah": 81,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3787,
            "text": "His command, when He desires a thing, is to say to it 'Be,' and it is.",
            "numberInSurah": 82,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3788,
            "text": "So glory be to Him, in whose hand is the dominion of everything, and unto whom you shall be returned.",
            "numberInSurah": 83,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 37,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الصَّافَّاتِ",
        "englishName": "As-Saaffaat",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Those drawn up in Ranks",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3789,
            "text": "By the rangers ranging",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3790,
            "text": "and the scarers scaring",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3791,
            "text": "and the reciters of a Remembrance,",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3792,
            "text": "surely your God is One,",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3793,
            "text": "Lord of the heavens and the earth, and of what between them is Lord of the Easts.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3794,
            "text": "We have adorned the lower heaven with the adornment of the stars",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3795,
            "text": "and to preserve against every rebel Satan;",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3796,
            "text": "they listen not to the High Council, for they are pelted from every side,",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3797,
            "text": "rejected, and theirs is an everlasting chastisement,",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3798,
            "text": "except such as snatches a fragment, and he is pursued by a piercing flame.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3799,
            "text": "So ask them for a pronouncement -- Are they stronger in constitution, or those We created? We created them of clinging clay.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3800,
            "text": "Nay, thou marvellest; and they scoff",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3801,
            "text": "and, when reminded, do not remember",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3802,
            "text": "and, when they see a sign, would scoff;",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3803,
            "text": "and they say, 'This is nothing but manifest sorcery.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3804,
            "text": "What, when we are dead and become dust and bones, shall we indeed be raised up?",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3805,
            "text": "What, and our fathers, the ancients?'",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3806,
            "text": "Say: 'Yes, and in all lowliness.'",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3807,
            "text": "For it is only a single scaring, then behold, they are watching",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3808,
            "text": "and they say, 'Woe, alas for us! This is the Day of Doom.'",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3809,
            "text": "'This is the Day of Decision, even that you cried lies to.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3810,
            "text": "Muster those who did evil, their wives, and that they were serving,",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3811,
            "text": "apart from God, and guide them unto the path of Hell!",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3812,
            "text": "And halt them, to be questioned:",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3813,
            "text": "'Why help you not one another?'",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3814,
            "text": "No indeed; but today they resign themselves in submission",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3815,
            "text": "and advance one upon another, asking each other questions.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3816,
            "text": "These say, 'Why, you of old would come to us from the right hand.'",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3817,
            "text": "Those say, 'No; on the contrary, you were not believers;",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3818,
            "text": "we had no authority over you; no, you were an insolent people.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3819,
            "text": "So our Lord's Word is realised against us; we are tasting it.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3820,
            "text": "Therefore we perverted you, and we ourselves were perverts.'",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3821,
            "text": "So all of them on that day are sharers in the chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3822,
            "text": "Even so We do with the sinners;",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3823,
            "text": "for when it was said to them, 'There is no god but God,' they were ever waxing proud,",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3824,
            "text": "saying, 'What, shall we forsake our gods for a poet possessed?'",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3825,
            "text": "'No indeed; but he brought the truth, and confirmed the Envoys.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3826,
            "text": "Now certainly you shall be tasting the painful chastisement,",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3827,
            "text": "and not be recompensed, except according to what you were doing.'",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3828,
            "text": "Except for God's sincere servants;",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3829,
            "text": "for them awaits a known provision,",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3830,
            "text": "fruits -- and they high-honoured",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3831,
            "text": "in the Gardens of Bliss",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3832,
            "text": "upon couches, set face to face,",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3833,
            "text": "a cup from a spring being passed round to them,",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3834,
            "text": "white, a delight to the drinkers,",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3835,
            "text": "wherein no sickness is, neither intoxication;",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3836,
            "text": "and with them wide-eyed maidens restraining their glances",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3837,
            "text": "as if they were hidden pearls.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3838,
            "text": "They advance one upon another, asking each other questions.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3839,
            "text": "One of them says, 'I had a comrade",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3840,
            "text": "who would say, 'Are you a confirmer?",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3841,
            "text": "What, when we are dead and become dust and bones, shall we indeed be requited?'",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3842,
            "text": "He says, 'Are you looking down?'",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3843,
            "text": "Then he looks, and sees him in the midst of Hell.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3844,
            "text": "He says, 'By God, wellnigh thou didst destroy me;",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3845,
            "text": "But for my Lord's blessing, I were one of the arraigned.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3846,
            "text": "What, do we then not die",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3847,
            "text": "except for our first death, and are we not chastised?",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3848,
            "text": "This is indeed the mighty triumph,",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3849,
            "text": "for the like of this let the workers work.'",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3850,
            "text": "Is that better as a hospitality, or the Tree of Ez-Zakkoum?",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3851,
            "text": "We have appointed it as a trial for the evildoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3852,
            "text": "It is a tree that comes forth in the root of Hell;",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3853,
            "text": "its spathes are as the heads of Satans,",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3854,
            "text": "and they eat of it, and of it fill their bellies,",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3855,
            "text": "then on top of it they have a brew of boiling water,",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3856,
            "text": "then their return is unto Hell.",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3857,
            "text": "They found their fathers erring,",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3858,
            "text": "and they run in their footsteps.",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3859,
            "text": "Before them erred most of the ancients,",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3860,
            "text": "and We sent among them warners;",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3861,
            "text": "and behold, how was the end of them that were warned,",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3862,
            "text": "except for God's sincere servants.",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3863,
            "text": "Noah called to Us; and how excellent were the Answerers!",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3864,
            "text": "And We delivered him and his people from the great distress,",
            "numberInSurah": 76,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3865,
            "text": "and We made his seed the survivors,",
            "numberInSurah": 77,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3866,
            "text": "and left for him among the later folk",
            "numberInSurah": 78,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3867,
            "text": "'Peace be upon Noah among all beings!'",
            "numberInSurah": 79,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3868,
            "text": "Even so We recompense the good-doers;",
            "numberInSurah": 80,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3869,
            "text": "he was among Our believing servants.",
            "numberInSurah": 81,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3870,
            "text": "Then afterwards We drowned the rest.",
            "numberInSurah": 82,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3871,
            "text": "Of his party was also Abraham;",
            "numberInSurah": 83,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3872,
            "text": "when he came unto his Lord with a pure heart,",
            "numberInSurah": 84,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3873,
            "text": "when he said to his father and his folk, 'What do you serve?",
            "numberInSurah": 85,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3874,
            "text": "Is it a calumny, gods apart from God, that you desire?",
            "numberInSurah": 86,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3875,
            "text": "What think you then of the Lord of all Being?'",
            "numberInSurah": 87,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3876,
            "text": "And he cast a glance at the stars,",
            "numberInSurah": 88,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3877,
            "text": "and he said, 'Surely I am sick.'",
            "numberInSurah": 89,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3878,
            "text": "But they went away from him, turning their backs.",
            "numberInSurah": 90,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3879,
            "text": "Then he turned to their gods, and said, 'What do you eat?",
            "numberInSurah": 91,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3880,
            "text": "What ails you, that you speak not?'",
            "numberInSurah": 92,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3881,
            "text": "And he turned upon them smiting them with his right hand.",
            "numberInSurah": 93,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3882,
            "text": "Then came the others to him hastening.",
            "numberInSurah": 94,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3883,
            "text": "He said, 'Do you serve what you hew,",
            "numberInSurah": 95,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3884,
            "text": "and God created you and what you make?'",
            "numberInSurah": 96,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3885,
            "text": "They said, 'Build him a building, and cast him into the furnace!'",
            "numberInSurah": 97,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3886,
            "text": "They desired to outwit him; so We made them the lower ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 98,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3887,
            "text": "He said, 'I am going to my Lord; He will guide me.",
            "numberInSurah": 99,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3888,
            "text": "My Lord, give me one of the righteous.'",
            "numberInSurah": 100,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3889,
            "text": "Then We gave him the good tidings of a prudent boy;",
            "numberInSurah": 101,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3890,
            "text": "and when he had reached the age of running with him, he said, 'My son, I see in a dream that I shall sacrifice thee; consider, what thinkest thou?' He said, 'My father, do as thou art bidden; thou shalt find me, God willing, one of the steadfast.'",
            "numberInSurah": 102,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3891,
            "text": "When they had surrendered, and he flung him upon his brow,",
            "numberInSurah": 103,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3892,
            "text": "We called unto him, 'Abraham,",
            "numberInSurah": 104,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3893,
            "text": "thou hast confirmed the vision; even so We recompense the good-doers.",
            "numberInSurah": 105,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3894,
            "text": "This is indeed the manifest trial.'",
            "numberInSurah": 106,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3895,
            "text": "And We ransomed him with a mighty sacrifice,",
            "numberInSurah": 107,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3896,
            "text": "and left for him among the later folk",
            "numberInSurah": 108,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3897,
            "text": "'Peace be upon Abraham!'",
            "numberInSurah": 109,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3898,
            "text": "Even so We recompense the good-doers;",
            "numberInSurah": 110,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3899,
            "text": "he was among Our believing servants.",
            "numberInSurah": 111,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3900,
            "text": "Then We gave him the good tidings of Isaac, a Prophet, one of the righteous.",
            "numberInSurah": 112,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3901,
            "text": "And We blessed him, and Isaac; and of their seed some are good-doers, and some manifest self-wrongers.",
            "numberInSurah": 113,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3902,
            "text": "We also favoured Moses and Aaron,",
            "numberInSurah": 114,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3903,
            "text": "and We delivered them and their people from the great distress.",
            "numberInSurah": 115,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3904,
            "text": "And We helped them, so that they were the victors;",
            "numberInSurah": 116,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3905,
            "text": "and We gave them the Manifesting Book,",
            "numberInSurah": 117,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3906,
            "text": "and guided them in the straight path,",
            "numberInSurah": 118,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3907,
            "text": "and left for them among the later folk",
            "numberInSurah": 119,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3908,
            "text": "'Peace be upon Moses and, Aaron!'",
            "numberInSurah": 120,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3909,
            "text": "Even so We recompense the good-doers;",
            "numberInSurah": 121,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3910,
            "text": "they were among Our believing servants.",
            "numberInSurah": 122,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3911,
            "text": "Elias too was one of the Envoys;",
            "numberInSurah": 123,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3912,
            "text": "when he said to his people, 'Will you not be godfearing?",
            "numberInSurah": 124,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3913,
            "text": "Do you call on Baal, and abandon the Best of creators?",
            "numberInSurah": 125,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3914,
            "text": "God, your Lord, and the Lord of your fathers, the ancients?'",
            "numberInSurah": 126,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3915,
            "text": "But they cried him lies; so they will be among the arraigned,",
            "numberInSurah": 127,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3916,
            "text": "except for God's sincere servants;",
            "numberInSurah": 128,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3917,
            "text": "and We left for him among the later folk",
            "numberInSurah": 129,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3918,
            "text": "'Peace be upon Elias!'",
            "numberInSurah": 130,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3919,
            "text": "Even so We recompense the good-doers;",
            "numberInSurah": 131,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3920,
            "text": "he was among Our believing servants.",
            "numberInSurah": 132,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3921,
            "text": "Lot too was one of the Envoys;",
            "numberInSurah": 133,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3922,
            "text": "when We delivered him and his people all together,",
            "numberInSurah": 134,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3923,
            "text": "save an old woman among those that tarried;",
            "numberInSurah": 135,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3924,
            "text": "then We destroyed the others,",
            "numberInSurah": 136,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3925,
            "text": "and you pass by them in the morning",
            "numberInSurah": 137,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3926,
            "text": "and in the night; will you not understand?",
            "numberInSurah": 138,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3927,
            "text": "Jonah too was one of the Envoys;",
            "numberInSurah": 139,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3928,
            "text": "when he ran away to the laden ship",
            "numberInSurah": 140,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3929,
            "text": "and cast lots, and was of the rebutted,",
            "numberInSurah": 141,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3930,
            "text": "then the whale swallowed him down, and he blameworthy.",
            "numberInSurah": 142,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3931,
            "text": "Now had he not been of those that glorify God,",
            "numberInSurah": 143,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3932,
            "text": "he would have tarried in its belly until the day they shall be raised;",
            "numberInSurah": 144,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3933,
            "text": "but We cast him upon the wilderness, and he was sick,",
            "numberInSurah": 145,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3934,
            "text": "and We caused to grow over him a tree of gourds.",
            "numberInSurah": 146,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3935,
            "text": "Then We sent him unto a hundred thousand, or more,",
            "numberInSurah": 147,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3936,
            "text": "and they believed; so We gave them enjoyment for a while.",
            "numberInSurah": 148,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3937,
            "text": "So ask them for a pronouncement -- Has thy Lord daughters, and they sons?",
            "numberInSurah": 149,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3938,
            "text": "Or did We create the angels females, while they were witnesses?",
            "numberInSurah": 150,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3939,
            "text": "Is it not of their own calumny that they say,",
            "numberInSurah": 151,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3940,
            "text": "'God has begotten?' They are truly liars.",
            "numberInSurah": 152,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3941,
            "text": "Has He chosen daughters above sons?",
            "numberInSurah": 153,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3942,
            "text": "What ails you then, how you judge?",
            "numberInSurah": 154,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3943,
            "text": "What, and will you not remember?",
            "numberInSurah": 155,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3944,
            "text": "Or have you a clear authority?",
            "numberInSurah": 156,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3945,
            "text": "Bring your Book, if you speak truly!",
            "numberInSurah": 157,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3946,
            "text": "They have set up a kinship between Him and the jinn; and the jinn know that they shall be arraigned.",
            "numberInSurah": 158,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3947,
            "text": "Glory be to God above that they describe,",
            "numberInSurah": 159,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3948,
            "text": "except for God's sincere servants.",
            "numberInSurah": 160,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3949,
            "text": "But as for you, and that you serve,",
            "numberInSurah": 161,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3950,
            "text": "you shall not tempt any against Him",
            "numberInSurah": 162,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3951,
            "text": "except him who shall roast in Hell.",
            "numberInSurah": 163,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3952,
            "text": "None of us is there, but has a known station;",
            "numberInSurah": 164,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3953,
            "text": "we are the rangers,",
            "numberInSurah": 165,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3954,
            "text": "we are they that give glory.",
            "numberInSurah": 166,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3955,
            "text": "What though they would say,",
            "numberInSurah": 167,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3956,
            "text": "'If only we had had a Reminder from the ancients,",
            "numberInSurah": 168,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3957,
            "text": "then were we God's sincere servants.'",
            "numberInSurah": 169,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3958,
            "text": "But they disbelieved in it; soon they shall know!",
            "numberInSurah": 170,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3959,
            "text": "Already Our Word has preceded to Our servants, the Envoys;",
            "numberInSurah": 171,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3960,
            "text": "assuredly they shall be helped,",
            "numberInSurah": 172,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3961,
            "text": "and Our host -- they are the victors.",
            "numberInSurah": 173,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3962,
            "text": "So turn thou from them for a while,",
            "numberInSurah": 174,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3963,
            "text": "and see them; soon they shall see!",
            "numberInSurah": 175,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3964,
            "text": "What, do they seek to hasten Our chastisement?",
            "numberInSurah": 176,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3965,
            "text": "When it lights in their courtyard, how evil will be the morning of them that are warned!",
            "numberInSurah": 177,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3966,
            "text": "So turn thou from them for a while,",
            "numberInSurah": 178,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3967,
            "text": "and see; soon they shall see!",
            "numberInSurah": 179,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3968,
            "text": "Glory be to thy Lord, the Lord of Glory, above that they describe!",
            "numberInSurah": 180,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3969,
            "text": "And peace be upon the Envoys;",
            "numberInSurah": 181,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3970,
            "text": "and praise belongs to God, the Lord of all Being.",
            "numberInSurah": 182,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 38,
        "name": "سُورَةُ صٓ",
        "englishName": "Saad",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The letter Saad",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3971,
            "text": "Sad. By the Koran, containing the Remembrance --",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3972,
            "text": "nay, but the unbelievers glory in their schism.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3973,
            "text": "How many a generation We destroyed before them, and they called, but time was none to escape.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3974,
            "text": "Now they marvel that a warner has come to them from among them; and the unbelievers say, 'This is a lying sorcerer.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3975,
            "text": "What, has he made the gods One God? This is indeed a marvellous thing.'",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3976,
            "text": "And the Council of them depart, saying 'Go! Be steadfast to your gods; this is a thing to be desired.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3977,
            "text": "We have not heard of this in the last religion; this is surely an invention.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3978,
            "text": "What, has the Remembrance been sent down on him out of us all?' Nay, but they are in doubt of My Remembrance; nay, they have not yet tasted My chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3979,
            "text": "Or have they the treasuries of thy Lord's mercy, the All-mighty, the All-giving?",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3980,
            "text": "Or is theirs the kingdom of the heavens and earth and of what between them is? Why, then let them ascend the cords!",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3981,
            "text": "A very host of parties is routed there!",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3982,
            "text": "Cried lies before them the people of Noah, and Ad, and Pharaoh, he of the tent-pegs,",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3983,
            "text": "and Thamood, and the people of Lot, and the men of the Thicket - those were the parties;",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3984,
            "text": "not one, that cried not lies to the Messengers, so My retribution was just.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3985,
            "text": "These are only awaiting for a single Cry, to which there is no delay.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3986,
            "text": "They say, 'Our Lord, hasten to us our share before the Day of Reckoning.'",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3987,
            "text": "Bear patiently what they say, and remember Our servant David, the man of might; he was a penitent.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3988,
            "text": "With him We subjected the mountains to give glory at evening and sunrise,",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3989,
            "text": "and the birds, duly mustered, every one to him reverting;",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3990,
            "text": "We strengthened his kingdom, and gave him wisdom and speech decisive.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3991,
            "text": "Has the tiding of the dispute come to thee? When they scaled the Sanctuary,",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3992,
            "text": "when they entered upon David, and he took fright at them; and they said, 'Fear not; two disputants we are -- one of us has injured the other; so judge between us justly, and transgress not, and guide us to the right path.'",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3993,
            "text": "'Behold, this my brother has ninety-nine ewes, and I have one ewe. So he said, 'Give her into my charge'; and he overcame me in the argument.'",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3994,
            "text": "Said he, 'Assuredly he has wronged thee in asking for thy ewe in addition to his sheep; and indeed many intermixers do injury one against the other, save those who believe, and do deeds of righteousness -- and how few they are!' And David thought that We had only tried him; therefore he sought forgiveness of his Lord, and he fell down, bowing, and he repented.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": {
              "id": 11,
              "recommended": true,
              "obligatory": false
            }
          },
          {
            "number": 3995,
            "text": "Accordingly We forgave him that, and he has a near place in Our presence and a fair resort.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3996,
            "text": "'David, behold, We have appointed thee a viceroy in the earth; therefore judge between men justly, and follow not caprice, lest it lead thee astray from the way of God. Surely those who go astray from the way of God -- there awaits them a terrible chastisement, for that they have forgotten the Day of Reckoning.'",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3997,
            "text": "We have not created the heavens and earth, and what between them is, for vanity; such is the thought of the unbelievers, wherefore woe unto the unbelievers because of the Fire!",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3998,
            "text": "Or shall We make those who believe and do righteous deeds as the workers of corruption in the earth, or shall We make the godfearing as the transgressors?",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3999,
            "text": "A Book We have sent down to thee, Blessed, that men possessed of minds may ponder its signs and so remember.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4000,
            "text": "And We gave unto David Solomon; how excellent a servant he was! He was a penitent.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4001,
            "text": "When in the evening were presented to him the standing steeds,",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4002,
            "text": "he said, 'Lo, I have loved the love of good things better than the remembrance of my Lord, until the sun was bidden behind the veil.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4003,
            "text": "Return them to me!' And he began to stroke their shanks and necks.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4004,
            "text": "Certainly We tried Solomon, and We cast upon his throne a mere body; then he repented.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4005,
            "text": "He said, 'My Lord, forgive me, and give me a kingdom such as may not befall anyone after me; surely Thou art the All-giver.'",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4006,
            "text": "So We subjected to him the wind, that ran at his commandment, softly, wherever he might light on,",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4007,
            "text": "and the Satans, every builder and diver",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4008,
            "text": "and others also, coupled in fetters:",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4009,
            "text": "'This is Our gift; bestow or withhold without reckoning.'",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4010,
            "text": "And he had a near place in Our presence and a fair resort.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4011,
            "text": "Remember also Our servant Job; when he called to his Lord, 'Behold, Satan has visited me with weariness and chastisement.'",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4012,
            "text": "'Stamp thy foot! This is a laving-place cool, and a drink.'",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4013,
            "text": "And We gave to him his family, and the like of them with them, as a mercy from us, and a reminder unto men possessed of minds;",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4014,
            "text": "and, 'Take in thy hand a bundle of rushes, and strike therewith, and do not fail in thy oath.' Surely We found him a steadfast man. How excellent a servant he was! He was a penitent.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4015,
            "text": "Remember also Our servants Abraham, Isaac and Jacob -- men of might they and of vision.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4016,
            "text": "Assuredly We purified them with a quality most pure, the remembrance of the Abode,",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4017,
            "text": "and in Our sight they are of the chosen, the excellent.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4018,
            "text": "Remember also Our servants Ishmael, Elisha, and Dhul Kifl; each is among the excellent.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4019,
            "text": "This is a Remembrance; and for the godfearing is a fair resort,",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4020,
            "text": "Gardens of Eden, whereof the gates are open to them,",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4021,
            "text": "wherein they recline, and wherein they call for fruits abundant, and sweet potions,",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4022,
            "text": "and with them maidens restraining their glances of equal age.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4023,
            "text": "'This is what you were promised for the Day of Reckoning;",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4024,
            "text": "this is Our provision, unto which there is no end.'",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4025,
            "text": "All this; but for the insolent awaits an ill resort,",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4026,
            "text": "Gehenna, wherein they are roasted - an evil cradling!",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4027,
            "text": "All this; so let them taste it - boiling water and pus,",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4028,
            "text": "and other torments of the like kind coupled together.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4029,
            "text": "'This is a troop rushing in with you; there is no Welcome for them; they shall roast in the Fire.'",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4030,
            "text": "They say, 'No, it is you have no Welcome; you forwarded it for us; how evil a stablishment!'",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4031,
            "text": "They say, 'Our Lord, whoso forwarded this for us, give him a double chastisement in the Fire!'",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4032,
            "text": "They say, 'How is it with us, that we do not see men here that we counted among the wicked?",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4033,
            "text": "What, did we take them for a laughing-stock? Or have our eyes swerved away from them?'",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4034,
            "text": "Surely that is true -- the disputing of the inhabitants of the Fire.",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4035,
            "text": "Say: 'I am only a warner. There is not any god but God, the One, the Omnipotent,",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4036,
            "text": "Lord of the heavens and earth, and of what between them is, the All-mighty, the All-forgiving.'",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4037,
            "text": "Say: 'It is a mighty tiding",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4038,
            "text": "from which you are turning away.",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4039,
            "text": "I had no knowledge of the High Council when they disputed.",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4040,
            "text": "This alone is revealed to me, that I am only a clear warner.'",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4041,
            "text": "When thy Lord said to the angels, 'See, I am creating a mortal of a clay.",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4042,
            "text": "When I have shaped him, and breathed My spirit in him, fall you down, bowing before him!'",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4043,
            "text": "Then the angels bowed themselves all together,",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4044,
            "text": "save Iblis; he waxed proud, and was one of the unbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4045,
            "text": "Said He, 'Iblis, what prevented thee to bow thyself before that I created with My own hands? Hast thou waxed proud, or art thou of the lofty ones?'",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4046,
            "text": "Said he, 'I am better than he; Thou createdst me of fire, and him Thou createdst of clay.'",
            "numberInSurah": 76,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4047,
            "text": "Said He, 'Then go thou forth hence; thou art accursed.",
            "numberInSurah": 77,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4048,
            "text": "Upon thee shall rest My curse, till the Day of Doom.'",
            "numberInSurah": 78,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4049,
            "text": "Said he, 'My Lord, respite me till the day they shall be raised.'",
            "numberInSurah": 79,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4050,
            "text": "Said He, 'Thou art among the ones that are respited",
            "numberInSurah": 80,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4051,
            "text": "until the day of the known time.'",
            "numberInSurah": 81,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4052,
            "text": "Said he, 'Now, by Thy glory, I shall pervert them all together,",
            "numberInSurah": 82,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4053,
            "text": "excepting those Thy servants among them that are sincere.'",
            "numberInSurah": 83,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4054,
            "text": "Said He, 'This is the truth, and the truth I say;",
            "numberInSurah": 84,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4055,
            "text": "I shall assuredly fill Gehenna with thee, and with whosoever of them follows thee, all together.'",
            "numberInSurah": 85,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4056,
            "text": "Say: 'I ask of you no wage for it, neither am I of those who take things upon themselves.",
            "numberInSurah": 86,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4057,
            "text": "It is nothing but a reminder unto all beings,",
            "numberInSurah": 87,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4058,
            "text": "and you shall surely know its tiding after a while.'",
            "numberInSurah": 88,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 39,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الزُّمَرِ",
        "englishName": "Az-Zumar",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Groups",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4059,
            "text": "The sending down of the Book is from God the All-mighty, the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 396,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4060,
            "text": "We have sent down to thee the Book with the truth; so worship God, making thy religion His sincerely.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 396,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4061,
            "text": "Belongs not sincere religion to God? And those who take protectors, apart from Him -- 'We only serve them that they may bring us nigh in nearness to God' -- surely God shall judge between them touching that whereon they are at variance. Surely God guides not him who is a liar, unthankful.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 396,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4062,
            "text": "Had God desired to take to Him a son, He would have chosen whatever He willed of that He has created. Glory be to Him! He is God, the One, the Omnipotent.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 396,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4063,
            "text": "He created the heavens and the earth in truth, wrapping night about the day, and wrapping the day about the night; and He has subjected the sun and the moon, each of them running to a stated term. Is not He the All-mighty, the All-forgiving?",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 396,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4064,
            "text": "He created you of a single soul, then from it He appointed its mate; and He sent down to you of the cattle eight couples. He creates you in your mothers' wombs creation after creation in threefold shadows. That then is God, your Lord; to Him belongs the Kingdom; there is no god but He; so how are you turned about?",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 459,
            "ruku": 396,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4065,
            "text": "If you are unthankful, God is independent of you, yet He approves not unthankfulness in His servants; but if you are thankful, He will approve it in you. And no soul laden bears the load of another. Then to your Lord shall you return, and He will tell you what you have been doing. He knows the thoughts within the breasts.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 459,
            "ruku": 396,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4066,
            "text": "When some affliction visits a man, he calls upon his Lord, turning to him; then when He confers on him a blessing from Him he forgets that he was calling to before and sets up compeers to God, to lead astray from His way. Say: 'Enjoy thy unbelief a little; thou shalt be among the inhabitants of the Fire.'",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 459,
            "ruku": 396,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4067,
            "text": "Or is he who is obedient in the watches of the night, bowing himself and standing, he being afraid of the world to come and hoping for the mercy of his Lord..? Say: 'Are they equal -- those who know and those who know not?' Only men possessed of minds remember.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 459,
            "ruku": 396,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4068,
            "text": "Say: 'My servants who believe, fear your Lord. For those who do good in this world good, and God's earth is wide. Surely the patient will be paid their wages in full without reckoning.'",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 459,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4069,
            "text": "Say: 'I have been commanded to serve God making my religion His sincerely;",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4070,
            "text": "and I have been commanded to be the first of those that surrender.'",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4071,
            "text": "Say: 'Truly I fear, if I should rebel against my Lord, the chastisement of a dreadful day.'",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4072,
            "text": "Say: 'God I serve, making my religion His sincerely;",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4073,
            "text": "so serve what you will apart from Him.' Say: 'Surely the losers are they who lose themselves and their families on the Day of Resurrection; is not that the manifest loss?",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4074,
            "text": "Above them they shall have overshadowings. of the Fire, and underneath them overshadowings; that it is wherewith God frightens His servants: 'O My servants, so fear you Me!''",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4075,
            "text": "Those who eschew the serving of idols and turn penitent to God, for them is good tidings! So give thou good tidings to My servants",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4076,
            "text": "who give ear to the Word and follow the fairest of it. Those are they whom God has guided; those -- they are men possessed of minds.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4077,
            "text": "He against whom the word of chastisement is realized -- shalt thou deliver him out of the Fire?",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4078,
            "text": "But those who fear their Lord -- for them await lofty chambers, above which are built lofty chambers, underneath which rivers flow -- God's promise; God fails not the tryst.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4079,
            "text": "Hast thou not seen how that God has sent down out of heaven water and threaded it as springs in the earth, then He brings forth therewith crops of diverse hues, then they wither, and thou seest them turning yellow, then He makes them broken orts? Surely in that is a reminder for men possessed of minds.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4080,
            "text": "Is he whose breast God has expanded unto Islam, so he walks in a light from his Lord...? But woe to those whose hearts are hardened against the remembrance of God! Those are in manifest error.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4081,
            "text": "God has sent down the fairest discourse as a Book, consimilar in its oft-repeated, whereat shiver the skins of those who fear their Lord; then their skins and their hearts soften to the remembrance of God. That is God's guidance, whereby. He guides whomsoever He will; and whomsoever God leads astray, no guide has he.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4082,
            "text": "Is he who guards himself with his face against the evil of the chastisement on the Day of Resurrection...? And it is said to the evildoers, 'Taste now that you were earning!'",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4083,
            "text": "Those that were before them cried lies, then the chastisement came upon them from whence they were not aware;",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4084,
            "text": "so God let them taste degradation in this present life; and the chastisement of the world to come is assuredly greater, did they but know.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4085,
            "text": "Indeed We have struck for the people in this Koran every manner of similitude; haply they will remember;",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4086,
            "text": "Koran, wherein there is no crookedness; haply they will be godfearing.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4087,
            "text": "God has struck a similitude -- a man in whom partners disagreeing share, and a man the property of one man. Are the two equal in likeness? Praise belongs to God! Nay, but most of them do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4088,
            "text": "Thou art mortal, and they are mortal;",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4089,
            "text": "then on the Day of Resurrection before your Lord you shall dispute.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4090,
            "text": "But who does greater evil than he who lies against God and cries lies to the very truth, when it comes to him? Is there not in Gehenna a lodging for the unbelievers?",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 462,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4091,
            "text": "And he who has come with the very truth and confirms it, those they are the godfearing.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 462,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4092,
            "text": "They shall have whatsoever they will with their Lord; that is the recompense of the good-doers,",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 462,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4093,
            "text": "that God may acquit them of the worst of what they did, and recompense them with the wages of the fairest of what they were doing.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 462,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4094,
            "text": "Shall not God suffice His servant, though they frighten thee with those apart from Him? And whomsoever God leads astray, no guide has he.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 462,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4095,
            "text": "But whomso God guides, none shall lead him astray; is not God All-mighty, All-vengeful?",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 462,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4096,
            "text": "If thou askest them, 'Who created the heavens and the earth?' they will say, 'God.' Say: 'What think you? That you call upon apart from God -- if God desires affliction for me, shall they remove His affliction? Or if He desires mercy for me, shall they withhold His mercy?' Say: 'God is enough for me; in Him all those put their trust who put their trust.'",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 462,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4097,
            "text": "Say: 'My people, act according to your station; I am acting; and soon you will know",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 462,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4098,
            "text": "to whom will come a chastisement degrading him, and upon whom lights a lasting chastisement.'",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 462,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4099,
            "text": "Surely We have sent down upon thee the Book for mankind with the truth. Whosoever is guided, is only guided to his own gain, and whosoever goes astray, it is only to his own loss; thou art not a guardian over them.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 463,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4100,
            "text": "God takes the souls at the time of their death, and that which has not died, in its sleep; He withholds that against which He has decreed death, but looses the other till a stated term. Surely in that are signs for a people who reflect. Or have they taken intercessors apart from God?",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 463,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4101,
            "text": "Say: 'What, even though they have no power whatever and no understanding?'",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 463,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4102,
            "text": "Say: 'To God belongs intercession altogether. His is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth; then unto Him you will be returned.'",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 463,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4103,
            "text": "When God is mentioned alone, then shudder the hearts of those who believe not in the Hereafter, but when those apart from Him are mentioned behold, they rejoice.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 463,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4104,
            "text": "Say: 'O God, Thou originator of the heavens and the earth who knowest the Unseen and the Visible, Thou shalt judge between Thy servants touching that whereon they are at variance.'",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 463,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4105,
            "text": "If the evildoers possessed all that is in the earth, and the like of it with it, they would offer it to ransom themselves from the evil of the chastisement on the Day of Resurrection; yet there would appear to them from God that they never reckoned with,",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 463,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4106,
            "text": "and there would appear to them die evils of that they have earned, and they would be encompassed by that they mocked at.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 464,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4107,
            "text": "When some affliction visits a man, he calls unto Us; then, when We confer on him a blessing from Us, he says, 'I was given it only because of a knowledge.' Nay, it is a trial, but most of them do not know it.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 464,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4108,
            "text": "So said those that were before them; but that they earned did not avail them,",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 464,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4109,
            "text": "in that the evils of that they earned smote them. The evildoers of these men, they too shall be smitten by the evils -- of that they earned; they will not be able to frustrate it.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 464,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4110,
            "text": "Do they know that God outspreads and straitens His provision to whomsoever He will? Surely in that are signs for a people who believe.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 464,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4111,
            "text": "Say: 'O my people who have been prodigal against yourselves, do not despair of God's mercy; surely God forgives sins altogether; surely He is the All-forgiving, the All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 464,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4112,
            "text": "Turn unto your Lord and surrender to Him, ere the chastisement comes upon you, then you will not be helped.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 464,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4113,
            "text": "And follow the fairest of what has been sent down to you from your Lord, ere the chastisement comes upon you suddenly while you are unaware.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 464,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4114,
            "text": "Lest any soul should say, 'Alas for me, in that I neglected my duty to God, and was a scoffer,'",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 464,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4115,
            "text": "or lest it should say, 'If only God had guided me, I should have been or lest among the godfearing,'",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4116,
            "text": "it should say, when it sees the chastisement, 'O that I might return again, and be among the good-doers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4117,
            "text": "'Yes indeed! My signs did come to thee, but thou hast cried them lies, and thou hast waxed proud, and become one of the unbelievers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4118,
            "text": "And upon the Day of Resurrection thou shalt see those who lied against God, their faces blackened; is there not in Gehenna a lodging for those that are proud?",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4119,
            "text": "But God shall deliver those that were godfearing in their security; evil shall not visit them, neither shall they sorrow.",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4120,
            "text": "God is the Creator of every thing; He is Guardian over every thing;",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4121,
            "text": "unto Him belong the keys of the heavens and the earth. And those who disbelieve in the signs of God, those they are the losers.",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4122,
            "text": "Say: 'Is it other than God you bid me serve, you ignorant ones?'",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 402,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4123,
            "text": "It has been revealed to thee, and to those before thee, 'If thou associatest other gods with God, thy work shall surely fail and thou wilt be among the losers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 402,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4124,
            "text": "Nay, but God do thou serve; and be thou among the thankful.",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 402,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4125,
            "text": "They measure not God with His true measure. The earth altogether shall be His handful on the Day of Resurrection, and the heavens shall be rolled up in His right hand. Glory be to Him! High be He exalted above that they associate!",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 402,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4126,
            "text": "For the Trumpet shall be blown, and whosoever is in the heavens and whosoever is in the earth shall swoon, save whom God wills. Then it shall be blown again, and lo, they shall stand, beholding.",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 466,
            "ruku": 402,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4127,
            "text": "And the earth shall shine with the light of its Lord, and the Book shall be set in place, and the Prophets and witnesses shall be brought, and justly the issue be decided between them, and they not wronged.",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 466,
            "ruku": 402,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4128,
            "text": "Every soul shall be paid in full for what it has wrought; and He knows very well what they do.",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 466,
            "ruku": 402,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4129,
            "text": "Then the unbelievers shall be driven in companies into Gehenna till, when they have come thither, then its gates will be opened and its keepers will say to them, 'Did not Messengers come to you from among yourselves, reciting to you the signs of your Lord and warning you against the encounter of this your day?' They shall say, 'Yes indeed; but the word of the chastisement has been realized against the unbelievers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 466,
            "ruku": 403,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4130,
            "text": "It shall be said, 'Enter the gates of Gehenna, to dwell therein forever.' How evil is the lodging of those that are proud!",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 466,
            "ruku": 403,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4131,
            "text": "Then those that feared their Lord shall be driven in companies into Paradise, till, when they have come thither, and its gates are opened, and its keepers will say to them, 'Peace be upon you! Well you have fared; enter in, to dwell forever.'",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 466,
            "ruku": 403,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4132,
            "text": "And they shall say, 'Praise belongs to God, who has been true in His promise to us, and has bequeathed upon us the earth, for us to make our dwelling wheresoever we will in Paradise.' How excellent is the wage of those that labour!",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 466,
            "ruku": 403,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4133,
            "text": "And thou shalt see the angels encircling about the Throne proclaiming the praise of their Lord; and justly the issue shall be decided between them; and it shall be said, 'Praise belongs to God, the Lord of all Being.'",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 467,
            "ruku": 403,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 40,
        "name": "سُورَةُ غَافِرٍ",
        "englishName": "Ghafir",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Forgiver",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4134,
            "text": "Ha Mim",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 467,
            "ruku": 404,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4135,
            "text": "The sending down of the Book is from God the All-mighty, the All-knowing,",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 467,
            "ruku": 404,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4136,
            "text": "Forgiver of sins, Accepter of penitence, Terrible in retribution, the Bountiful; there is no god but He, and unto Him is the homecoming.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 467,
            "ruku": 404,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4137,
            "text": "None but the unbelievers dispute concerning the signs of God; so let not their going to and fro in the land delude thee.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 467,
            "ruku": 404,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4138,
            "text": "The people of Noah before them also cried lies, and the parties after them; every nation purposed against their Messenger to seize him, and disputed with falsehood that they might rebut thereby the truth. Then I seized them; and how was My retribution!",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 467,
            "ruku": 404,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4139,
            "text": "Even so the Word of thy Lord was realised against the unbelievers, that they are the inhabitants of the Fire.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 467,
            "ruku": 404,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4140,
            "text": "Those who bear the Throne, and those round about it proclaim the praise of their Lord, and believe in Him, and they ask forgiveness for those who believe: 'Our Lord, Thou embracest every thing in mercy and knowledge; therefore forgive those who have repented, and follow Thy way, and guard them against the chastisement of Hell.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 467,
            "ruku": 404,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4141,
            "text": "Our Lord, and admit them to the Gardens of Eden that Thou hast promised them and those who were righteous of their fathers, and their wives, and their seed; surely Thou art the All-mighty, the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 468,
            "ruku": 404,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4142,
            "text": "And guard them against evil deeds; whomsoever Thou guardest against evil deeds on that day, on him Thou hast had mercy; and that is indeed the mighty triumph.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 468,
            "ruku": 404,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4143,
            "text": "It shall be proclaimed to the unbelievers, 'Surely God's hatred is greater than your hatred one of another, when you were called unto belief, and disbelieved.'",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 468,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4144,
            "text": "They shall say, 'Our Lord, Thou hast caused us to die two deaths and Thou hast given us twice to live; now we confess our sins. Is there any way to go forth?'",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 468,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4145,
            "text": "That is because, when God was called to alone, you disbelieved; but if others are associated with Him, then you believe. Judgment belongs to God, the All-high, the All-great.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 468,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4146,
            "text": "It is He who shows you His signs and sends down to you out of heaven provision; yet none remembers but he who repents.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 468,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4147,
            "text": "So call unto God, making your religion His sincerely, though the unbelievers be averse.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 468,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4148,
            "text": "Exalter of ranks is He, Possessor of the Throne, casting the Spirit of His bidding upon whomever He will of His servants, that he may warn them of the Day of Encounter,",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 468,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4149,
            "text": "the day they sally forth, and naught of theirs is hidden from God. 'Whose is' the Kingdom today?' 'God's, the One, the Omnipotent.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 468,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4150,
            "text": "Today each soul shall be recompensed for that it has earned; no wrong today. Surely God is swift at the reckoning.'",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 469,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4151,
            "text": "And warn them against the Day of the Imminent when, choking with anguish, the hearts are in the throats and the evildoers have not one loyal friend, no intercessor to be heeded.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 469,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4152,
            "text": "He knows the treachery of the eyes and what the breasts conceal.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 469,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4153,
            "text": "God shall decide justly, and those they call on, apart from Him, shall not decide by any means. surely God is the All-hearing, the All-seeing.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 469,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4154,
            "text": "What, have they not journeyed in the land and beheld how was the end of those before them? They were stronger than themselves in might and left firmer traces in the earth; yet God seized them in their sins, and they had none to defend them from God.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 469,
            "ruku": 406,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4155,
            "text": "That was because their Messengers came to them with the clear signs; but they disbelieved, so God seized them. Surely He is All-strong, terrible in retribution.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 469,
            "ruku": 406,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4156,
            "text": "We also sent Moses with Our signs and a clear authority,",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 469,
            "ruku": 406,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4157,
            "text": "to Pharaoh, Haman and Korah; they said, 'A lying sorcerer!'",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 469,
            "ruku": 406,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4158,
            "text": "And when he brought them the truth from Us, they said, 'Slay the sons of those who believe with him, and spare their women.' But the guile of the unbelievers is ever in error.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 469,
            "ruku": 406,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4159,
            "text": "And Pharaoh said, 'Let me slay Moses, and let him call to his Lord. I fear that he may change, your religion, or that he may cause corruption to appear in the land.'",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 470,
            "ruku": 406,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4160,
            "text": "And Moses said, 'I take refuge in my Lord and your Lord from every man who is proud, and believes not in the Day of Reckoning.'",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 470,
            "ruku": 406,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4161,
            "text": "Then said a certain man, a believer 'of Pharaoh's folk that kept hidden his belief, 'What, will you slay a man because he says, 'My Lord is God,' yet he has brought you the clear signs from your Lord? If he is a liar, his lying is upon his own head; but if he is truthful, somewhat of that he promises you will smite you. Surely God guides not him who is prodigal and a liar.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 470,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4162,
            "text": "O my people, today the kingdom is yours, who are masters in the land. But who will help us, against the might of God, if it comes upon us?' Said Pharaoh, 'I only let you see what I see; I only guide you in the way of rectitude.'",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 470,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4163,
            "text": "Then said he who believed, 'My people, truly I fear for you the like of the day of the parties,",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 470,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4164,
            "text": "the like of the case of Noah's people, Ad, Thamood, and those after them; and God desires not wrong for His servants.'",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 470,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4165,
            "text": "O my people, I fear for you the Day of Invocation,",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 470,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4166,
            "text": "the day you turn about, retreating, having none to defend you from God; and whomsoever God leads astray, no guide has he.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 470,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4167,
            "text": "Joseph brought you the clear signs before, yet you continued in doubt concerning that he brought you until, when he perished, you said, 'God will never send forth a Messenger after him.' Even, so God leads astray the prodigal and the doubter.'",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 471,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4168,
            "text": "(Those who dispute concerning the signs of God, without any authority come to them, very hateful is that in the sight of God and the believers; 'so God sets a seal on every heart proud', arrogant.)",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 471,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4169,
            "text": "Pharaoh said, 'Haman, build for me a tower, that haply so I may reach the cords,",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 471,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4170,
            "text": "the cords of the heavens, and look upon Moses' God; for I think that he is a liar.' So the evil of his deeds was decked out fair to Pharaoh, and he was barred from the way, and Pharaoh's guile came only to ruin.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 471,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4171,
            "text": "Then said he who believed, 'My people, follow me, and I will guide you in the way of rectitude.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 471,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4172,
            "text": "O my people, surely this present life is but a passing enjoyment; surely the world to come is the abode of stability.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 471,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4173,
            "text": "Whosoever does an evil deed shall be recompensed only with the like of it, but whosoever does a righteous deed, be it male or female, believing -- those shall enter Paradise, therein provided without reckoning.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 471,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4174,
            "text": "O my people, how is it with me, that I call you to salvation, and you call me to the Fire?",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 472,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4175,
            "text": "You call me to disbelieve in God, and to associate with Him that whereof I have no knowledge, while I call you to the All-mighty, the All-forgiving.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 472,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4176,
            "text": "No doubt that what you call me to has no call heard, in this world or in the world to come, that to God we return, and that the prodigal are the inhabitants of the Fire.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 472,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4177,
            "text": "You will remember what I say to you. I commit my affair to God; surely God sees His servants.'",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 472,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4178,
            "text": "So God guarded him against the evil things of their devising, and there encompassed the folk of Pharaoh the evil chastisement,",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 472,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4179,
            "text": "the Fire, to which they shall be exposed morning and evening; and on the day when the Hour is come: 'Admit the folk of Pharaoh into the most terrible chastisement!'",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 472,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4180,
            "text": "And when they argue one with the other in the Fire, and the weak say unto those who waxed proud, 'Why, we were your followers; will you avail us now against any part of the Fire?'",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 472,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4181,
            "text": "Then those who waxed proud shall say, 'Every one of us is in it; indeed, God already has passed judgment between His servants.'",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 472,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4182,
            "text": "And those who are in the Fire will say to the keepers of Gehenna, 'Call on your Lord, to lighten for us one day of the chastisement!'",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 472,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4183,
            "text": "They shall say, 'Did not your Messengers bring you the clear signs?' They shall say, 'Yes indeed.' They shall say, 'Then do you call!' But the calling of the unbelievers is only in error.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 473,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4184,
            "text": "Surely We shall help Our Messengers and those who have believed, in the present life, and upon the day when the witnesses arise,",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 473,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4185,
            "text": "upon the day when their excuses shall not profit the evildoers, and theirs shall be the curse, and theirs the evil abode.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 473,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4186,
            "text": "We also gave Moses the guidance, and We bequeathed upon the Children of Israel the Book",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 473,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4187,
            "text": "for a guidance and for a reminder to men possessed of minds.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 473,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4188,
            "text": "So be thou patient; surely God's promise is true. And ask forgiveness for thy sin, and proclaim the praise of thy Lord at evening and dawn.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 473,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4189,
            "text": "Those who dispute concerning the signs of God, without any authority come to them, in their breasts is only pride, that they shall never attain. So seek thou refuge in God; surely He is the All-hearing, the All-seeing.",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 473,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4190,
            "text": "Certainly the creation of the heavens and earth is greater than the creation of men; but most men know it not.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 473,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4191,
            "text": "Not equal are the blind and the seeing man, those who believe and do deeds of righteousness, and the wrong-doer. Little do you reflect.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 473,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4192,
            "text": "The Hour is coming, no doubt of it, but most men do not believe.",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 474,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4193,
            "text": "Your Lord has said, 'Call upon Me and I will answer you. Surely those who wax too proud to do Me service shall enter Gehenna utterly abject.'",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 474,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4194,
            "text": "It is God who made for you the night, to repose in it, and the day, to see. Surely God is bountiful to men, but most men are not thankful.",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 474,
            "ruku": 410,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4195,
            "text": "That then is God, your Lord, the Creator of everything; there is no god but He. How then are you perverted?",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 474,
            "ruku": 410,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4196,
            "text": "Even so perverted are they who deny the signs of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 474,
            "ruku": 410,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4197,
            "text": "It is God who made for you the earth a fixed place and heaven for an edifice; And He shaped you, and shaped you well, and provided you with the good things. That then is God, your Lord, so blessed be God, the Lord of all Being.",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 474,
            "ruku": 410,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4198,
            "text": "He is the Living One; there is no god but He. So call upon Him, making your religion His sincerely. Praise belongs to God, the Lord of all Being.",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 474,
            "ruku": 410,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4199,
            "text": "Say: 'I am forbidden to serve those you call on apart from God once the clear signs came to me from my Lord; and I am commanded to surrender to the Lord of All Being.'",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 474,
            "ruku": 410,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4200,
            "text": "It is He who created you of dust then of a sperm-drop, then of a blood-clot, then He delivers you as infants, then that you may come of age, then that you may be old men -- though some of you there are who die before it -- and that you may reach a stated term; haply you will understand.",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 410,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4201,
            "text": "It is He who gives life, and makes to die; and when He decrees a thing, He but says to it 'Be,' and it is.",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 410,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4202,
            "text": "Hast thou not regarded those who dispute concerning the signs of God, how they are turned about?",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4203,
            "text": "Those who cry lies to the Book and that wherewith We sent Our Messengers -- soon they will know!",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4204,
            "text": "When the fetters and chains are on their necks, and they dragged",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4205,
            "text": "into the boiling water, then into the Fire they are poured;",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4206,
            "text": "then it is said to them, 'Where are those you associated, apart from God?'",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4207,
            "text": "They shall say, 'They have gone astray from us; nay, but it was nothing at all that we called upon aforetime.' Even so God leads astray the unbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4208,
            "text": "'That is because you rejoiced in the earth without right, and were exultant.",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4209,
            "text": "Enter the gates of Gehenna, to dwell therein forever.' How evil is the lodging of those that are proud!",
            "numberInSurah": 76,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4210,
            "text": "So be thou patient; surely God's promise is true. Whether We show thee a part of that We promise them, or We call thee unto Us, to Us they shall be returned.",
            "numberInSurah": 77,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4211,
            "text": "We sent Messengers before thee; of some We have related to thee, and some We have not related to thee. It was not for any Messenger to bring a sign, save by God's leave. When God's command comes, justly the issue shall be decided; then the vain-doers shall be lost.",
            "numberInSurah": 78,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 476,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4212,
            "text": "It is God who appointed for you the cattle, some of them to ride and of some you eat;",
            "numberInSurah": 79,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 476,
            "ruku": 412,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4213,
            "text": "other uses also you have in them; and that on them you may attain a need in your breasts, and upon them and on the ships you are carried.",
            "numberInSurah": 80,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 476,
            "ruku": 412,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4214,
            "text": "And He shows you His signs; then which of God's signs do you reject?",
            "numberInSurah": 81,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 476,
            "ruku": 412,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4215,
            "text": "What, have they not journeyed in the land and beheld how was the end of those before them? They were stronger than themselves in might and left firmer traces in the earth; yet that they earned did not avail them.",
            "numberInSurah": 82,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 476,
            "ruku": 412,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4216,
            "text": "So, when their Messengers brought them the clear signs, they rejoiced in what knowledge they had, and were encompassed by that they mocked at.",
            "numberInSurah": 83,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 476,
            "ruku": 412,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4217,
            "text": "Then, when they saw Our might, they said, 'We believe in God alone, and we disbelieve in that we were associating with Him.'",
            "numberInSurah": 84,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 476,
            "ruku": 412,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4218,
            "text": "But their belief when they saw Our might did not profit them -- the wont of God, as in the past, touching His servants; then the unbelievers shall be lost.",
            "numberInSurah": 85,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 476,
            "ruku": 412,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 41,
        "name": "سُورَةُ فُصِّلَتۡ",
        "englishName": "Fussilat",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Explained in detail",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4219,
            "text": "Ha Mim",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 413,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4220,
            "text": "A sending down from the Merciful, the Compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 413,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4221,
            "text": "A Book whose signs have been distinguished as an Arabic Koran for a people having knowledge,",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 413,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4222,
            "text": "good tidings to bear, and warning, but most of them have turned away, and do not give ear.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 413,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4223,
            "text": "They say, 'Our hearts are veiled from what thou callest us to, and in our ears is a heaviness, and between us and thee there is a veil; so act; we are acting!'",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 413,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4224,
            "text": "Say: 'I am only a mortal, like you are. To me it has been revealed that your God is One God; so go straight with Him, and ask for His forgiveness; and woe to the idolaters",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 413,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4225,
            "text": "who pay not the alms, and disbelieve in the world to come.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 413,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4226,
            "text": "Surely those who believe, and do righteous deeds shall have a wage unfailing.'",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 413,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4227,
            "text": "Say: 'What, do you disbelieve in Him who created the earth in two days, and do you set up compeers to Him? That is the Lord of all Being.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4228,
            "text": "'And He set therein firm mountains over it, and He blessed it, and He ordained therein its diverse sustenance in four days, equal to those who ask.'",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4229,
            "text": "Then He lifted Himself to heaven when it was smoke, and said to it and to the earth, 'Come willingly, or unwillingly!' They said, 'We come willingly.'",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4230,
            "text": "So He determined them as seven heavens in two days, and revealed its commandment in every heaven.'",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 478,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4231,
            "text": "And We adorned the lower heaven with lamps, and to reserve; that is the ordaining of the All-mighty, the All-knowing. But if they turn away, then say, 'I warn you of a thunderbolt like to the thunderbolt of Ad and Thamood.'",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 478,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4232,
            "text": "When the Messengers came unto them from before them and from behind them, saying, 'Serve none but God,' they said, 'Had our Lord willed, surely He would have sent down angels; so we disbelieve in the Message you were sent with.'",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 478,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4233,
            "text": "As for Ad, they waxed proud in the earth without right, and they said, 'Who is stronger than we in might?' What, did they not see that God, who created them, was stronger than they in might? And they denied Our signs.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 478,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4234,
            "text": "Then We loosed against them a wind clamorous in days of ill fortune, that We might let them taste the chastisement of degradation in the present life; and the chastisement of the world to come is even more degrading, and they shall not be helped.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 478,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4235,
            "text": "As for Thamood, We guided them, but they preferred blindness above guidance, so the thunderbolt of the chastisement of humiliation seized them for that they were earning.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 478,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4236,
            "text": "And We delivered those who believed and were godfearing.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 478,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4237,
            "text": "Upon the day when God's enemies are mustered to the Fire, duly disposed,",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 478,
            "ruku": 415,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4238,
            "text": "till when they are come to it, their hearing, their eyes and their skins bear witness against them concerning what they have been doing,",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 478,
            "ruku": 415,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4239,
            "text": "and they will say to their skins, 'Why bore you witness against us?' They shall say, 'God gave us speech, as He gave everything speech. He created you the first time, and unto Him you shall be returned.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 479,
            "ruku": 415,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4240,
            "text": "Not so did you cover yourselves, that your hearing, your eyes and your skins should not bear witness against you; but you thought that God would never know much of the things that you were working.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 479,
            "ruku": 415,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4241,
            "text": "That then, the thought you thought about your Lord, has destroyed you, and therefore you find yourselves this morning among the losers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 479,
            "ruku": 415,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4242,
            "text": "Then if they persist, the Fire shall be a lodging for them; and if they ask amends yet no amends shall be made to them.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 479,
            "ruku": 415,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4243,
            "text": "We have allotted them comrades, and they have decked out fair to them that which is before them and behind them. So against them has been realized the Word concerning nations that passed away before them, men and jinn alike; surely they were losers.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 479,
            "ruku": 415,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4244,
            "text": "The unbelievers say, 'Do not give ear to this Koran, and talk idly about it; haply you will overcome.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 479,
            "ruku": 416,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4245,
            "text": "So We shall let the unbelievers taste a terrible chastisement, and shall recompense them with the worst of what they were working.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 479,
            "ruku": 416,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4246,
            "text": "That is the recompense of God's enemies -- the Fire, wherein they shall have the Abode of Eternity as a recompense, for that they denied Our signs.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 479,
            "ruku": 416,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4247,
            "text": "And the unbelievers shall say, 'Our Lord, show us those that led us astray, both jinn and men, and we shall set them underneath our feet, that they may be among the lower ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 479,
            "ruku": 416,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4248,
            "text": "Those who have said, 'Our Lord is God.' then have gone straight, upon them the angels descend, saying, 'Fear not, neither sorrow; rejoice in Paradise that you were promised.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 480,
            "ruku": 416,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4249,
            "text": "We are your friends in the present life and in the world to come; therein you shall have all that your souls desire, all that you call for,",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 480,
            "ruku": 416,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4250,
            "text": "as hospitality from One All-forgiving, One All-compassionate.'",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 480,
            "ruku": 416,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4251,
            "text": "And who speaks fairer than he who calls unto God and does righteousness and says, 'Surely I am of them that surrender'?",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 480,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4252,
            "text": "Not equal are the good deed and the evil deed. Repel with that which is fairer and behold, he between whom and thee there is enmity shall be as if he were a loyal friend.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 480,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4253,
            "text": "Yet none shall receive it, except the steadfast; none shall receive it, except a man of mighty fortune.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 480,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4254,
            "text": "If a provocation from Satan should provoke thee, seek refuge in God; He is the All-hearing, the All-knowing.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 480,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4255,
            "text": "And of His signs are the night and the day, the sun and the moon. Bow not yourselves to the sun and moon, but bow yourselves to God who created them, if Him you serve.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 480,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4256,
            "text": "And if they wax proud, yet those who are with thy Lord do glorify Him by night and day, and grow not weary.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 480,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": {
              "id": 12,
              "recommended": false,
              "obligatory": true
            }
          },
          {
            "number": 4257,
            "text": "And of His signs is that thou seest the earth humble; then, when We send down water upon it, it quivers, and swells. Surely He who quickens it is He who quickens the dead; surely He is powerful over everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 481,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4258,
            "text": "Those who blaspheme Our signs are not hidden from Us. What, is he who shall be cast into the Fire better, or he who comes on the Day of Resurrection in security? Do what you will; surely He sees the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 481,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4259,
            "text": "Those who disbelieve in the Remembrance when it comes to them -- and surely it is a Book Sublime;",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 481,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4260,
            "text": "falsehood comes not to it from before it nor from behind it; a sending down from One All-wise, All-laudable.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 481,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4261,
            "text": "Naught is said to thee but what already was said to the Messengers before thee. Surely thy Lord is a Lord of forgiveness and of painful retribution.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 481,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4262,
            "text": "If We had made it a barbarous Koran, they would have said, 'Why are its signs not distinguished? What, barbarous and Arabic?' Say: 'To the believers it is a guidance, and a healing; but those who believe not, in their ears is a heaviness, and to them it is a blindness; those -- they are called from a far place.'",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 481,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4263,
            "text": "And We gave Moses the Book; and there was difference concerning it, and but for a Word that preceded from thy Lord, it had been decided between them; and they are in doubt of it disquieting.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 481,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4264,
            "text": "Whoso does righteousness, it is to his own gain, and whoso does evil, it is to his own loss. Thy Lord wrongs not His servants.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 481,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4265,
            "text": "To Him is referred the knowledge of the Hour. Not a fruit comes forth from its sheath, no female bears or brings forth, save with His knowledge. Upon the day when He shall call to them, 'Where now are My associates?' they shall say, 'We proclaim to Thee, there is not a witness among us.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 482,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4266,
            "text": "Then that they called upon before will go astray from them and they will think that they have no asylum.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 482,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4267,
            "text": "Man wearies not of praying for good; but when evil visits him, then he is cast down and desperate.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 482,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4268,
            "text": "And if We let him taste mercy from Us after hardship that has visited him, he surely says, 'This is mine; I think not the Hour is coming. If I am returned to my Lord, surely the reward most fair with Him will be mine.' Then We shall tell the unbelievers the things they have done, and assuredly We shall let them taste a harsh chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 482,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4269,
            "text": "And when We bless man, he turns away and withdraws aside; but when evil visits him, he is full of endless prayers.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 482,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4270,
            "text": "Say: 'What think you? If it is from God, then you disbelieve in it, who is further astray than he who is in wide schism?'",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 482,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4271,
            "text": "We shall show them Our signs in the horizons and in themselves, till it is clear to them that it is the truth. Suffices it not as to thy Lord, that He is witness over everything?",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 482,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4272,
            "text": "Are they not in doubt touching the encounter with their Lord? Does He not encompass everything?",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 482,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 42,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الشُّورَىٰ",
        "englishName": "Ash-Shura",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Consultation",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4273,
            "text": "Ha Mim",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 419,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4274,
            "text": "Ain Sin Qaf",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 419,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4275,
            "text": "So reveals to thee, and to those before thee, God, the All-mighty, the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 419,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4276,
            "text": "To Him belongs whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth; and He is the All-high, the All-glorious.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 419,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4277,
            "text": "The heavens wellnigh are rent above them, when the angels proclaim the praise of their Lord, and ask forgiveness for those on earth. Surely God -- He is the All-forgiving, the All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 419,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4278,
            "text": "And those who have taken to them protectors apart from Him -- God is Warden over them; thou art not a guardian over them.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 419,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4279,
            "text": "And so We have revealed to thee an Arabic Koran, that thou mayest warn the Mother of Cities and those who dwell about it, and that thou mayest warn of the Day of Gathering, wherein is no doubt -- a party in Paradise, and a party in the Blaze.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 419,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4280,
            "text": "If God had willed, He would have made them one nation; but He admits whomsoever He will into His mercy, and the evildoers shall have neither protector nor helper.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 419,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4281,
            "text": "Or have they taken to them protectors apart from Him? But God -- He is the Protector; He quickens the dead, and He is powerful over everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 419,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4282,
            "text": "And whatever you are at variance on, the judgment thereof belongs to God. That then is God, my Lord; in Him I have put my trust, and to Him I turn, penitent.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4283,
            "text": "The Originator of the heavens and the earth; He has appointed for you, of yourselves, pairs, and pairs also of the cattle, therein multiplying you. Like Him there is naught; He is the All-hearing, the All-seeing.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 484,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4284,
            "text": "To Him belong the keys of the heavens and the earth. He outspreads and straitens His provision to whom He will; surely He has knowledge of everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 484,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4285,
            "text": "He has laid down for you as religion that He charged Noah with, and that We have revealed to thee, and that We charged Abraham with, Moses and Jesus: 'Perform the religion, and scatter not regarding it. Very hateful is that for the idolaters, that thou callest them to. God chooses unto Himself whomsoever He will, and He guides to Himself whosoever turns, penitent.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 484,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4286,
            "text": "They scattered not, save after knowledge had come to them, being insolent one to another; and but for a Word that preceded from thy Lord until a stated term, it had been decided between them. But those to whom the Book has been given as an inheritance after them, behold, they are in doubt of it disquieting.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 484,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4287,
            "text": "Therefore call thou, and go straight as thou hast been commanded; do not follow their caprices. And say: 'I believe in whatever Book God has sent down; I have been commanded to be just between you. God is our Lord and your Lord. We have our deeds, and you have your deeds; there is no argument between us and you; God shall bring us together, and unto Him is the homecoming.'",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 484,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4288,
            "text": "And those who argue concerning God after that answer has been made to Him, their argument is null and void in the sight of their Lord; anger shall rest upon them, and there awaits them a terrible chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 485,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4289,
            "text": "God it is who has sent down the Book with the truth, and also the Balance. And what shall make thee know? Haply the Hour is nigh.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 485,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4290,
            "text": "Those that believe not therein seek to hasten it; but those who believe in it go in fear of it, knowing that it is the truth. Why, surely those who are in doubt concerning the Hour are indeed in far error.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 485,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4291,
            "text": "God is All-gentle to His servants, providing for whomsoever He will. He is the All-strong, the All-mighty.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 485,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4292,
            "text": "Whoso desires the tillage of the world to come, We shall give him increase in his tillage; and whoso desires the tillage of this world, We shall give him of it, but in the world to come he will have no share.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 485,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4293,
            "text": "Or have they associates who have laid down for them as religion that for which God gave not leave? But for the Word of Decision, it had been decided between them. For the evildoers there awaits a painful chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 485,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4294,
            "text": "Thou seest the evildoers going in fear of that they have earned, that is about to fall on them; but those who believe and do righteous deeds are in Meadows of the Gardens; whatsoever they will they shall have with their Lord; that is the great bounty.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 485,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4295,
            "text": "That is the good tidings God gives to His servants who believe and do righteous deeds. Say: 'I do not ask of you a wage for this, except love for the kinsfolk; and whosoever gains a good deed, We shall give him increase of good in respect of it. Surely God is All-forgiving, All-thankful.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 486,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4296,
            "text": "Or do they say, 'He has forged against God a lie?' But if God wills, He will set a seal on thy heart; and God blots out falsehood and verifies the truth by His words; He knows the thoughts within the breasts.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 486,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4297,
            "text": "It is He who accepts repentance from His servants, and pardons evil deeds; He knows the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 486,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4298,
            "text": "And He answers those who believe and do righteous deeds, and He gives them increase of His bounty. And the unbelievers -- for them awaits a terrible chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 486,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4299,
            "text": "Had God expanded His provision to His servants, they would have been insolent in the earth; but He sends down in measure whatsoever He will; surely He is aware of and sees His servants.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 486,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4300,
            "text": "And it is He who sends down the rain after they have despaired, and He unfolds His mercy; He is the Protector, the All-laudable.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 486,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4301,
            "text": "And of His signs is the creation of the heavens and earth and the crawling things He has scattered abroad in them; and He is able to gather them whenever He will.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 486,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4302,
            "text": "Whatever affliction may visit you is for what you own hands have earned; and He pardons much.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 486,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4303,
            "text": "You are not able to frustrate Him in the earth; and, apart from God, you have neither protector nor helper.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 486,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4304,
            "text": "And of His signs are the ships that run on the sea like landmarks;",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4305,
            "text": "and if He wills, He stills the wind, and they remain motionless on its back. Surely in that are signs for every man enduring, thankful.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4306,
            "text": "Or He wrecks them for what they have earned; and He pardons much;",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4307,
            "text": "and that those who dispute concerning Our signs may know they have no asylum.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4308,
            "text": "Whatever thing you have been given is the enjoyment of the present life; but what is with God is better and more enduring for those who believe and put their trust in their Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4309,
            "text": "And those who avoid the heinous sins and indecencies and when they are angry forgive,",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4310,
            "text": "and those who answer their Lord, and perform the prayer, their affair being counsel between them, and they expend of that We have provided them,",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4311,
            "text": "and who, when insolence visits them, do help themselves --",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4312,
            "text": "and the recompense of evil is evil the like of it; but whoso pardons and puts things right, his wage falls upon God; surely He loves not the evildoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4313,
            "text": "And whosoever helps himself after he has been wronged -- against them there is no way.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4314,
            "text": "The way is only open against those who do wrong to the people, and are insolent in the earth wrongfully; there awaits them a painful chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4315,
            "text": "But surely he who bears patiently and is forgiving -- surely that is true constancy.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4316,
            "text": "Whomsoever God leads astray, he has no protector after him; and thou shalt see the evildoers, when they see the chastisement, saying, 'Is there any way to be sent back?'",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4317,
            "text": "And thou shalt see them, as they are exposed to it, abject in humbleness, looking with furtive glance; and the believers shall say, 'Surely the losers are they who lose themselves and their families on the Day of Resurrection; surely the evildoers are in lasting chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 488,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4318,
            "text": "They have no protectors to help them, apart from God, and whomsoever God leads astray, no way has he.'",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 488,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4319,
            "text": "Answer your Lord, before there comes a day from God that cannot be turned back; upon that day you shall have no shelter, no denial.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 488,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4320,
            "text": "But if they turn away, We sent thee not to be a guardian over them. It is for thee only to deliver the Message. And when We let man taste mercy from Us, he rejoices in it; but if some evil befalls him for that his own hands have forwarded, then surely man is unthankful.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 488,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4321,
            "text": "To God belongs the Kingdom of the heavens and the earth; He creates what He will; He gives to whom He will females, and He gives to whom He will males",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 488,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4322,
            "text": "or He couples them, both males and females; and He makes whom He will barren. Surely He is All-knowing, All-powerful.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 488,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4323,
            "text": "It belongs not to any mortal that God should speak to him, except by revelation, or from behind a veil, or that He should send a messenger and he reveal whatsoever He will, by His leave; surely He is All-high, All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 488,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4324,
            "text": "Even so We have revealed to thee a Spirit of Our bidding. Thou knewest not what the Book was, nor belief; but We made it a light, whereby We guide whom We will of Our servants. And thou, surely thou shalt guide unto a straight path --",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4325,
            "text": "the path of God, to whom belongs whatsoever is in the heavens, and whatsoever is in the earth. Surely unto God all things come home.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 43,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الزُّخۡرُفِ",
        "englishName": "Az-Zukhruf",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Ornaments of gold",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4326,
            "text": "Ha Mim",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4327,
            "text": "By the Clear Book,",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4328,
            "text": "behold, We have made it an Arabic Koran; haply you will understand;",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4329,
            "text": "and behold, it is in the Essence of the Book, with Us; sublime indeed, wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4330,
            "text": "Shall We turn away the Remembrance from you, for that you are a prodigal people?",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4331,
            "text": "How many a Prophet We sent among the ancients,",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4332,
            "text": "but not a Prophet came to them, without they mocked at him;",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4333,
            "text": "so We destroyed men stronger in valour than they, and the example of the ancients passed away.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4334,
            "text": "If thou askest them, 'Who created the heavens and earth?' they will say, 'The All-mighty, the All-knowing created them.'",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4335,
            "text": "He who appointed the earth to be a cradle for you, and appointed ways for you therein, that haply you may be guided;",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4336,
            "text": "and who sent down out of heaven water in measure; and We revived thereby a land that was dead; even so you shall be brought forth;",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4337,
            "text": "and who created the pairs, all of them, and appointed for you ships and cattle such as you ride,",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4338,
            "text": "that you may be seated on their backs and then remember your Lord's blessing when you are seated on them, and say, 'Glory be to Him, who has subjected this to us, and we ourselves were not equal to it;",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4339,
            "text": "surely unto our Lord we are turning.'",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4340,
            "text": "Yet they have assigned to Him a part of His own servants! Man is dearly unthankful.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4341,
            "text": "Or has He taken to Himself, from that He creates, daughters, and favoured you with sons?",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4342,
            "text": "And when any of them is given the good tidings of that he has likened to the All-merciful, his face is darkened, and he chokes inwardly.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4343,
            "text": "What, one who is reared amid ornaments and, when the time of altercation comes, is not to be seen?",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4344,
            "text": "And they have made the angels, who are themselves servants of the All-merciful, females. What, did they witness their creation? Their witness shall be written down, and they shall be questioned.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4345,
            "text": "They say, 'Had the All-merciful so willed, we would not have served them.' They have no knowledge of that; they are only conjecturing.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4346,
            "text": "Or did We bring them a Book aforetime to which they hold?",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4347,
            "text": "Nay, but they say, 'We found our fathers upon a community, and we are guided upon their traces.'",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4348,
            "text": "Even so We sent never before thee any warner into any city, except that its men who lived at ease said, 'We indeed found our fathers upon a community, and we are following upon their traces.'",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4349,
            "text": "Say: 'What, though I should bring you a better guidance than you found your fathers upon?' They say, 'We disbelieve in that you were sent with.'",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4350,
            "text": "So We took vengeance upon them; and behold how was the end of them that cried lies.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4351,
            "text": "And when Abraham said to his father and his people, 'Surely I am quit of that you serve,",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4352,
            "text": "except Him who originated me; and He will guide me.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4353,
            "text": "And he made it a word enduring among his posterity; haply so they would return.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4354,
            "text": "Nay, but I gave these and their fathers enjoyment of days, until the truth came unto them, and a manifest Messenger.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4355,
            "text": "And when the truth came to them, they said, 'This is a sorcery, and in it we are unbelievers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4356,
            "text": "They say, 'Why was this Koran not sent down upon some man of moment in the two cities?'",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4357,
            "text": "What, is it they who divide the mercy of the Lord? We have divided between them their livelihood in the present life, and raised some of them above others in rank, that some of them may take others in servitude; and the mercy of thy Lord is better than that they amass.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4358,
            "text": "And were it not that mankind would be one nation, We would have appointed for those who disbelieve in the All-merciful roofs of silver to their houses, and stairs whereon to mount,",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4359,
            "text": "and doors to their houses, and couches whereon to recline,",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4360,
            "text": "and ornaments; surely all this is but the enjoyment of the present life, and the world to come with thy Lord is for the godfearing.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4361,
            "text": "Whoso blinds himself to the Remembrance of the All-merciful, to him We assign a Satan for comrade;",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4362,
            "text": "and they bar them from the way, and they think they are guided,",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4363,
            "text": "till, when he comes to Us, he says, 'Would there had been between me and thee the distance of the two Easts!' An evil comrade!",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4364,
            "text": "It shall not profit you today, since you did evil, that you are partners in the chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4365,
            "text": "What, shalt thou make the deaf to hear, or shalt thou guide the blind and him who is in manifest error?",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4366,
            "text": "Whether We take thee away, We shall take vengeance upon them,",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4367,
            "text": "or We show thee a part of that We promised them, surely We have power over them.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4368,
            "text": "So hold thou fast unto that which has been revealed unto thee; surely thou art upon a straight path.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4369,
            "text": "Surely it is a Reminder to thee and to thy people; and assuredly you will be questioned.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4370,
            "text": "Ask those of Our Messengers We sent before thee: Have We appointed, apart from the All-merciful, gods to be served?",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4371,
            "text": "We also sent Moses with Our signs to Pharaoh and his Council, and he said, 'Surely, I am the Messenger of the Lord of all Being.'",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4372,
            "text": "But when he brought them Our signs, lo, they laughed at them.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4373,
            "text": "And not a sign We showed them, but it was greater than its sister sign; and We seized them with chastisement, that haply they should return.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4374,
            "text": "And they said, 'Sorcerer, pray to thy Lord for us by the covenant He has made with thee, and surely we shall be right-guided.'",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4375,
            "text": "But when We removed from them the chastisement, behold, they broke their troth.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4376,
            "text": "And Pharaoh proclaimed among his people: 'O my people, do I not possess the kingdom of Egypt, and these rivers flowing beneath me? What, do you not see?",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4377,
            "text": "Or am I better than this man, who is contemptible and scarcely makes things clear?",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4378,
            "text": "Why then have bracelets of gold not been cast on him, or angels not come with him conjoined?'",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4379,
            "text": "So he made his people unsteady, and they obeyed him; surely they were an ungodly people.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4380,
            "text": "So, when they had angered Us, We took vengeance on them, and We drowned them all together;",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4381,
            "text": "and We made them a thing past, and We appointed them for an example to later folk.",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4382,
            "text": "And when the son of Mary is cited as an example, behold, thy people turn away from it",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4383,
            "text": "and say, 'What, are our gods better, or he?' They cite not him to thee, save to dispute;. nay, but they are a people contentious.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4384,
            "text": "He is only a servant We blessed, and We made him to be an example to the Children of Israel.",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4385,
            "text": "Had We willed, We would have appointed angels among you to be successors in the earth.",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4386,
            "text": "It is knowledge of the Hour; doubt not concerning it, and follow me. This is a straight path.",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4387,
            "text": "Let not Satan bar you; he is for you a manifest foe.",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4388,
            "text": "And when Jesus came with the clear signs he said, 'I have come to you with wisdom, and that I may make clear to you some of that whereon you are at variance; so fear you God and obey you me.",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4389,
            "text": "Assuredly God is my Lord and your Lord; therefore serve Him; this is a straight path.'",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4390,
            "text": "But the parties among them fell into variance; so woe unto those who did evil, because of the chastisement of a painful day.",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4391,
            "text": "Are they looking for aught but the Hour, that it shall come upon them suddenly, when they are not aware?",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4392,
            "text": "Friends on that day shall be foes to one another, but the god-fearing.",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4393,
            "text": "'O My servants, today no fear is on you, neither do you sorrow' --",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4394,
            "text": "even those who believed in Our signs, and had surrendered themselves",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4395,
            "text": "'Enter Paradise, you and your wives, walking with joy!'",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4396,
            "text": "There shall be passed around them platters of gold, and cups, therein being whatever the souls desire, and the eyes delight in. 'And therein, you shall dwell forever.",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4397,
            "text": "This is the Paradise that you have been given for an inheritance for the things that you were doing.",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4398,
            "text": "Therein you have abundant fruits, whereof you may eat.'",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4399,
            "text": "But the evildoers dwell forever in the chastisement of Gehenna",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4400,
            "text": "that is not abated for them and therein they are sore confounded.",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4401,
            "text": "We never wronged them, but they themselves did the wrong.",
            "numberInSurah": 76,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4402,
            "text": "And they shall call, 'O",
            "numberInSurah": 77,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4403,
            "text": "'We brought you the truth, but most of you were averse to the truth.'",
            "numberInSurah": 78,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4404,
            "text": "Or have they contrived some matter? We too are contriving.",
            "numberInSurah": 79,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4405,
            "text": "Or do they think We hear not their secret and what they conspire together? Yes indeed, and Our messengers are present with them writing it down.",
            "numberInSurah": 80,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4406,
            "text": "Say: 'If the All-merciful has a son, then I am the first to serve him.",
            "numberInSurah": 81,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4407,
            "text": "Glory be to the Lord of the heavens and the earth, the Lord of the Throne, above that they describe.'",
            "numberInSurah": 82,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4408,
            "text": "Then leave them alone to plunge and play, until they encounter that day of theirs which they are promised.",
            "numberInSurah": 83,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4409,
            "text": "And it is He who in heaven is God and in earth is God; He is the All-wise, the All-knowing.",
            "numberInSurah": 84,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4410,
            "text": "Glory be to Him, to whom belongs the Kingdom of the heavens and the earth and all that between them is; with Him is the knowledge of the Hour, and to Him you shall be returned.",
            "numberInSurah": 85,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4411,
            "text": "Those they call upon, apart from Him, have no power of intercession, save such as have testified to the truth, and that knowingly.",
            "numberInSurah": 86,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4412,
            "text": "If thou askest them, 'Who created you?' they will say, 'God.' How then are they perverted?",
            "numberInSurah": 87,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4413,
            "text": "And for his saying, 'My Lord, surely these are a people who believe not' --",
            "numberInSurah": 88,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4414,
            "text": "yet pardon them, and say, 'Peace!' Soon they will know.",
            "numberInSurah": 89,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 44,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الدُّخَانِ",
        "englishName": "Ad-Dukhaan",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Smoke",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4415,
            "text": "Ha Mim",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4416,
            "text": "By the Clear Book.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4417,
            "text": "We have sent it down in a blessed night (We are ever warning)",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4418,
            "text": "therein every wise bidding",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4419,
            "text": "determined as a bidding from Us, (We are ever sending)",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4420,
            "text": "as a mercy from thy Lord (surely He is the All-hearing, the All-knowing)",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4421,
            "text": "Lord of the heavens and earth, and all that between them is if you have faith.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4422,
            "text": "There is no god but He; He gives life and makes to die; your Lord and the Lord of your fathers, the ancients.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4423,
            "text": "Nay, but they are in doubt, playing.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4424,
            "text": "So be on the watch for a day when heaven shall bring a manifest smoke",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4425,
            "text": "covering the people; this is a painful chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4426,
            "text": "'O our Lord, remove Thou from us the chastisement; we are believers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4427,
            "text": "How should they have the Reminder, seeing a clear Messenger already came to them,",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4428,
            "text": "then they turned away from him and said, 'A man tutored, possessed!'",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4429,
            "text": "'Behold, We are removing the chastisement a little; behold, you revert!'",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4430,
            "text": "Upon the day when We shall assault most mightily, then We shall take Our vengeance.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4431,
            "text": "Already before them We tried the people of Pharaoh, and a noble Messenger came unto them,",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4432,
            "text": "saying, 'Deliver to me God's servants; I am for you a faithful Messenger,",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4433,
            "text": "and, 'Rise not up against God; behold, I come to you with a clear authority,",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4434,
            "text": "and I take refuge in my Lord and your Lord, lest you should stone me.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4435,
            "text": "'But if so be that you believe me not, go you apart from me!'",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4436,
            "text": "And he called to his Lord, saying, 'These are a sinful people.'",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4437,
            "text": "'Then set thou forth with My servants in a watch of the night; surely you will be followed.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4438,
            "text": "And leave the sea becalmed; they are a drowned host.'",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4439,
            "text": "They left how many gardens and fountains,",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4440,
            "text": "sown fields, and how noble a station,",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4441,
            "text": "and what prosperity they had rejoiced in!",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4442,
            "text": "Even so; and We bequeathed them upon another people.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4443,
            "text": "Neither heaven nor earth wept for them, nor were they respited;",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4444,
            "text": "and We delivered the Children of Israel from the humbling chastisement,",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4445,
            "text": "from Pharaoh; surely he was a high One, of the prodigals;",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4446,
            "text": "and We chose them, out of a knowledge, above all beings,",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4447,
            "text": "and gave them signs wherein there was a manifest trial.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4448,
            "text": "These men do say,",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4449,
            "text": "'There is nothing but our first death; we shall not be revived.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4450,
            "text": "Bring us our fathers, if you speak truly!'",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4451,
            "text": "Are they better, or the people of Tubba' and those before them whom We destroyed? They were surely sinners.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4452,
            "text": "We created not the heavens and earth, and all that between them is, in play;",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4453,
            "text": "We created them not save in truth; but most of them know it not.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4454,
            "text": "Surely the Day of Decision shall be their appointed time, all together,",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4455,
            "text": "the day a master shall avail nothing a client, and they shall not be helped,",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4456,
            "text": "save him upon whom God has mercy; He is the All-mighty, the All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4457,
            "text": "Lo, the Tree of Ez-Zakkoum",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4458,
            "text": "is the food of the guilty,",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4459,
            "text": "like molten copper, bubbling in the belly",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4460,
            "text": "as boiling water bubbles.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4461,
            "text": "'Take him, and thrust him into the midst of Hell,",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4462,
            "text": "then pour over his head the chastisement of boiling water!'",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4463,
            "text": "'Taste! Surely thou art the mighty, the noble.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4464,
            "text": "This is that concerning which you were doubting.'",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4465,
            "text": "Surely the godfearing shall be in a station secure",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4466,
            "text": "among gardens and fountains,",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4467,
            "text": "robed in silk and brocade, set face to face.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4468,
            "text": "Even so; and We shall espouse them to wide-eyed houris,",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4469,
            "text": "therein calling for every fruit, secure.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4470,
            "text": "They shall not taste therein of death, save the first death, And He shall guard them against the chastisement of Hell --",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4471,
            "text": "a bounty from thy Lord; that is the mighty triumph.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4472,
            "text": "Now We have made it easy by thy tongue, that haply they may remember.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4473,
            "text": "So be on the watch; they too are on the watch.",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 45,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الجَاثِيَةِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Jaathiya",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Crouching",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4474,
            "text": "Ha Mim",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4475,
            "text": "The sending down of the Book is from God, the All-mighty, the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4476,
            "text": "Surely in the heavens and earth there are signs for the believers;",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4477,
            "text": "and in your creation, and the crawling things He scatters abroad, there are signs for a people having sure faith,",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4478,
            "text": "and in the alternation of night and day, and the provision God sends down from heaven, and therewith revives the earth after it is dead, and the turning about of the winds, there are signs for a people who understand.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4479,
            "text": "Those are the signs of God that We recite to thee in truth; in what manner of discourse then, after God and His signs, will they believe?",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4480,
            "text": "Woe to every guilty impostor",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4481,
            "text": "who hears the signs of God being recited to him, then perseveres in waxing proud, as if he has not heard them; so give him the good tidings of a painful chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4482,
            "text": "And when he knows anything of Our signs, he takes them in mockery; those for them awaits a humbling chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4483,
            "text": "Behind them Gehenna; and that they have earned shall not avail them aught, nor those they took as protectors, apart from God; for them awaits a mighty chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4484,
            "text": "This is guidance; and those who disbelieve in the signs of their Lord, there awaits them a painful chastisement of wrath.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4485,
            "text": "God is He who has subjected to you the sea, that the ships may run on it at His commandment, and that you may seek His bounty; haply so you will be thankful.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4486,
            "text": "And He has subjected to you what is in the heavens and what is in the earth, all together, from Him. Surely in that are signs for a people who reflect.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4487,
            "text": "Say unto those who believe, that they forgive those who do not look for the days of God, that He may recompense a people for that they have been earning.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 500,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4488,
            "text": "Whoso does righteousness, it is to his own gain, and whoso does evil, it is to his own loss; then to your Lord you shall be returned.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 500,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4489,
            "text": "Indeed, We gave the Children of Israel the Book, the Judgment, and the Prophethood, and We provided them with good things, and We preferred them above all beings.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 500,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4490,
            "text": "We gave them clear signs of the Command; so they differed not, except after the knowledge had come to them, being insolent one to another. Surely thy Lord will decide between them on the Day of Resurrection touching their differences.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 500,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4491,
            "text": "Then We set thee upon an open way of the Command; therefore follow it, and follow not the caprices of those who do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 500,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4492,
            "text": "Surely they will not avail thee aught against God. Surely the evildoers are friends one of the other; God is the friend of the godfearing.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 500,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4493,
            "text": "This is clear proofs for men, and a guidance, and a mercy to a people having sure faith.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 500,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4494,
            "text": "Or do those who commit evil deeds think that We shall make them as those who believe and do righteous deeds, equal their living and their dying? How ill they judge!",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 500,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4495,
            "text": "God created the heavens and the earth in truth, and that every soul may be recompensed for what it has earned; they shall not be wronged.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 500,
            "ruku": 436,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4496,
            "text": "Hast thou seen him who has taken his caprice to be his god, and God has led him astray out of a knowledge, and set a seal upon his hearing and his heart, and laid a covering on his eyes? Who shall guide him after God? What, will you not remember?",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 436,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4497,
            "text": "They say, 'There is nothing but our present life; we die, and we live, and nothing but Time destroys us.' Of that they have no knowledge; they merely conjecture.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 436,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4498,
            "text": "And when Our signs are recited to them, clear signs, their only argument is that they say, 'Bring us our fathers, if you speak truly.'",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 436,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4499,
            "text": "Say: 'God gives you life, then makes you die, then He shall gather you to the Day of Resurrection, wherein is no doubt, but most men do not know.'",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 436,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4500,
            "text": "To God belongs the Kingdom of the heavens and the earth. And on the day when the Hour is come, upon that day the vain-doers shall lose.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4501,
            "text": "And thou shalt see every nation hobbling on their knees, every nation being summoned unto its Book: 'Today you shall be recompensed for that you were doing.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4502,
            "text": "This is Our Book, that speaks against you the truth; We have been registering all that you were doing.'",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4503,
            "text": "And as for those who have believed and done deeds of righteousness, their Lord shall admit them into His mercy; that is the manifest triumph.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4504,
            "text": "But as for those who have disbelieved: 'Were not My signs recited to you, and you waxed proud, and were a sinful people?",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4505,
            "text": "And when it was said, 'God's promise is true, and the Hour, there is no doubt of it,' you said; 'We know not what the Hour may be; we have only a surmise, and are by no means certain.'",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4506,
            "text": "And the evil deeds that they have done shall appear to them, and they shall be encompassed by that they mocked at.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4507,
            "text": "And it shall be said, 'Today We do forget you, even as you forgot the encounter of this your day; and your refuge is the Fire, and you shall have no helpers.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4508,
            "text": "That is for that you took God's signs in mockery, and the present life deluded you.' So today they shall not be brought forth from it, nor will they be suffered to make amends.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4509,
            "text": "So to God belongs praise, the Lord of the heavens and the Lord of the earth, Lord of all Being.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4510,
            "text": "His is the Domination an the heavens and the earth; He is the All-mighty, the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 46,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الأَحۡقَافِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Ahqaf",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Dunes",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4511,
            "text": "Ha Mim",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4512,
            "text": "The sending down of the Book is from God, the All-mighty, the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4513,
            "text": "We have not created the heavens and the earth, and what between them is, save with the truth and a stated term; but the unbelievers are turning away from that they were warned of.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4514,
            "text": "Say: 'Have you considered that you call upon apart from God? Show me what they have created of the earth; or have they a partnership in the heavens? Bring me a Book before this, or some remnant of a knowledge, if you speak truly.'",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4515,
            "text": "And who is further astray than he who calls, apart from God, upon such a one as shall not answer him till the Day of Resurrection? Such as are heedless of their calling,",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4516,
            "text": "and when mankind are mustered, shall be enemies to them, and shall deny their service.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 503,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4517,
            "text": "And when Our signs are recited to them, clear signs, the unbelievers say to the truth when it has come to them, 'This is manifest sorcery.'",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 503,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4518,
            "text": "Or do they say, 'He has forged it'? Say: 'If I have forged it, you have no power to help me against God. He knows very well what you are pressing upon; He suffices as a witness between me and you; He is the All-forgiving, the All-compassionate.'",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 503,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4519,
            "text": "Say: 'I am not an innovation among the Messengers, and I know not what shall be done with me or with you. I only follow what is revealed to me; I am only a clear warner.'",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 503,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4520,
            "text": "Say: 'Have you considered? If it be from God, and you disbelieve in it, and a witness from among the Children of Israel hears witness to its like, and believes, and you wax proud, God guides not the people of the evildoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 503,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4521,
            "text": "The unbelievers say, as regards the believers, 'If it had been aught good, they had not outstripped us to it.' And since they are not guided by it, certainly they will say, 'This is an old calumny!'",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 503,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4522,
            "text": "Yet before it was the Book of Moses for a model and a mercy; and this is a Book confirming, in Arabic tongue, to warn the evildoers, and good tidings to the good-doers.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 503,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4523,
            "text": "Surely those who say, 'Our Lord is God' and then go straight, no fear shall be on them, neither shall they sorrow.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 503,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4524,
            "text": "Those are the inhabitants of Paradise, therein dwelling forever, as a recompense for that they have been doing.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 503,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4525,
            "text": "We have charged man, that he be kind to his parents; his mother bore him painfully, and painfully she gave birth to him; his bearing and his weaning are thirty months. Until, when he is fully grown, and reaches forty years, he says, 'O my Lord, dispose me that I may be thankful for Thy blessing wherewith Thou hast blessed me and my father and mother, and that I may do righteousness well-pleasing to Thee; and make me righteous also in my seed. Behold, I repent to Thee, and am among those that surrender.'",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 504,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4526,
            "text": "Those are they from whom We shall accept the best of what they have done, and We shall pass over their evil deeds. They are among the inhabitants of Paradise -- the promise of the very truth, which they were promised.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 504,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4527,
            "text": "But he who says to his father and his mother, 'Fie upon you! Do you promise me that I shall be brought forth, when already generations have passed away before me?' while they call upon God for succour -- 'Woe upon thee! Believe; surely God's promise is true'; then he says, 'This is naught but the fairy-tales of the ancients' --",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 504,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4528,
            "text": "such men are they against whom has been realized the Word concerning nations that passed away before them, men and jinn alike; they were losers.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 504,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4529,
            "text": "All shall have their degrees, according to what they have wrought, and that He may pay them in full for their works, and they not being wronged.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 504,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4530,
            "text": "Upon the day when the unbelievers are exposed to the Fire: 'You dissipated your good things in your present life, and you took your enjoyment in them; therefore today you shall be recompensed with the chastisement of humiliation for that you waxed proud in the earth without right, and for your ungodliness.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 504,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4531,
            "text": "And remember the brother of Ad, when he warned his people beside the sand-dunes -- and already warners had passed away alike before him and behind him -- saying, 'Serve none but God! Truly I fear for you the chastisement of a dreadful day.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 505,
            "ruku": 440,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4532,
            "text": "They said, 'What, hast thou come to pervert us from our gods? Then bring us that thou promisest us, if indeed thou speakest truly.'",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 505,
            "ruku": 440,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4533,
            "text": "He said, 'Knowledge is only with God, and I deliver to you the Message with which I was sent; but I see you are an ignorant people.'",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 505,
            "ruku": 440,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4534,
            "text": "Then, when they saw it as a sudden cloud coming towards their valleys, they said, 'This is a cloud, that shall give us rain!' 'Not so; rather it is that you sought to hasten -- a wind, wherein is a painful chastisement,",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 505,
            "ruku": 440,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4535,
            "text": "destroying everything by the commandment of its Lord.' So in the morning there was naught to be seen but their dwelling-places. Even so do We recompense the people of the sinners.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 505,
            "ruku": 440,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4536,
            "text": "And We had established them in that wherein We have not established you, and We appointed for them hearing, and sight, and hearts; and yet their hearing, their sight and their hearts availed them nothing, since they denied the signs of God, and they were encompassed by that they mocked at.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 505,
            "ruku": 440,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4537,
            "text": "And We destroyed the cities about you, and We turned about the signs, that haply they would return.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 505,
            "ruku": 441,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4538,
            "text": "Then why did those not help them that they had taken to themselves as mediators, gods apart from God? Not so; but they went astray from them, and that was their calumny, and what they had been forging.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 505,
            "ruku": 441,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4539,
            "text": "And when We turned to thee a company of jinn giving ear to the Koran; and when they were in its presence they said, 'Be silent!' Then, when it was finished, they turned back to their people, warning.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 506,
            "ruku": 441,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4540,
            "text": "They said, 'Our people, we have heard a Book that was sent down after Moses, confirming what was before it, guiding to the truth and to a straight path.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 506,
            "ruku": 441,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4541,
            "text": "O our people, answer God's summoner, and believe in Him, and He will forgive you some of your sins, and protect you from a painful chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 506,
            "ruku": 441,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4542,
            "text": "Whosoever answers not God's summoner cannot frustrate God in the earth, and he has no protectors apart from Him; those are in manifest error.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 506,
            "ruku": 441,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4543,
            "text": "What, have they not seen that God who created the heavens and earth, not being wearied by creating them, is able to give life to the dead? Yes indeed; He is powerful over everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 506,
            "ruku": 441,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4544,
            "text": "Upon the day when the unbelievers are exposed to the Fire: 'Is not this the truth?' They shall say, 'Yes, by our Lord!' He shall say, 'Then taste the chastisement of your unbelief!'",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 506,
            "ruku": 441,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4545,
            "text": "So be thou patient, as the Messengers possessed of constancy were also patient. Seek not to hasten it for them -- it shall be as if on the day they see that they are promised, they had not tarried but for an hour of a single day. A Message to be delivered! And shall any be destroyed but the people of the ungodly?",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 506,
            "ruku": 441,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 47,
        "name": "سُورَةُ مُحَمَّدٍ",
        "englishName": "Muhammad",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Muhammad",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4546,
            "text": "Those who disbelieve and bar from God's way, God will send their works astray.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4547,
            "text": "But those who believe and do righteous deeds and believe in what is sent down to Muhammad -- and it is the truth from their Lord -- He will acquit them of their evil deeds, and dispose their minds aright.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4548,
            "text": "That is because those who disbelieve follow falsehood, and those who believe follow the truth from their Lord. Even so God strikes their similitudes for men.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4549,
            "text": "When you meet the unbelievers, smite their necks, then, when you have made wide slaughter among them, tie fast the bonds; then set them free, either by grace or ransom, till the war lays down its loads. So it shall be; and if God had willed, He would have avenged Himself upon them; but that He may try some of you by means of others. And those who are slain in the way of God, He will not send their works astray.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4550,
            "text": "He will guide them, and dispose their minds aright,",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4551,
            "text": "and He will admit them to Paradise, that He has made known to them.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4552,
            "text": "O believers, if you help God, He will help you, and confirm your feet.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4553,
            "text": "But as for the unbelievers, ill chance shall befall them! He will send their works astray.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4554,
            "text": "That is because they have been averse to what God has sent down, so He has made their works to fail.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4555,
            "text": "What, have they not journeyed in the land and beheld how was the end of those before them? God destroyed them; the unbelievers shall have the likes thereof.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4556,
            "text": "That is because God is the Protector of the believers, and that the unbelievers have no protector.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4557,
            "text": "God shall surely admit those who believe and do righteous deeds into gardens underneath which rivers flow. As for the unbelievers, they take their enjoyment and eat as cattle eat; and the Fire shall be their lodging.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 508,
            "ruku": 443,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4558,
            "text": "How many a city that was stronger in might than thy city which has expelled thee have We destroyed! And there was no helper for them.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 508,
            "ruku": 443,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4559,
            "text": "What, is he who is upon a clear sign from his Lord like unto such a one unto whom his evil deeds have been decked out fair, and they have followed their caprices?",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 508,
            "ruku": 443,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4560,
            "text": "This is the similitude of Paradise which the godfearing have been promised: therein are rivers of water unstaling, rivers of milk unchanging in flavour, and rivers of wine -- a delight to the drinkers, rivers, too, of honey purified; and therein for them is every fruit, and forgiveness from their Lord -- Are they as he who dwells forever in the Fire, such as are given to drink boiling water, that tears their bowels asunder?",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 508,
            "ruku": 443,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4561,
            "text": "And some of them there are give ear to thee, till, when they go forth from thee, they say to those who have been given knowledge, 'What said he just now?' Those are they upon whose hearts God has set a seal, and they have followed their caprices.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 508,
            "ruku": 443,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4562,
            "text": "But those who are guided aright, them He increases in guidance, and gives them their godfearing.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 508,
            "ruku": 443,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4563,
            "text": "Are they looking for aught but the Hour, that it shall come upon them suddenly? Already its tokens have come; so, when it has come to them, how shall they have their Reminder?",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 508,
            "ruku": 443,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4564,
            "text": "Know thou therefore that there is no god but God, and ask forgiveness for thy sin, and for the believers, men and women. God knows your going to and fro, and your lodging.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 508,
            "ruku": 443,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4565,
            "text": "Those who believe say, 'Why has a sura not been sent down?' Then, when a clear sura is sent down, and therein fighting is mentioned, thou seest those in whose hearts is sickness looking at thee as one who swoons of death; but better for them would be",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 444,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4566,
            "text": "obedience, and words honourable. Then, when the matter is resolved, if they were true to God, it would be better for them.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 444,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4567,
            "text": "If you turned away, would you then haply work corruption in the land, and break your bonds of kin?",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 444,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4568,
            "text": "Those are they whom God has cursed, and so made them deaf, and blinded their eyes.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 444,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4569,
            "text": "What, do they not ponder the Koran? Or is it that there are locks upon their hearts?",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 444,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4570,
            "text": "Those who have turned back in their traces after the guidance has become clear to them, Satan it was that tempted them, and God respited them.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 444,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4571,
            "text": "That is because they said to those who were averse to what God sent down, 'We will obey you in some of the affair'; and God knows their secrets.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 444,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4572,
            "text": "How shall it be, when the angels take them, beating their faces and their backs?",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 444,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4573,
            "text": "That is because they have followed what angers God, and have been averse to His good pleasure, so He has made their works to fail.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 444,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4574,
            "text": "Or did those in whose hearts is sickness think that God would not bring to light their rancour?",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4575,
            "text": "Did We will, We would show them to thee, then thou wouldst know them by their mark; and thou shalt certainly know them in the twisting of their speech; and God knows your deeds.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 510,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4576,
            "text": "And We shall assuredly try you until We know those of you who struggle and are steadfast, and try your tidings.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 510,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4577,
            "text": "Those who disbelieve and bar from God's way and make a breach with the Messenger after the guidance has become clear to them, they will nothing hurt God, and He will make their works to fail.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 510,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4578,
            "text": "O believers, obey God, and obey the Messenger, and do not make your own works vain.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 510,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4579,
            "text": "Those who disbelieve and bar from God's way and then die disbelieving, them God will not forgive.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 510,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4580,
            "text": "So do not faint and call for peace; you shall be the upper ones, and God is with you, and will not deprive you of your works.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 510,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4581,
            "text": "The present life is naught but a sport and a diversion; and if you believe and are godfearing, He will give you your wages, and will not ask of you your goods.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 510,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4582,
            "text": "If He asks you for them, and presses you, you are niggardly, and He brings to light your rancour.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 510,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4583,
            "text": "Ha, there you are; you are called upon to expend in God's way, and some of you are niggardly. Whoso is niggardly is niggardly only to his own soul. God is the All-sufficient; you are the needy ones. If you turn away, He will substitute another people instead of you, then they will not be your likes.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 510,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 48,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الفَتۡحِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Fath",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Victory",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4584,
            "text": "Surely We have given thee a manifest victory,",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 511,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4585,
            "text": "that God may forgive thee thy former and thy latter sins, and complete His blessing upon thee, and guide thee on a straight path,",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 511,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4586,
            "text": "and that God may help thee with mighty help.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 511,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4587,
            "text": "It is He who sent down the Shechina (tranquillity) into the hearts of the believers, that they might add faith to their faith -- to God belong the hosts of the heavens and the earth; God is All-knowing, All-wise --",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 511,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4588,
            "text": "and that He may admit the believers, men and women alike, into gardens underneath which rivers flow, therein to dwell forever, and acquit them of their evil deeds; that is in God's sight a mighty triumph;",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 511,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4589,
            "text": "and that He may chastise the hypocrites, men and women alike, and the idolaters men and women alike, and those who think evil thoughts of God; against them shall be the evil turn of fortune. God is wroth with them, and has cursed them, and has prepared for them Gehenna -- an evil homecoming!",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 511,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4590,
            "text": "To God belong the hosts of the heavens and the earth; God is All-mighty, All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 511,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4591,
            "text": "Surely We have sent thee as a witness, good tidings to bear, and warning,",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 511,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4592,
            "text": "that you may believe in God and His Messenger and succour Him, and reverence Him, and that you may give Him glory at the dawn and in the evening.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 511,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4593,
            "text": "Those who swear fealty to thee swear fealty in truth to God; God's hand is over their hands. Then whosoever breaks his oath breaks it but to his own hurt; and whoso fulfils his covenant made with God, God will give him a mighty wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 512,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4594,
            "text": "The Bedouins who were left behind will say to thee, 'We were occupied by our possessions and our families; so ask forgiveness for us!' They say with their tongues what is not in their hearts. Say: 'Who can avail you aught against God, if He desires hurt for you, or desires profit for you? Nay, but God is ever aware of the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 512,
            "ruku": 447,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4595,
            "text": "Nay, but you thought that the Messenger and the believers would never return to their families, and that was decked out fair in your hearts, and you thought evil thoughts, and you were a people corrupt.'",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 512,
            "ruku": 447,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4596,
            "text": "Whoso believes not in God and His Messenger, We have prepared for the unbelievers a Blaze.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 512,
            "ruku": 447,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4597,
            "text": "To God belongs the kingdom of the heavens and of the earth; whomsoever He will He forgives, and whomsoever He will He chastises; God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 512,
            "ruku": 447,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4598,
            "text": "The Bedouins who were left behind will say, when you set forth after spoils, to take them, 'Let us follow you,' desiring to change God's words. Say: 'You shall not follow us; so God said before.' Then they will say, 'Nay, but you' are jealous of us.' Nay, but they have not understood except a little.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 512,
            "ruku": 447,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4599,
            "text": "Say to the Bedouins who were left behind: 'You shall be called against a people possessed of great might' to fight them, or they surrender. If you obey, God will give you a goodly wage; but if you turn your backs, as you turned your backs before, He will chastise you with a painful chastisement.'",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 513,
            "ruku": 447,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4600,
            "text": "There is no fault in the blind, and there is no fault in the lame, and there is no fault in the sick. And whosoever obeys God and His Messenger, He will admit him into gardens underneath which rivers flow; but whosoever turns his back, him He will chastise with a painful chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 513,
            "ruku": 447,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4601,
            "text": "God was well pleased with the believers when they were swearing fealty to thee under the tree, and He knew what was in their hearts, so He sent down the Shechina upon them, and rewarded them with a nigh victory",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 513,
            "ruku": 448,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4602,
            "text": "and many spoils to take; and God is ever All-mighty, All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 513,
            "ruku": 448,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4603,
            "text": "God has promised you many spoils to take; these He has hastened to you, and has restrained the hands of men from you, and that it may be a sign to the believers, and to guide you on a straight path,",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 513,
            "ruku": 448,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4604,
            "text": "and other spoils you were not able to take; God had encompassed them already. God is powerful over everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 513,
            "ruku": 448,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4605,
            "text": "If the unbelievers had fought you, they would have turned their backs, and then found neither protector nor helper;",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 513,
            "ruku": 448,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4606,
            "text": "the wont of God, as in the past before, and thou shalt never find any changing the wont of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 513,
            "ruku": 448,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4607,
            "text": "It is He who restrained their hands from you, and your hands from them, in the hollow of Mecca, after that He made you victors over them. God sees the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 514,
            "ruku": 448,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4608,
            "text": "They are the ones who disbelieved, and barred you from the Holy Mosque and the offering, detained so as not to reach its place of sacrifice. If it had not been for certain men believers and certain women believers whom you knew not, lest you should trample them, and there befall you guilt unwittingly on their account (that God may admit into His mercy whom He will), had they been separated clearly, then We would have chastised the unbelievers among them with a painful chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 514,
            "ruku": 448,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4609,
            "text": "When the unbelievers set in their hearts fierceness, the fierceness of pagandom, then God sent down His Shechina upon His Messenger and the believers, and fastened to them the word of godfearing to which they have better right and are worthy of; and God has' knowledge of everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 514,
            "ruku": 448,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4610,
            "text": "God has indeed fulfilled the vision He vouchsafed to His Messenger truly: 'You shall enter the Holy Mosque, if God wills, in security, your heads shaved, your hair cut short, not fearing.' He knew what you knew not, and appointed ere that a nigh victory.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 514,
            "ruku": 449,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4611,
            "text": "It is He who has sent His Messenger with the guidance and the religion of truth, that He may uplift it above every religion. God suffices as a witness.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 514,
            "ruku": 449,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4612,
            "text": "Muhammad is the Messenger of God, and those who are with him are hard against the unbelievers, merciful one to another. Thou seest them bowing, prostrating, seeking bounty from God and good pleasure. Their mark is on their faces, the trace of prostration. That is their likeness in the Torah, and their likeness in the Gospel: as a seed that puts forth its shoot, and strengthens it, and it grows stout and rises straight upon its stalk, pleasing the sowers, that through them He may enrage the unbelievers. God has promised those of them who believe and do deeds of righteousness forgiveness and a mighty wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 515,
            "ruku": 449,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 49,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الحُجُرَاتِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Hujuraat",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Inner Apartments",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4613,
            "text": "O believers, advance not before God and His Messenger; and fear God. God is All-hearing, All-knowing.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 515,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4614,
            "text": "O believers, raise not your voices above the Prophet's voice, and be not loud in your speech to him, as you are loud one to another, lest your works fail while you are not aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 515,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4615,
            "text": "Surely those who lower their voices in the presence of God's Messenger, those are they whose hearts God has tested for godfearing; they shall have forgiveness and a mighty wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 515,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4616,
            "text": "Surely those who call unto thee from behind the apartments, the most of them do not understand.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 515,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4617,
            "text": "And if they had patience, until thou comest out to them, that would be better for them; and God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 516,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4618,
            "text": "O believers, if an ungodly man comes to you with a tiding, make clear, lest you afflict a people unwittingly, and then repent of what you have done.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 516,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4619,
            "text": "And know that the Messenger of God is among you. If he obeyed you in much of the affair, you would suffer; but God has endeared to you belief, decking it fair in your hearts, and He has made detestable to you unbelief and ungodliness and disobedience. Those -- they are the right-minded,",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 516,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4620,
            "text": "by God's favour and blessing; God is All-knowing, All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 516,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4621,
            "text": "If two parties of the believers fight, put things right between them; then, if one of them is insolent against the other, fight the insolent one till it reverts to God's commandment. If it reverts, set things right between them equitably, and be just. Surely God loves the just.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 516,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4622,
            "text": "The believers indeed are brothers; so set things right between your two brothers, and fear God; haply so you will find mercy.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 516,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4623,
            "text": "O believers, let not any people scoff at another people who may be better than they; neither let women scoff at women who may be better than themselves. And find not fault with one another, neither revile one another by nicknames. An evil name is ungodliness after belief. And whoso repents not, those -- they are the evildoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 516,
            "ruku": 451,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4624,
            "text": "O believers, eschew much suspicion; some suspicion is a sin. And do not spy, neither backbite one another; would any of you like to eat the flesh of his brother dead? You would abominate it. And fear you God; assuredly God turns, and He is All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 517,
            "ruku": 451,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4625,
            "text": "O mankind, We have created you male and female, and appointed you races and tribes, that you may know one another. Surely the noblest among you in the sight of God is the most godfearing of you. God is All-knowing, All-aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 517,
            "ruku": 451,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4626,
            "text": "The Bedouins say, 'We believe.' Say: 'You do not believe; rather say, 'We surrender'; for belief has not yet entered your hearts. If you obey God and His Messenger, He will not diminish you anything of your works. God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate.'",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 517,
            "ruku": 451,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4627,
            "text": "The believers are those who believe in God and His Messenger, then have not doubted, and have struggled with their possessions and their selves in the way of God; those -- they are the truthful ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 517,
            "ruku": 451,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4628,
            "text": "Say: 'What, would you teach God what your religion is, and God knows what is in the heavens and what is in the earth? And God has knowledge of everything.'",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 517,
            "ruku": 451,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4629,
            "text": "They count it as a favour to thee that they have surrendered! Say: 'Do not count your surrendering as a favour to me; nay, but rather God confers a favour upon you, in that He has guided you to belief, if it be that you are truthful.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 517,
            "ruku": 451,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4630,
            "text": "God knows the Unseen of the heavens and of the earth; and God sees the things you do.'",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 517,
            "ruku": 451,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 50,
        "name": "سُورَةُ قٓ",
        "englishName": "Qaaf",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The letter Qaaf",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4631,
            "text": "Qaf. By the glorious Koran!",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4632,
            "text": "Nay, but they marvel that a warner has come to them from among them; and the unbelievers say, 'This is a marvellous thing!",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4633,
            "text": "What, when we are dead and become dust? That is a far returning!'",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4634,
            "text": "We know what the earth diminishes of them; with Us is a book recording.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4635,
            "text": "Nay, but they cried lies to the truth when it came to them, and so they are in a case confused.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4636,
            "text": "What, have they not beheld heaven above them, how We have built it, and decked it out fair, and it has no cracks?",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4637,
            "text": "And the earth -- We stretched it forth, and cast on it firm mountains, and We caused to grow therein of every joyous kind",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4638,
            "text": "for an insight and a reminder to every penitent servant.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4639,
            "text": "And We sent down out of heaven water blessed, and caused to grow thereby gardens and grain of harvest",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4640,
            "text": "and tall palm-trees with spathes compact,",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4641,
            "text": "a provision for the servants, and thereby We revived a land that was dead. Even so is the coming forth.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4642,
            "text": "Cried lies before them the people of Noah and the men of Er-Rass, and Thamood,",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4643,
            "text": "and Ad and Pharaoh, the brothers of Lot,",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4644,
            "text": "the men of the Thicket, the people of Tubba'. Every one cried lies to the Messengers, and My threat came true.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4645,
            "text": "What, were We wearied by the first creation? No indeed; but they are in uncertainty as to the new creation.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4646,
            "text": "We indeed created man; and We know what his soul whispers within him, and We are nearer to him than the jugular vein.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4647,
            "text": "When the two angels meet together, sitting one on the right, and one on the left,",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4648,
            "text": "not a word he utters, but by him is an observer ready.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4649,
            "text": "And death's agony comes in truth; that is what thou wast shunning!",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4650,
            "text": "And the Trumpet shall be blown; that is the Day of the Threat.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4651,
            "text": "And every soul shall come, and with it a driver and a witness.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4652,
            "text": "'Thou wast heedless of this; therefore We have now removed from thee thy covering, and so thy sight today is piercing.'",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4653,
            "text": "And his comrade shall say, 'This is what I have, made ready.'",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4654,
            "text": "'Cast, you twain, into Gehenna every froward unbeliever,",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4655,
            "text": "every hinderer of the good, transgressor, disquieter,",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4656,
            "text": "who set up with God another god; therefore, you twain, cast him into the terrible chastisement.'",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4657,
            "text": "And his comrade shall say, 'Our Lord, I made him not insolent, but he was in far error.'",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4658,
            "text": "He shall say, 'Dispute not before Me! For I sent you beforehand -- the threat.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4659,
            "text": "The Word is not changed with Me; I wrong not My servants.'",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4660,
            "text": "Upon the day We shall say unto Gehenna, 'Art thou filled?' And it shall say, 'Are there any more to come?'",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4661,
            "text": "And Paradise shall be brought forward to the godfearing, not afar:",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4662,
            "text": "'This is that you were promised; it is for every mindful penitent.'",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4663,
            "text": "Whosoever fears the All-merciful in the Unseen, and comes with a penitent heart:",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4664,
            "text": "'Enter it in peace! This is the Day of Eternity.'",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4665,
            "text": "Therein they shall have whatever they will; and with Us there is yet more.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4666,
            "text": "How many a generation We destroyed before them that was stronger in valour than they, then they searched about in the land; was there any asylum?",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4667,
            "text": "Surely in that there is a reminder to him who has a heart, or will give ear with a present mind.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4668,
            "text": "We created the heavens and the earth, and what between them is, in six days, and no weariness touched Us.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4669,
            "text": "So be thou patient under what they say, and proclaim thy Lord's praise before the rising of the sun, and before its setting,",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4670,
            "text": "and proclaim thy Lord's praise in the night, and at the ends of the prostrations.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4671,
            "text": "And listen thou for the day when the caller shall call from a near place.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4672,
            "text": "On the day they hear the Cry in truth, that is the day of coming forth.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4673,
            "text": "It is We who give life, and make to die, and to Us is the homecoming.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4674,
            "text": "Upon the day when the earth is split asunder from about them as they hasten forth; that is a mustering easy for Us.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4675,
            "text": "We know very well what they say; thou art not a tyrant over them. Therefore remind by the Koran him who fears My threat.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 51,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الذَّارِيَاتِ",
        "englishName": "Adh-Dhaariyat",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Winnowing Winds",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4676,
            "text": "By the swift scatterers",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4677,
            "text": "and the burden-bearers",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4678,
            "text": "and the smooth runners",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4679,
            "text": "and the partitioners,",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4680,
            "text": "surely that you are promised is true,",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4681,
            "text": "and surely the Doom is about to fall!",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4682,
            "text": "By heaven with all its tracks",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4683,
            "text": "surely you speak at variance,",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4684,
            "text": "and perverted therefrom are some.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4685,
            "text": "Perish the conjecturers",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4686,
            "text": "who are dazed in perplexity",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4687,
            "text": "asking, 'When shall be the Day of Doom?'",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4688,
            "text": "Upon the day when they shall be tried at the Fire:",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4689,
            "text": "'Taste your trial! This is that you were seeking to hasten.'",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4690,
            "text": "Surely the godfearing shall be among gardens and fountains",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4691,
            "text": "taking whatsoever their Lord has given them; they were good-doers before that.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4692,
            "text": "Little of the night would they slumber,",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4693,
            "text": "and in the mornings they would ask for forgiveness;",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4694,
            "text": "and the beggar and the outcast had a share in their wealth.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4695,
            "text": "In the earth are signs for those having sure faith;",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4696,
            "text": "and in your selves; what, do you not see?",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4697,
            "text": "And in heaven is your provision, and that you are promised.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4698,
            "text": "So by the Lord of heaven and earth, it is as surely true as that you have speech.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4699,
            "text": "Hast thou received the story of the honoured guests of Abraham?",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4700,
            "text": "When they entered unto him, saying 'Peace!' he said 'Peace! You are a people unknown to me.'",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4701,
            "text": "Then he turned to his household and brought a fattened calf,",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4702,
            "text": "and he laid it before them saying, 'Will you not eat?'",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4703,
            "text": "Then he conceived a fear of them. They said, 'Be not afraid!' And they gave him good tidings of a cunning boy.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4704,
            "text": "Then came forward his wife, clamouring, and she smote her face, and said, 'An old woman, barren!'",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4705,
            "text": "They said, 'So says thy Lord; He is the All-wise, the All-knowing.'",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4706,
            "text": "Said he, 'And what is your business, envoys?'",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4707,
            "text": "They said, 'We have been sent to a people of sinners,",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4708,
            "text": "to loose upon them stones of clay",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4709,
            "text": "marked with thy Lord for the prodigal.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4710,
            "text": "So We brought forth such believers as were in it,",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4711,
            "text": "but We found not therein except one house of those that have surrendered themselves.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4712,
            "text": "And therein We left a sign to those who fear the painful chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4713,
            "text": "And also in Moses, when We sent him unto Pharaoh, with a clear authority,",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4714,
            "text": "but he turned his back, with his court, saying, 'A sorcerer, or a man possessed!'",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4715,
            "text": "So We seized him and his hosts, and We cast them into the sea, and he blameworthy.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4716,
            "text": "And also in Ad, when We loosed against them the withering wind",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4717,
            "text": "that left nothing it came upon, but made it as stuff decayed.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4718,
            "text": "And also in Thamood, when it was said to them, 'Take your enjoyment for a while!'",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4719,
            "text": "Then they turned in disdain from the commandment of their Lord, and the thunderbolt took them and they themselves beholding",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4720,
            "text": "and they were not able to stand upright, and were not helped.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4721,
            "text": "And the people of Noah before; surely they were an ungodly people.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4722,
            "text": "And heaven -- We built it with might, and We extend it wide.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4723,
            "text": "And the earth -- We spread it forth; O excellent Smoothers!",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4724,
            "text": "And of everything created We two kinds; haply you will remember.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4725,
            "text": "Therefore flee unto God! I am a clear warner from Him to you.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4726,
            "text": "And set not up with God another god; I am a clear warner from Him to you.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4727,
            "text": "Even so not a Messenger came to those before them but they said, 'A sorcerer, or a man possessed!'",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4728,
            "text": "What, have they bequeathed it one to another? Nay, but they are an insolent people.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4729,
            "text": "So turn thou from them; thou wilt not be reproached.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4730,
            "text": "And remind; the Reminder profits the believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4731,
            "text": "I have not created jinn and mankind except to serve Me.",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4732,
            "text": "I desire of them no provision, neither do I desire that they should feed Me.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4733,
            "text": "Surely God is the All-provider, the Possessor of Strength, the Ever-Sure.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4734,
            "text": "The evildoers shall have their portion, like the portion of their fellows; so let them not hasten Me!",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4735,
            "text": "So woe to the unbelievers, for that day of theirs that they are promised.",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 52,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الطُّورِ",
        "englishName": "At-Tur",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Mount",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4736,
            "text": "By the Mount",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4737,
            "text": "and a Book inscribed",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4738,
            "text": "in a parchment unrolled,",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4739,
            "text": "by the House inhabited",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4740,
            "text": "and the roof uplifted",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4741,
            "text": "and the sea swarming,",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4742,
            "text": "surely thy Lord's chastisement is about to fall;",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4743,
            "text": "there is none to avert it.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4744,
            "text": "Upon the day when heaven spins dizzily",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4745,
            "text": "and the mountains are in motion,",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4746,
            "text": "woe that day unto those that cry lies,",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4747,
            "text": "such as play at plunging,",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4748,
            "text": "the day when they shall be pitched into the fire of Gehenna:",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4749,
            "text": "'This is the fire that you cried lies to!",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4750,
            "text": "What, is this magic, or is it you that do not see?",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4751,
            "text": "Roast in it! And bear you patiently, or bear not patiently, equal it is to you; you are only being recompensed for that you were working.'",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4752,
            "text": "Surely the godfearing shall be in gardens and bliss,",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4753,
            "text": "rejoicing in that their Lord has given them; and their Lord shall guard them against the chastisement of Hell.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4754,
            "text": "'Eat and drink, with wholesome appetite, for that you were working.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4755,
            "text": "Reclining upon couches ranged in rows; and We shall espouse them to wide-eyed houris.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4756,
            "text": "And those who believed, and their seed followed them in belief, We shall join their seed with them, and We shall not defraud them of aught of their work; every man shall be pledged for what he earned.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4757,
            "text": "And We shall succour them with fruits and flesh such as they desire",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4758,
            "text": "while they pass therein a cup one to another wherein is no idle talk, no cause of sin,",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4759,
            "text": "and there go round them youths, their own, as if they were hidden pearls.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4760,
            "text": "They advance one upon another, asking each other questions.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4761,
            "text": "They say, 'We were before among our people, ever going in fear,",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4762,
            "text": "and God was gracious to us, and guarded us against the chastisement of the burning wind;",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4763,
            "text": "we were before ever calling upon Him; surely He is the All-benign, the All-compassionate.'",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4764,
            "text": "Therefore remind! by thy Lord's blessing thou art not a soothsayer neither possessed.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4765,
            "text": "Or do they say, 'He is a poet for whom we await Fate's uncertainty'?",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4766,
            "text": "Say: 'Await! I shall be awaiting with you.'",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4767,
            "text": "Or do their intellects bid them do this? Or are they an insolent people?",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4768,
            "text": "Or do they say, 'He has invented it?' Nay, but they do not believe.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4769,
            "text": "Then let them bring a discourse like it, if they speak truly.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4770,
            "text": "Or were they created out of nothing? Or are they the creators?",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4771,
            "text": "Or did they create the heavens and earth? Nay, but they have not sure faith.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4772,
            "text": "Or are thy Lord's treasuries in their keeping? Or are they the registrars?",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4773,
            "text": "Or have they a ladder whereon they listen? Then let any of them that has listened bring a clear authority.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4774,
            "text": "Or has He daughters, and they sons?",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4775,
            "text": "Or askest thou them for a wage, and so they are weighed down with debt?",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4776,
            "text": "Or is the Unseen in their keeping, and so they are writing it down?",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4777,
            "text": "Or desire they to outwit? The unbelievers, they are the outwitted.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4778,
            "text": "Or have they a god, other than God? Glory be to God, above that which they associate!",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4779,
            "text": "Even if they saw lumps falling from heaven, they would say, 'A massed cloud!'",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4780,
            "text": "Then leave them, till they encounter their day wherein they shall be thunderstruck,",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4781,
            "text": "the day when their guile shall avail them naught, and they shall not be helped.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4782,
            "text": "And there surely awaits the evildoers a chastisement beyond even that, but most of them know it not.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4783,
            "text": "And be thou patient under the judgment of thy Lord; surely thou art before Our eyes. And proclaim the praise of thy Lord when thou arisest,",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4784,
            "text": "and proclaim the praise of thy Lord in the night, and at the declining of the stars.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 53,
        "name": "سُورَةُ النَّجۡمِ",
        "englishName": "An-Najm",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Star",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4785,
            "text": "By the Star when it plunges,",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4786,
            "text": "your comrade is not astray, neither errs,",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4787,
            "text": "nor speaks he out of caprice.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4788,
            "text": "This is naught but a revelation revealed,",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4789,
            "text": "taught him by one terrible in power,",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4790,
            "text": "very strong; he stood poised,",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4791,
            "text": "being on the higher horizon,",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4792,
            "text": "then drew near and suspended hung,",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4793,
            "text": "two bows' length away, or nearer,",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4794,
            "text": "then revealed to his servant that he revealed.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4795,
            "text": "His heart lies not of what he saw;",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4796,
            "text": "what, will you dispute with him what he sees?",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4797,
            "text": "Indeed, he saw him another time",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4798,
            "text": "by the Lote-Tree of the Boundary",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4799,
            "text": "nigh which is the Garden of the Refuge,",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4800,
            "text": "when there covered the Lote-Tree that which covered;",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4801,
            "text": "his eye swerved not; nor swept astray.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4802,
            "text": "Indeed, he saw one of the greatest signs of his Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4803,
            "text": "Have you considered El-Lat and El-'Uzza",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4804,
            "text": "and Manat the third, the other?",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4805,
            "text": "What, have you males, and He females?",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4806,
            "text": "That were indeed an unjust division.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4807,
            "text": "They are naught but names yourselves have named, and your fathers; God has sent down no authority touching them. They follow only surmise, and what the souls desire; and yet guidance has come to them from their Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4808,
            "text": "Or shall man have whatever he fancies?",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4809,
            "text": "And to God belongs the First and the Last.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4810,
            "text": "How many an angel there is in the heavens whose intercession avails not anything, save after that God gives leave to whomsoever He wills and is well-pleased.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 461,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4811,
            "text": "Those who do not believe in the world to come name the angels with the names of females.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 461,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4812,
            "text": "They have not any knowledge thereof; they follow only surmise, and surmise avails naught against truth.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 461,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4813,
            "text": "So turn thou from him who turns away from Our Remembrance, and desires only the present life.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 461,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4814,
            "text": "That is their attainment of knowledge. Surely thy Lord knows very well those who have gone astray from His way, and He knows very well those who are guided.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 461,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4815,
            "text": "To God belongs whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth, that He may recompense those who do evil for what they have done, and recompense those who have done good with the reward most fair.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 461,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4816,
            "text": "Those who avoid the heinous sins and indecencies, save lesser offences surely thy Lord is wide in His forgiveness. Very well He knows you, when He produced you from the earth, and when you were yet unborn in your mothers' wombs; therefore hold not yourselves purified; God knows very well him who is godfearing.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 461,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4817,
            "text": "Hast thou considered him who turns his back",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4818,
            "text": "and gives a little, and then grudgingly?",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4819,
            "text": "Does he possess the knowledge of the Unseen, and therefore he sees?",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4820,
            "text": "Or has he not been told of what is in the scrolls of Moses,",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4821,
            "text": "and Abraham, he who paid his debt in full?",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4822,
            "text": "That no soul laden bears the load of another,",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4823,
            "text": "and that a man shall have to his account only as he has laboured,",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4824,
            "text": "and that his labouring shall surely be seen,",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4825,
            "text": "then he shall be recompensed for it with the fullest recompense,",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4826,
            "text": "and that the final end is unto thy Lord,",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4827,
            "text": "and that it is He who makes to laugh, and that makes to weep,",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4828,
            "text": "and that it is He who makes to die, and that makes to live,",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4829,
            "text": "and that He Himself created the two kinds, male and female,",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4830,
            "text": "of a sperm-drop, when it was cast forth,",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4831,
            "text": "and that upon Him rests the second growth,",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4832,
            "text": "and that it is He who gives wealth and riches,",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4833,
            "text": "and that it is He who is the Lord of Sirius,",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4834,
            "text": "and that He destroyed Ad, the ancient,",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4835,
            "text": "and Thamood, and He did not spare them,",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4836,
            "text": "and the people of Noah before -- certainly they did exceeding evil, and were insolent",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4837,
            "text": "and the Subverted City He also overthrew,",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4838,
            "text": "so that there covered it that which covered.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4839,
            "text": "Then which of thy Lord's bounties disputest thou?",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4840,
            "text": "This is a warner, of the warners of old.",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4841,
            "text": "The Imminent is imminent;",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4842,
            "text": "apart from God none can disclose it.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4843,
            "text": "Do you then marvel at this discourse,",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4844,
            "text": "and do you laugh, and do you not weep,",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4845,
            "text": "while you make merry?",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4846,
            "text": "So bow yourselves before God, and serve Him!",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": {
              "id": 13,
              "recommended": false,
              "obligatory": true
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 54,
        "name": "سُورَةُ القَمَرِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Qamar",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Moon",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4847,
            "text": "The Hour has drawn nigh: the moon is split.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4848,
            "text": "Yet if they see a sign they turn away, and they say 'A continuous sorcery!'",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4849,
            "text": "They have cried lies, and followed their caprices; but every matter is settled.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4850,
            "text": "And there have come to them such tidings as contain a deterrent --",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4851,
            "text": "a Wisdom far-reaching; yet warnings do not avail.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4852,
            "text": "So turn thou away from them. Upon the day when the Caller shall call unto a horrible thing,",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4853,
            "text": "abasing their eyes, they shall come forth from the tombs as if they were scattered grasshoppers,",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4854,
            "text": "running with outstretched necks to the Caller. The unbelievers shall say, 'This is a hard day!'",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4855,
            "text": "The people of Noah cried lies before them; they cried lies to Our servant, and said, 'A man possessed!' And he was rejected.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4856,
            "text": "And so he called unto his Lord, saying, 'I am vanquished; do Thou succour me!'",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4857,
            "text": "Then We opened the gates of heaven unto water torrential,",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4858,
            "text": "and made the earth to gush with fountains, and the waters met for a matter decreed.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4859,
            "text": "And We bore him upon a well-planked vessel well-caulked",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4860,
            "text": "running before Our eyes-a recompense for him denied.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4861,
            "text": "And We left it for a sign. Is there any that will remember?",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4862,
            "text": "How then were My chastisement and My warnings?",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4863,
            "text": "Now We have made the Koran easy for Remembrance. Is there any that will remember?",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4864,
            "text": "Ad cried lies. How then were My chastisement and My warnings?",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4865,
            "text": "We loosed against them a wind clamorous in a day of ill fortune continuous,",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4866,
            "text": "plucking up men as if they were stumps of uprooted palm-trees.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4867,
            "text": "How then were My chastisement and My warnings?",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4868,
            "text": "Now We have made the Koran easy for Remembrance. Is there any that will remember?",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4869,
            "text": "Thamood cried lies to the warnings",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4870,
            "text": "and said, 'What, shall we follow a mortal, one out of ourselves? Then indeed we should be in error and insanity!",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4871,
            "text": "Has the Reminder been cast upon him alone among us? Nay, rather he is an impudent liar.'",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4872,
            "text": "'They shall surely know tomorrow who is the impudent liar.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4873,
            "text": "They shall send the She-camel as a trial for them; so watch thou them and keep patience.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4874,
            "text": "And tell them that the water is to be divided between them, each drink for each in turn.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4875,
            "text": "Then they called their comrade, and he took in hand, and hamstrung her.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4876,
            "text": "How then were My chastisement and My warnings?",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4877,
            "text": "We loosed against them one Cry, and they were as the wattles of a pen-builder.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4878,
            "text": "Now We have made the Koran easy for Remembrance. Is there any that will remember?",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4879,
            "text": "The people of Lot cried lies to the warnings.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4880,
            "text": "We loosed against them a squall of pebbles except the folk of Lot; We delivered them at the dawn --",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4881,
            "text": "a blessing from Us; even so We recompense him who is thankful.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4882,
            "text": "He had warned them of Our assault, but they disputed the warnings.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4883,
            "text": "Even his guests they had solicited of him; so We obliterated their eyes, saying, 'Taste now My chastisement and My warnings!'",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4884,
            "text": "In the morning early there came upon them a settled chastisement:",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4885,
            "text": "'Taste now My chastisement and My warnings!'",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4886,
            "text": "Now We have made the Koran easy for Remembrance. Is there any that will remember?",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4887,
            "text": "The warnings came also to Pharaoh's folk.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 465,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4888,
            "text": "They cried lies to Our signs, all of them, so We seized them with the seizing of One mighty, omnipotent.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 465,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4889,
            "text": "What, are your unbelievers better than those? Or have you an immunity in the Scrolls?",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 465,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4890,
            "text": "Or do they say, 'We are a congregation that shall be succoured?'",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 465,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4891,
            "text": "Certainly the host shall be routed, and turn their backs.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 465,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4892,
            "text": "Nay, but the Hour is their tryst, and the Hour is very calamitous and bitter.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 465,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4893,
            "text": "Surely the sinners are in error and insanity!",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 465,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4894,
            "text": "The day when they are dragged on their faces into the Fire: 'Taste now the touch of Sakar!'",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 465,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4895,
            "text": "Surely We have created everything in measure.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 465,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4896,
            "text": "Our commandment is but one word, as the twinkling of an eye.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 531,
            "ruku": 465,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4897,
            "text": "We have destroyed the likes of you; is there any that will remember?",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 531,
            "ruku": 465,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4898,
            "text": "Every thing that they have done is in the Scrolls,",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 531,
            "ruku": 465,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4899,
            "text": "and everything, great and small, is inscribed.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 531,
            "ruku": 465,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4900,
            "text": "Surely the godfearing shall dwell amid gardens and a river",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 531,
            "ruku": 465,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4901,
            "text": "in a sure abode, in the presence of a King Omnipotent.",
