            "number": 5024,
            "text": "and before that they lived at ease,",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5025,
            "text": "and persisted in the Great Sin,",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5026,
            "text": "ever saying, 'What, when we are dead and become dust and bones, shall we indeed be raised up?",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5027,
            "text": "What, and our fathers, the ancients?'",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5028,
            "text": "Say: 'The ancients, and the later folk",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5029,
            "text": "shall be gathered to the appointed time of a known day.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5030,
            "text": "Then you erring ones, you that cried lies,",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5031,
            "text": "you shall eat of a tree called Zakkoum,",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5032,
            "text": "and you shall fill therewith your bellies",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5033,
            "text": "and drink on top of that boiling water",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5034,
            "text": "lapping it down like thirsty camels.'",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5035,
            "text": "This shall be their hospitality on the Day of Doom.",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5036,
            "text": "We created you; therefore why will you not believe?",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5037,
            "text": "Have you considered the seed you spill?",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5038,
            "text": "Do you yourselves create it, or are We the Creators?",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5039,
            "text": "We have decreed among you Death; We shall not be outstripped;",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5040,
            "text": "that We may exchange the likes of you, and make you to grow again in a fashion you know not.",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5041,
            "text": "You have known the first growth; so why will you not remember?",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5042,
            "text": "Have you considered the soil you till?",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5043,
            "text": "Do you yourselves sow it, or are We the Sowers?",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5044,
            "text": "Did We will, We would make it broken orts, and you would remain bitterly jesting --",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5045,
            "text": "'We are debt-loaded;",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5046,
            "text": "nay, we have been robbed!'",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5047,
            "text": "Have you considered the water you drink?",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5048,
            "text": "Did you send it down from the clouds, or did We send it?",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5049,
            "text": "Did We will, We would make it bitter; so why are you not thankful?",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5050,
            "text": "Have you considered the fire you kindle?",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5051,
            "text": "Did you make its timber to grow, or did We make it?",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5052,
            "text": "We Ourselves made it for a reminder, and a boon to the desert-dwellers.",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5053,
            "text": "Then magnify the Name of thy Lord, the All-mighty.",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5054,
            "text": "No! I swear by the fallings of the stars",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5055,
            "text": "(and that is indeed a mighty oath, did you but know it)",
            "numberInSurah": 76,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5056,
            "text": "it is surely a noble Koran",
            "numberInSurah": 77,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5057,
            "text": "in a hidden Book",
            "numberInSurah": 78,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5058,
            "text": "none but the purified shall touch,",
            "numberInSurah": 79,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5059,
            "text": "a sending down from the Lord of all Being.",
            "numberInSurah": 80,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5060,
            "text": "What, do you hold this discourse in disdain,",
            "numberInSurah": 81,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5061,
            "text": "and do you make it your living to cry lies?",
            "numberInSurah": 82,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5062,
            "text": "Why, but when the soul leaps to the throat of the dying",
            "numberInSurah": 83,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5063,
            "text": "and that hour you are watching",
            "numberInSurah": 84,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5064,
            "text": "(And We are nigher him than you, but you do not see Us)",
            "numberInSurah": 85,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5065,
            "text": "why, if you are not at Our disposal,",
            "numberInSurah": 86,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5066,
            "text": "do you not bring back his soul, if you speak truly?",
            "numberInSurah": 87,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5067,
            "text": "Then, if he be of those brought nigh the Throne,",
            "numberInSurah": 88,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5068,
            "text": "there shall be repose and ease, and a Garden of Delight;",
            "numberInSurah": 89,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5069,
            "text": "and if he be a Companion of the Right:",
            "numberInSurah": 90,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5070,
            "text": "'Peace be upon thee, Companion of the Right!'",
            "numberInSurah": 91,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5071,
            "text": "But if he be of them that cried lies, and went astray,",
            "numberInSurah": 92,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5072,
            "text": "there shall be a hospitality of boiling water",
            "numberInSurah": 93,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5073,
            "text": "and the roasting in Hell.",
            "numberInSurah": 94,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5074,
            "text": "Surely this is the truth of certainty.",
            "numberInSurah": 95,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5075,
            "text": "Then magnify the Name of thy Lord, the All-mighty.",
            "numberInSurah": 96,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 57,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الحَدِيدِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Hadid",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Iron",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5076,
            "text": "All that is in the heavens and the earth magnifies God; He is the All-mighty, the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5077,
            "text": "To Him belongs the Kingdom of the heavens and the earth; He gives life, and He makes to die, and He is powerful over everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5078,
            "text": "He is the First and the Last, the Outward and the Inward; He has knowledge of everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5079,
            "text": "It is He that created the heavens and the earth in six days then seated Himself upon the Throne. He knows what penetrates into the earth, and what comes forth from it, -- what comes down from heaven, and what goes up unto it. He is with you wherever you are; and God sees the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5080,
            "text": "To Him belongs the Kingdom of the heavens and the earth; and unto Him all matters are returned.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5081,
            "text": "He makes the night to enter into the day and makes the day to enter into the night. He knows the thoughts within the breasts.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5082,
            "text": "Believe in God and His Messenger, and expend of that unto which He has made you successors. And those of you who believe and expend shall have a mighty wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5083,
            "text": "How is it with you, that you believe not in God seeing that the Messenger is calling you to believe in your Lord, and He has taken compact with you, if you are believers?",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5084,
            "text": "It is He who sends down upon His servant signs, clear signs, that He may bring you forth from the shadows into the light. Surely God is to you All-gentle, All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5085,
            "text": "How is it with you, that you expend not in the way of God, and to God belongs the inheritance of the heavens and the earth? Not equal is he among you who spent, and who fought before the victory; those are mightier in rank than they who spent and fought afterwards; and unto each God has promised the reward most fair; and God is aware of the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5086,
            "text": "Who is he that will lend to God a good loan, and He will multiply it for him, and his shall be a generous wage?",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5087,
            "text": "Upon the day when thou seest the believers, men and women, their light running before them, and on their right hands. 'Good tidings for you today! Gardens underneath which rivers flow, therein to dwell for ever; that is indeed the mighty triumph.'",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5088,
            "text": "Upon the day when the hypocrites, men and women, shall say to those who have believed, 'Wait for us, so that we may borrow your light!' It shall be said, 'Return you back behind, and seek for a light!' And a wall shall be set up between them, having a door in the inward whereof is mercy, and against the outward thereof is chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5089,
            "text": "They shall be calling unto them, 'Were we not with you?' They shall say, 'Yes indeed; but you tempted yourselves, and you awaited, and you were in doubt, and fancies deluded you, until God's commandment came, and the Deluder deluded you concerning God.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5090,
            "text": "Therefore today no ransom shall be taken from you, neither from those who disbelieved. Your refuge is the Fire, that is your master -- an evil homecoming!'",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5091,
            "text": "Is it not time that the hearts of those who believe should be humbled to the Remembrance of God and the Truth which He has sent down, and that they should not be as those to whom the Book was given aforetime, and the term seemed over long to them, so that their hearts have become hard, and many of them are ungodly?",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5092,
            "text": "Know that God revives the earth after it was dead. We have indeed made clear for you the signs, that haply you will understand.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5093,
            "text": "Surely those, the men and the women, who make freewill offerings and have lent to God a good loan, it shall be multiplied for them, and theirs shall be a generous wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5094,
            "text": "And those who believe in God and His Messengers -- they are the just men and the martyrs in their Lord's sight; they have their wage, and their light. But the unbelievers, who have cried lies to Our signs, they are the inhabitants of Hell.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 540,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5095,
            "text": "Know that the present life is but a sport and a diversion, an adornment and a cause for boasting among you, and a rivalry in wealth and children. It is as a rain whose vegetation pleases the unbelievers; then it withers, and thou seest it turning yellow, then it becomes broken orts. And in the world to come there is a terrible chastisement, and forgiveness from God and good pleasure; and the present life is but the joy of delusion.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 540,
            "ruku": 474,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5096,
            "text": "Race to forgiveness from your Lord, and a Garden the breadth whereof is as the breadth of heaven and earth, made ready for those who believe in God and His Messengers. That is the bounty of God; He gives it unto whomsoever He will; and God is of bounty abounding.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 540,
            "ruku": 474,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5097,
            "text": "No affliction befalls in the earth or in yourselves, but it is in a Book, before We create it; that is easy for God;",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 540,
            "ruku": 474,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5098,
            "text": "that you may not grieve for what escapes you, nor rejoice in what has come to you; God loves not any man proud and boastful,",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 540,
            "ruku": 474,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5099,
            "text": "such as are niggardly, and bid men to be niggardly. And whosoever turns away, God is the All-sufficient, the All-laudable.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 540,
            "ruku": 474,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5100,
            "text": "Indeed, We sent Our Messengers with the clear signs, and We sent down with them the Book and the Balance so that men might uphold justice. And We sent down iron, wherein is great might, and many uses for men, and so that God might know who helps Him, and His Messengers, in the Unseen. Surely God is All-strong, All-mighty.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 541,
            "ruku": 474,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5101,
            "text": "And We sent Noah, and Abraham, and We appointed the Prophecy and the Book to be among their seed; and some of them are guided, and many of them are ungodly.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 541,
            "ruku": 475,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5102,
            "text": "Then We sent, following in their footsteps, Our Messengers; and We sent, following, Jesus son of Mary, and gave unto him the Gospel. And We set in the hearts of those who followed him tenderness and mercy. And monasticism they invented -- We did not prescribe it for them -- only seeking the good pleasure of God; but they observed it not as it should be observed. So We gave those of them who believed their wage; and many of them are ungodly.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 541,
            "ruku": 475,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5103,
            "text": "O believers, fear God, and believe in His Messenger, and He will give you a twofold portion of His mercy; and He will appoint for you a light whereby you shall walk, and forgive you; God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate;",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 541,
            "ruku": 475,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5104,
            "text": "that the People of the Book may know that they have no power over anything of God's bounty, and that bounty is in the hand of God; He gives it unto whomsoever He will; and God is of bounty abounding.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 541,
            "ruku": 475,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 58,
        "name": "سُورَةُ المُجَادلَةِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Mujaadila",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Pleading Woman",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5105,
            "text": "God has heard the words of her that disputes with thee concerning her husband, and makes complaint unto God. God hears the two of you conversing together; surely God is All-hearing, All-seeing.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 542,
            "ruku": 476,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5106,
            "text": "Those of you who say, regarding their wives, 'Be as my mother's back,' they are not truly their mothers; their mothers are only those who gave them birth, and they are surely saying a dishonourable saying, and a falsehood. Yet surely God is All-pardoning, All-forgiving.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 542,
            "ruku": 476,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5107,
            "text": "And those who say, regarding their wives, 'Be as my mother's back,' and then retract what they have said, they shall set free a slave, before the two of them touch one another. By that you are admonished; and God is aware of the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 542,
            "ruku": 476,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5108,
            "text": "But whosoever finds not the means, then let him fast two successive months, before the two of them touch one another. And if any man is not able to, then let him feed sixty poor persons -- that, that you may believe in God and His Messenger. Those are God's bounds; and for the unbelievers there awaits yet a painful chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 542,
            "ruku": 476,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5109,
            "text": "Surely those who oppose God and His Messenger shall be frustrated as those before them were frustrated. Now We have sent down signs, clear signs; and for the unbelievers awaits a humbling chastisement,",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 542,
            "ruku": 476,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5110,
            "text": "upon the day when God shall raise them up all together, then He shall tell them what they did.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 542,
            "ruku": 476,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5111,
            "text": "God has numbered it, and they have forgotten it. God is witness over everything. Hast thou not seen that God knows whatsoever is in the heavens, and whatsoever is in the earth? Three men conspire not secretly together, but He is the fourth of them, neither five men, but He is the sixth of them, neither fewer than that, neither more, but He is with them, wherever they may be; then He shall tell them what they have done, on the Day of Resurrection. Surely God has knowledge of everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 543,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5112,
            "text": "Hast thou not regarded those who were forbidden to converse secretly together, then they return to that they were forbidden, and they converse secretly together in sin and enmity, and in disobedience to the Messenger? Then, when they come to thee, they greet thee with a greeting God never greeted thee withal; and they say within themselves, 'Why does God not chastise us for what we say?' Sufficient for them shall be Gehenna, at which they, shall be roasted -- an evil homecoming!",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 543,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5113,
            "text": "O believers, when you conspire secretly, then conspire not together in sin and enmity and disobedience to the Messenger, but conspire in piety and godfearing. Fear God, unto whom you shall be mustered.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 543,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5114,
            "text": "Conspiring secretly together is of Satan, that the believers may sorrow; but he will not hurt them anything, except by the leave of God. And in God let the believers put all their trust.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 543,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5115,
            "text": "O believers, when it is said to you 'Make room in the assemblies', then make room, and God will make room for you; and when it is said, 'Move up', move up, and God will raise up in rank those of you who believe and have been given knowledge. And God is aware of the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 543,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5116,
            "text": "O believers, when you conspire with the Messenger, before your conspiring advance a freewill offering; that is better for you and purer. Yet if you find not means, God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5117,
            "text": "Are you afraid, before your conspiring, to advance freewill offerings? If you do not so, and God turns again unto you, then perform the prayer, and pay the alms, and obey God and His Messenger. God is aware of the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5118,
            "text": "Hast thou not regarded those who have taken for friends a people against whom God is wrathful? They belong neither to you nor to them; and they swear upon falsehood, and that wittingly.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5119,
            "text": "God has made ready for them a chastisement terrible; surely they -- evil are the things they have been doing.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5120,
            "text": "They have taken their oaths as a covering, and barred from God's way; so there awaits them a humbling chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5121,
            "text": "Neither their riches nor their children shall avail them anything against God; those -- they are the inhabitants of the Fire, therein dwelling forever.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5122,
            "text": "Upon the day when God shall raise them up all together, and they will swear to Him, as they swear to you, and think they are on something. Surely, they are the liars!",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5123,
            "text": "Satan has gained the mastery over them, and caused them to forget God's Remembrance. Those are Satan's party; why, Satan's party, surely, they are the losers!",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5124,
            "text": "Surely those who oppose God and His Messenger, those are among the most abject.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5125,
            "text": "God has written, 'I shall assuredly be the victor, I and My Messengers.' Surely God is All-strong, All-mighty.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5126,
            "text": "Thou shalt not find any people who believe in God and the Last Day who are loving to anyone who opposes. God and His Messenger, not though they were their fathers, or their sons, or their brothers, or their clan. Those -- He has written faith upon their hearts, and He has confirmed them with a Spirit from Himself; and He shall admit them into gardens underneath which rivers flow, therein to dwell forever, God being well-pleased with them, and they well-pleased with Him. Those are God's party; why, surely God's party -- they are the prosperers.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 545,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 59,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الحَشۡرِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Hashr",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Exile",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5127,
            "text": "All that is in the heavens and the earth magnifies God; He is the All-mighty, the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 545,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5128,
            "text": "It is He who expelled from their habitations the unbelievers among the People of the Book at the first mustering. You did not think that they would go forth, and they thought that their fortresses would defend them against God; then God came upon them from whence they had not reckoned, and He cast terror into their hearts as they destroyed their houses with their own hands, and the hands of the believers; therefore take heed, you who have eyes!",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 545,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5129,
            "text": "Had God not prescribed dispersal for them, He would have chastised them in this world; and there awaits them in the world to come the chastisement of the Fire.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 545,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5130,
            "text": "That is because they made a breach with God and His Messenger; and whosoever makes a breach with God, God is terrible in retribution.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 546,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5131,
            "text": "Whatever palm-trees you cut down, or left standing upon their roots, that was by God's leave, and that He might degrade the ungodly.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 546,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5132,
            "text": "And whatever spoils of war God has given unto His Messenger from them, against that you pricked neither horse nor camel; but God gives authority to His Messengers over whomsoever He will. God is powerful over everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 546,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5133,
            "text": "Whatsoever spoils of war God has given to His Messenger from the people of the cities belongs to God, and His Messenger, and the near kinsman, orphans, the needy and the traveller, so that it be not a thing taken in turns among the rich of you. Whatever the Messenger gives you, take; whatever he forbids you, give over. And fear God; surely God is terrible in retribution.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 546,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5134,
            "text": "It is for the poor emigrants, who were expelled from their habitations and their possessions, seeking bounty from God and good pleasure, and helping God and His Messenger; those -- they are the truthful ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 546,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5135,
            "text": "And those who made their dwelling in the abode, and in belief, before them; love whosoever has emigrated to them, not finding in their breasts any need for what they have been given, and preferring others above themselves, even though poverty be their portion. And whoso is guarded against the avarice of his own soul, those -- they are the prosperers.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 546,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5136,
            "text": "And as for those who came after them, they say, 'Our Lord, forgive us and our brothers, who preceded us in belief, and put Thou not into our hearts any rancour towards those who believe. Our Lord, surely Thou art the All-gentle, the All-compassionate.'",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5137,
            "text": "Hast thou not regarded the hypocrites, saying to their brothers of the People of the Book who disbelieve, 'If you are expelled, we will go forth with you, and we will never obey anyone in regard to you. If you are fought against, we will help you.' And God bears witness that they are truly liars.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5138,
            "text": "If those are expelled, they will not go forth with them, and if they are fought against, they will not help them. Even if they helped them, they would surely turn their backs, then they would not be helped.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5139,
            "text": "Why, you arouse greater fear in their hearts than God; that is because they are a people who understand not.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5140,
            "text": "They will not fight against you all together except in fortified cities, or from behind walls. Their valour is great, among themselves; you think of them as a host; but their hearts are scattered; that is because they are a people who have no sense.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5141,
            "text": "Like those who a short time before them tasted the mischief of their action; there awaits them a painful chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5142,
            "text": "Like Satan, when he said to man, 'Disbelieve'; then, when he disbelieved, he said, 'Surely I am quit of you. Surely I fear God, the Lord of all Being.'",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5143,
            "text": "Their end is, both are in the Fire, there dwelling forever; that is the recompense of the evildoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5144,
            "text": "O believers, fear God. Let every soul consider what it has forwarded for the morrow. And fear God; God is aware of the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5145,
            "text": "Be not as those who forgot God, and so He caused them to forget their souls; those -- they are the ungodly.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5146,
            "text": "Not equal are the inhabitants of the Fire and the inhabitants of Paradise. The inhabitants of Paradise -- they are the triumphant.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5147,
            "text": "If We had sent down this Koran upon a mountain, thou wouldst have seen it humbled, split asunder out of the fear of God. And those similitudes -- We strike them for men; haply they will reflect.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5148,
            "text": "He is God; there is no god but He. He is the knower of the Unseen and the Visible; He is the All-merciful, the All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5149,
            "text": "He is God; there is no god but He. He is the King, the All-holy, the All-peaceable, the All-faithful, the All-preserver, the All-mighty, the All-compeller, the All-sublime. Glory be to God, above that they associate!",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5150,
            "text": "He is God, the Creator, the Maker, the Shaper. To Him belong the Names Most Beautiful. All that is in the heavens and the earth magnifies Him; He is the All-mighty, the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 60,
        "name": "سُورَةُ المُمۡتَحنَةِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Mumtahana",
        "englishNameTranslation": "She that is to be examined",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5151,
            "text": "O believers, take not My enemy and your enemy for friends, offering them love, though they have disbelieved in the truth that has come to you, expelling the Messenger and you because you believe in God your Lord. If you go forth to struggle in My way and seek My good pleasure, secretly loving them, yet I know very well what you conceal and what you publish; and whosoever of you does that, has gone astray from the right way.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 549,
            "ruku": 482,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5152,
            "text": "If they come on you, they will be enemies to you, and stretch against you their hands and their tongues, to do you evil, and they wish that you may disbelieve.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 549,
            "ruku": 482,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5153,
            "text": "Neither your blood-kindred nor your children shall profit you upon the Day of Resurrection; He shall distinguish between you. And God sees the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 549,
            "ruku": 482,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5154,
            "text": "You have had a good example in Abraham, and those with him, when they said to their people, 'We are quit of you and that you serve, apart from God. We disbelieve in you, and between us and you enmity has shown itself, and hatred for ever, until you believe in God alone. (Except that Abraham said unto his father, 'Certainly I shall ask pardon for thee; but I have no power to do aught for thee against God.') 'Our Lord, in Thee we trust; to Thee we turn; to Thee is the homecoming.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 549,
            "ruku": 482,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5155,
            "text": "Our Lord, make us not a temptation to those who disbelieve; and forgive us. Our. Lord, Thou art the All-mighty, the All-wise.'",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 549,
            "ruku": 482,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5156,
            "text": "You have had a good example in them for whoever hopes for God and the Last Day. And whosoever turns away, surely God is the All-sufficient, the All-laudable.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 550,
            "ruku": 482,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5157,
            "text": "It may be God will yet establish between you and those of them with whom you are at enmity love. God is All-powerful; God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 550,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5158,
            "text": "God forbids you not, as regards those who have not fought you in religion's cause, nor expelled you from your habitations, that you should be kindly to them, and act justly towards them; surely God loves the just.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 550,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5159,
            "text": "God only forbids you as to those who have fought you in religion's cause, and expelled you from your habitations, and have supported in your expulsion, that you should take them for friends. And whosoever takes them for friends, those -- they are the evildoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 550,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5160,
            "text": "O believers, when believing women come to you as emigrants, test them. God knows very well their belief. Then, if you know them to be believers, return them not to the unbelievers. They are not permitted to the unbelievers, nor are the unbelievers permitted to them. Give the unbelievers what they have expended; and there is no fault in you to marry them when you have given them their wages. Do not hold fast to the ties of unbelieving women, and ask what you have expended, and let them ask what they have expended. That is God's judgment; He judges between you; and God is All-knowing, All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 550,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5161,
            "text": "And if any of your wives slips away from you to the unbelievers, and then you retaliate, give those whose wives have gone away the like of what they have expended. And fear God, in whom you believe.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 550,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5162,
            "text": "O Prophet, when believing women come to thee, swearing fealty to thee upon the terms that they will not associate with God anything, and will not steal, neither commit adultery, nor slay their children, nor bring a calumny they forge between their hands and their feet, nor disobey thee in aught honourable, ask God's forgiveness for them; God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5163,
            "text": "O believers, take not for friends a people against whom God is wrathful, and who have despaired of the world to come, even as the unbelievers have despaired of the inhabitants of the tombs.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 61,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الصَّفِّ",
        "englishName": "As-Saff",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Ranks",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5164,
            "text": "All that is in the heavens and the earth magnifies God; He is the All-mighty; the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5165,
            "text": "O you who believe, wherefore do you say what you do not?",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5166,
            "text": "Very hateful is it to God, that you say what you do not.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5167,
            "text": "God loves those who fight in His way in ranks, as though they were a building well-compacted.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5168,
            "text": "And when Moses said to his people, 'O my people, why do you hurt me, though you know I am the Messenger of God to you?' When they swerved, God caused their hearts to swerve; and God. guides never the people of the ungodly.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5169,
            "text": "And when Jesus son of Mary said, 'Children of Israel, I am indeed the Messenger of God to you, confirming the Torah that is before me, and giving good tidings of a Messenger who shall come after me, whose name shall be Ahmad.' Then, when he brought them the clear signs, they said, 'This is a manifest sorcery.'",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5170,
            "text": "And who does greater evil than he who forges against God falsehood, when he is being called unto surrender? And God guides never the people of the evildoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5171,
            "text": "They desire to extinguish with their mouths, the light of God; but God will perfect His light, though the unbelievers be averse.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5172,
            "text": "It is He who has sent His Messenger with the guidance and the religion of truth, that he may uplift it above every religion, though the unbelievers be averse.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5173,
            "text": "O believers, shall I direct you to a commerce that shall deliver you from a painful chastisement?",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 485,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5174,
            "text": "You shall believe in God and His Messenger, and struggle in the way of God with your possessions and your selves. That is better for you, did you but know.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 485,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5175,
            "text": "He will forgive you your sins and admit you into gardens underneath which rivers flow, and to dwelling-places goodly in Gardens of Eden; that is the mighty triumph;",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 485,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5176,
            "text": "and other things you love, help from God and a nigh victory. Give thou good tidings to the believers!",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 485,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5177,
            "text": "O believers, be you God's helpers, as Jesus, Mary's son, said to the Apostles. 'Who will be my helpers unto God?' The Apostles said, 'We will be helpers of God.' And a party of the Children of Israel believed, and a party disbelieved. So We confirmed those who believed against their enemy, and they became masters.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 485,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 62,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الجُمُعَةِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Jumu'a",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Friday",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5178,
            "text": "All that is in the heavens and the earth magnifies God, the King, the All-holy, the All-mighty, the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5179,
            "text": "It is He who has raised up from among the common people a Messenger from among them, to recite His signs to them and to purify them, and to teach them the Book and the Wisdom, though before that they were in manifest error,",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5180,
            "text": "and others of them who have not yet joined them. And He is the All-mighty, the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5181,
            "text": "That is the bounty of God; He gives it to whom He will, and God is of bounty abounding.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5182,
            "text": "The likeness of those who have been loaded with the Torah then they have not carried it, is as the likeness of an ass carrying books. Evil is the likeness of the people who have cried lies to God's signs. God guides never the people of the evildoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5183,
            "text": "Say: 'You of Jewry, if you assert that you are the friends of God, apart from other men, then do you long for death, if you speak truly.'",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5184,
            "text": "But they will never long for it, because of that their hands have forwarded; God knows the evildoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5185,
            "text": "Say: 'Surely death, from which you flee, shall encounter you; then you shall be returned to the Knower of the Unseen and the Visible, and He will tell you that you have been doing.'",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5186,
            "text": "O believers, when proclamation is made for prayer on the Day of Congregation, hasten to God's remembrance and leave trafficking aside; that is better for you, did you but know.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 487,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5187,
            "text": "Then, when the prayer is finished, scatter in the land and seek God's bounty, and remember God frequently; haply you will prosper.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 487,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5188,
            "text": "But when they see merchandise or diversion they scatter off to it, and they leave thee standing. Say: 'What is with God is better than diversion and merchandise. God is the best of providers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 487,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 63,
        "name": "سُورَةُ المُنَافِقُونَ",
        "englishName": "Al-Munaafiqoon",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Hypocrites",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5189,
            "text": "When the hypocrites come to thee they say, 'We bear witness that thou art indeed the Messenger of God.' And God knows that thou art indeed His Messenger, and God bears witness that the hypocrites are truly liars.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5190,
            "text": "They have taken their oaths as a covering, then they have barred from the way of God. Surely they -- evil are the things they have been doing.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5191,
            "text": "That is because they have believed, then they have disbelieved; therefore a seal has been set on their hearts, and they do not understand.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5192,
            "text": "When thou seest them, their bodies please thee; but when they speak, thou listenest to their speech, and it is as they were propped-up timbers. They think every cry is against them. They are the enemy; so beware of them. God assail them! How they are perverted!",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5193,
            "text": "And when it is said to them, 'Come now, and God's Messenger will ask forgiveness for you,' they twist their heads, and thou seest them turning their faces away, waxing proud.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5194,
            "text": "Equal it is for them, whether thou askest forgiveness for them or thou askest not forgiveness for them; God will never forgive them. God guides not the people of the ungodly.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5195,
            "text": "Those are they that say, 'Do not expend on them that are with God's Messenger until they scatter off'; yet unto God belong the treasuries of the heavens and of the earth, but the hypocrites do not understand.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5196,
            "text": "They say, 'If we return to the City, the mightier ones of it will expel the more abased'; yet glory belongs unto God, and unto His Messenger and the believers, but the hypocrites do not know it.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5197,
            "text": "O believers, let not your possessions neither your children divert you from God's remembrance; whoso does that, they are the losers.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 489,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5198,
            "text": "Expend of what We have provided you before that death comes upon one of you and he says, 'O my Lord, if only Thou wouldst defer me unto a near term, so that I may make freewill offering, and so I may become one of the righteous.'",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 489,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5199,
            "text": "But God will never defer any soul when its term comes. And God is aware of the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 489,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 64,
        "name": "سُورَةُ التَّغَابُنِ",
        "englishName": "At-Taghaabun",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Mutual Disillusion",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5200,
            "text": "All that is in the heavens and the earth magnifies God. His is the Kingdom, and His is the praise, and He is powerful over everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5201,
            "text": "It is He who created you. One of you is an unbeliever, and one of you a believer; and God sees the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5202,
            "text": "He created the heavens and the earth with the truth, and He shaped you, and shaped you well; and unto Him is the homecoming.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5203,
            "text": "He knows whatever is in the heavens and the earth, and He knows what you conceal and what you publish. God knows the thoughts within the breasts.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5204,
            "text": "Has there not come to you the tidings of those that disbelieved before, then tasted the mischief of their action, and there yet awaits them a painful chastisement?",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5205,
            "text": "That is because their Messengers came to them with the clear signs, and then they said, 'What, shall mortals be our guides?' Therefore they disbelieved, and turned away; and God was in no need of them. And God is All-sufficient, All-laudable.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5206,
            "text": "The unbelievers assert that they will never be raised up. Say: 'Yes indeed, by my Lord! You shall be raised up, then you shall be told the things you did. That is easy for God.'",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5207,
            "text": "Therefore believe in God and His Messenger, and in the Light which We have sent down. And God is aware of the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5208,
            "text": "Upon the day when He shall gather you for the Day of Gathering; that shall be the Day of Mutual Fraud. And whosoever believes in God, and does righteousness, God will acquit him of his evil deeds, and admit him into gardens underneath which rivers flow, therein to dwell for ever and ever; that is the mighty triumph.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5209,
            "text": "And those who disbelieved and cried lies to Our signs, those shall be the inhabitants of the Fire. therein to dwell forever -- an evil homecoming!",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5210,
            "text": "No affliction befalls, except it be by the leave of God. Whosoever believes in God, He will guide his heart. And God has knowledge of everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5211,
            "text": "And obey God, and obey the Messenger; but if you turn your backs, it is only for the Messenger to deliver the Manifest Message.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5212,
            "text": "God -- there is no god but He. And in God let the believers put their trust.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5213,
            "text": "O believers, among your wives and children there is an enemy to you; so beware of them. But if you pardon, and overlook, and if you forgive, surely God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5214,
            "text": "Your wealth and your children are only a trial; and with God is a mighty wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5215,
            "text": "So fear God as far as you are able, and give ear, and obey, and expend well for yourselves. And whosoever is guarded against the avarice of his own soul, those -- they are the prosperers.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5216,
            "text": "If you lend to God a good loan, He will multiply it for you, and will forgive you. God is All-thankful, All-clement,",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5217,
            "text": "Knower He of the Unseen and the Visible, the All-mighty, the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 65,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الطَّلَاقِ",
        "englishName": "At-Talaaq",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Divorce",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5218,
            "text": "O Prophet, when you divorce women, divorce them when they have reached their period. Count the period, and fear God your Lord. Do not expel them from their houses, nor let them go forth, except when they commit a flagrant indecency. Those are God's bounds; whosoever trespasses the bounds of God has done wrong to himself. Thou knowest not, perchance after that God will bring something new to pass.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 558,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5219,
            "text": "Then, when they have reached their term, retain them honourably, or part from them honourably. And call in to witness two men of equity from among yourselves; and perform the witnessing to God Himself. By this then is admonished whosoever believes in God and the Last Day. And whosoever fears God, He will appoint for him a way out,",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 558,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5220,
            "text": "and He will provide for him from whence he never reckoned. And whosoever puts his trust in God, He shall suffice him. God attains his purpose. God has appointed a measure for everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 558,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5221,
            "text": "As for your women who have despaired of further menstruating, if you are in doubt, their period shall be three months; and those who have not menstruated as yet. And those who are with child, their term is when they bring forth their burden. Whoso fears God, God will appoint for him, of His command, easiness.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 558,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5222,
            "text": "That is God's command, that He has sent down unto you. And whosoever fears God, He will acquit him of his evil deeds, and He will give him a mighty wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 558,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5223,
            "text": "Lodge them where you are lodging, according to your means, and do not press them, so as to straiten their circumstances. If they are with child, expend upon them until they bring forth their burden. If they suckle for you, give them their wages, and consult together honourably. If you both make difficulties, another woman shall suckle for him.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5224,
            "text": "Let the man of plenty expend out of his plenty. As for him whose provision is stinted to him, let him expend of what God has given him. God charges no soul save with what He has given him. God will assuredly appoint, after difficulty, easiness.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5225,
            "text": "How many a city turned in disdain from the commandment of its Lord and His Messengers; and then We made with it a terrible reckoning and chastised it with a horrible chastisement.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 493,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5226,
            "text": "So it tasted the mischief of its action, and the end of its affair was loss.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 493,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5227,
            "text": "God prepared for them a terrible chastisement. So fear God, O men possessed of minds! Believers, God has sent down to you, for a remembrance,",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 493,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5228,
            "text": "a Messenger reciting to you the signs of God, clear signs, that He may bring forth those who believe and do righteous deeds from the shadows into the light. Whosoever believes in God, and does righteousness, He will admit him to gardens underneath which rivers flow; therein they shall dwell for ever and ever. God has made for him a goodly provision.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 493,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5229,
            "text": "It is God who created seven heavens, and of earth their like, between them the Command descending, that you may know that God is powerful over everything and that God encompasses everything in knowledge.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 493,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 66,
        "name": "سُورَةُ التَّحۡرِيمِ",
        "englishName": "At-Tahrim",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Prohibition",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5230,
            "text": "O Prophet, why forbiddest thou what God has made lawful to thee, seeking the good pleasure of thy wives? And God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5231,
            "text": "God has ordained for you the absolution of your oaths. God is your Protector, and He is the All-knowing, the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5232,
            "text": "And when the Prophet confided to one of his wives a certain matter; and then, when she told of it, and God disclosed that to him, he made known part of it, and turned aside from part; then, when he told her of it, she said, 'Who told thee this?' He said, 'I was told of it by the All-knowing, the All-aware.'",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5233,
            "text": "If you two repent to God, yet your hearts certainly inclined; but if you support one another against him, God is his Protector, and Gabriel, and the righteous among the believers; and, after that, the angels are his supporters.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5234,
            "text": "It is possible that, if he divorces you, his Lord will give him in exchange wives better than you, women who have surrendered, believing, obedient, penitent, devout, given to fasting, who have been married and virgins too.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5235,
            "text": "Believers, guard yourselves and your families against a Fire whose fuel is men and stones, and over which are harsh, terrible angels who disobey not God in what He commands them and do what they are commanded.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5236,
            "text": "'O you unbelievers, do not excuse yourselves today; you are only being recompensed for what you were doing.'",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5237,
            "text": "Believers, turn to God in sincere repentance; it may be that your Lord will acquit you of your evil deeds, and will admit you into gardens underneath which rivers flow. Upon the day when God will not degrade the Prophet and those who believe with him, their light running before them, and on their right hands; and they say, 'Our 'Lord, perfect for us our light, and forgive us; surely Thou art powerful over everything.'",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 561,
            "ruku": 495,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5238,
            "text": "O Prophet, struggle with the unbelievers and the hypocrites, and be thou harsh with them; their refuge shall be Gehenna -- an evil homecoming!",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 561,
            "ruku": 495,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5239,
            "text": "God has struck a similitude for the unbelievers -- the wife of Noah, and the wife of Lot; for they were under two of Our righteous servants, but they betrayed them, so they availed them nothing whatsoever against God; so it was said, 'Enter, you two, the Fire with those who enter.'",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 561,
            "ruku": 495,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5240,
            "text": "God has struck a similitude for the believers -- the wife of Pharaoh, when she said, 'My Lord, build for me a house in Paradise, in Thy presence, and deliver me from Pharaoh and his work, and do Thou deliver me from the people of the evildoers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 561,
            "ruku": 495,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5241,
            "text": "And Mary, Imran's daughter, who guarded her virginity, so We breathed into her of Our Spirit, and she confirmed the Words of her Lord and His Books, and became one of the obedient.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 561,
            "ruku": 495,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 67,
        "name": "سُورَةُ المُلۡكِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Mulk",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Sovereignty",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5242,
            "text": "Blessed be He in whose hand is the Kingdom -- He is powerful over everything --",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5243,
            "text": "who created death and life, that He might try you which of you is fairest in works; and He is the All-mighty, the All-forgiving --",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5244,
            "text": "who created seven heavens one upon another. Thou seest not in the creation of the All-merciful any imperfection. Return thy gaze; seest thou any fissure?",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5245,
            "text": "Then return thy gaze again, and again, and thy gaze comes back to thee dazzled, aweary.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5246,
            "text": "And We adorned the lower heaven with lamps, and made them things to stone Satans; and We have prepared for them the chastisement of the Blaze.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5247,
            "text": "And for those who disbelieve in their Lord there awaits the chastisement of Gehenna -- an evil homecoming!",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5248,
            "text": "When they are cast into it they will hear it sighing, the while it boils",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5249,
            "text": "and wellnigh bursts asunder with rage. As often as a troop is cast into it, its keepers ask them, 'Came there no warner to you?';",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5250,
            "text": "They say, 'Yes indeed, a warner came to us; but we cried lies, saying, 'God has not sent down anything; you are only in great error.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5251,
            "text": "They also say, 'If we had only heard, or had understood, we would not have been of the inhabitants of the Blaze.'",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5252,
            "text": "So they confess their sins. Curse the inhabitants of the Blaze!",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5253,
            "text": "Surely those who fear their Lord in the Unseen -- there awaits them forgiveness and a great wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5254,
            "text": "Be secret in your speech, or proclaim it, He knows the thoughts within the breasts.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5255,
            "text": "Shall He not know, who created? And He is the All-subtle, the All-aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5256,
            "text": "It is He who made the earth submissive to you; therefore walk in its tracts, and eat of His provision; to Him is the Uprising.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5257,
            "text": "Do you feel secure that He who is in heaven will not cause the earth to swallow you, the while it rocks?",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5258,
            "text": "Do you feel secure that He who is in heaven will not loose against you a squall of pebbles, then you shall know how My warning is?",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5259,
            "text": "Those that were before them also cried lies; then how was My horror!",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5260,
            "text": "Have they not regarded the birds above them spreading their wings, and closing them? Naught holds them but the All-merciful. Surely He sees everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5261,
            "text": "Or who is this that shall be a host for you to help you, apart from the All-merciful? The unbelievers are only in delusion.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5262,
            "text": "Or who is this that shall provide for you if He withholds His provision? No, but they persist in disdain and aversion.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5263,
            "text": "What, is he who walks prone upon his face better guided than he who walks upright on a straight path?",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5264,
            "text": "Say: 'It is He who produced you, and appointed for you hearing and sight and hearts; little thanks you show!'",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5265,
            "text": "Say: 'It is He who scattered you in the earth, and unto Him you shall be mustered.'",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5266,
            "text": "They say, 'When shall this promise come to pass, if you speak truly?'",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5267,
            "text": "Say: 'The knowledge is with God; I am only a clear warner.'",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5268,
            "text": "Then, when they see it nigh at hand, the faces of the unbelievers will be vexed, and it will be said, 'This is what you were promised.'",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5269,
            "text": "Say: 'What think you? If God destroys me and those with me, or has mercy on us, then who will protect the unbelievers from a painful chastisement?'",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5270,
            "text": "Say: 'He is the All-merciful. We believe in Him, and in Him we put all our trust. Assuredly, you will soon, know who is in manifest error.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5271,
            "text": "Say: 'What think you? If in the morning your water should have vanished into the earth, then who would bring you running water?'",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 68,
        "name": "سُورَةُ القَلَمِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Qalam",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Pen",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5272,
            "text": "Nun. By the Pen, and what they inscribe,",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5273,
            "text": "thou art not, by the blessing of thy Lord, a man possessed.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5274,
            "text": "Surely thou shalt have a wage unfailing;",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5275,
            "text": "surely thou art upon a mighty morality.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5276,
            "text": "So thou shalt see, and they will see,",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5277,
            "text": "which of you is the demented.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5278,
            "text": "Surely thy Lord knows very well those who have gone astray from His way, and He knows very well those who are guided.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5279,
            "text": "So obey thou not those who cry lies.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5280,
            "text": "They wish that thou shouldst compromise, then they would compromise.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5281,
            "text": "And obey thou not every mean swearer,",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5282,
            "text": "backbiter, going about with slander,",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5283,
            "text": "hinderer of good, guilty aggressor, coarse-grained,",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5284,
            "text": "moreover ignoble,",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5285,
            "text": "because he has wealth and sons.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5286,
            "text": "When Our signs are recited to him, he says, 'Fairy-tales of the ancients!'",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5287,
            "text": "We shall brand him upon the muzzle!",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5288,
            "text": "Now We have tried them, even as We tried the owners of the garden when they swore they would pluck in the morning",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5289,
            "text": "and they added not the saving words.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5290,
            "text": "Then a visitation from thy Lord visited it, while they were sleeping,",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5291,
            "text": "and in the morning it was as if it were a garden plucked.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5292,
            "text": "In the morning they called to one another,",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5293,
            "text": "'Come forth betimes upon your tillage, if you would pluck!'",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5294,
            "text": "So they departed, whispering together,",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5295,
            "text": "'No needy man shall enter it today against your will.'",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5296,
            "text": "And they went forth early, determined upon their purpose.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5297,
            "text": "But when they saw it, they said, 'Surely we are gone astray;",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5298,
            "text": "nay, rather we have been robbed!'",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5299,
            "text": "Said the most moderate of them, 'Did I not say to you, 'Why do you not give glory?''",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5300,
            "text": "They said, 'Glory be to God, our Lord; truly, we were evildoers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5301,
            "text": "And they advanced one upon another, blaming each other.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5302,
            "text": "They said, 'Woe, alas for us! Truly, we were insolent.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5303,
            "text": "It may be that our Lord will give us in exchange a better than it; to our Lord we humbly turn.'",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5304,
            "text": "Such is the chastisement; and the chastisement of the world to come, is assuredly greater, did they but know.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5305,
            "text": "Surely for the godfearing shall be Gardens of Bliss with their Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5306,
            "text": "What, shall we make those who have surrendered like to the sinners?",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5307,
            "text": "What ails you then, how you judge?",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5308,
            "text": "Or have you a Book wherein you study?",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5309,
            "text": "Surely therein you shall have whatever you choose!",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5310,
            "text": "Or have you oaths from Us, reaching to the Day of Resurrection? Surely you shall have whatever you judge!",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5311,
            "text": "Ask them, which of them will guarantee that!",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5312,
            "text": "Or do they have associates? Then let them bring their associates, if they speak truly.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5313,
            "text": "Upon the day when the leg shall be bared, and they shall be summoned to bow themselves, but they cannot;",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5314,
            "text": "humbled shall be their eyes, and abasement shall overspread them, for they had been summoned to bow themselves while they were whole.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5315,
            "text": "So leave Me with him who cries lies to this discourse! We will draw them on little by little whence they know not;",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5316,
            "text": "and I shall respite them -- assuredly My guile is sure.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5317,
            "text": "Or askest thou them for a wage, and so they are weighed down with debt?",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5318,
            "text": "Or is the Unseen in their keeping, and so they are writing it down?",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5319,
            "text": "So be thou patient under the judgment of thy Lord, and be not as the Man of the Fish, when he called, choking inwardly.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5320,
            "text": "Had there not overtaken him a blessing from his Lord he would have been cast upon the wilderness, being condemned.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5321,
            "text": "But his Lord had chosen him, and He placed him among the righteous.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5322,
            "text": "The unbelievers wellnigh strike thee down with their glances, when they hear the Reminder, and they say, 'Surely he is a man possessed!'",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5323,
            "text": "And it is nothing but a Reminder unto all beings.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 69,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الحَاقَّةِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Haaqqa",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Reality",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5324,
            "text": "The Indubitable!",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5325,
            "text": "What is the Indubitable?",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5326,
            "text": "And what will teach thee what is the Indubitable?",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5327,
            "text": "Thamood and Ad cried lies to the Clatterer.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5328,
            "text": "As for Thamood, they were destroyed by the Screamer;",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5329,
            "text": "and as for Ad, they were destroyed by a wind clamorous,",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5330,
            "text": "violent that He compelled against them seven nights and eight days, uninterruptedly, and thou mightest see the people laid prostrate in it as if they were the stumps of fallen down palm-trees.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5331,
            "text": "Now dost thou see any remnant of them?",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5332,
            "text": "Pharaoh likewise, and those before him, and the Subverted Cities -- they committed error,",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5333,
            "text": "and they rebelled against the Messenger of their Lord, and He seized them with a surpassing grip.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5334,
            "text": "Lo, when the waters rose, We bore you in the running ship",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5335,
            "text": "that We might make it a reminder for you and for heeding ears to hold.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5336,
            "text": "So, when the Trumpet is blown with a single blast",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5337,
            "text": "and the earth and the mountains are lifted up and crushed with a single blow,",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5338,
            "text": "then, on that day, the Terror shall come to pass,",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5339,
            "text": "and heaven shall be split, for upon that day it shall be very frail,",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5340,
            "text": "and the angels shall stand upon its borders, and upon that day eight shall carry above them the Throne of thy Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5341,
            "text": "On that day you shall be exposed, not one secret of yours concealed.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5342,
            "text": "Then as for him who is given his book in his right hand, he shall say, 'Here, take and read my book!",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5343,
            "text": "Certainly I thought that I should encounter my reckoning.'",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5344,
            "text": "So he shall be in a pleasing life",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5345,
            "text": "in a lofty Garden,",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5346,
            "text": "its clusters nigh to gather.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5347,
            "text": "'Eat and drink with wholesome appetite for that you did long ago, in the days gone by.'",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5348,
            "text": "But as for him who is given his book in his left hand, he shall say, 'Would that I had not been given my book",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5349,
            "text": "and not known my reckoning!",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5350,
            "text": "Would it had been the end!",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5351,
            "text": "My wealth has not availed me,",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5352,
            "text": "my authority is gone from me.'",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5353,
            "text": "'Take him, and fetter him,",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5354,
            "text": "and then roast him in Hell,",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5355,
            "text": "then in a chain of seventy cubits' length insert him!",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5356,
            "text": "Behold, he never believed in God the All-mighty,",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5357,
            "text": "and he never urged the feeding of the needy;",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5358,
            "text": "therefore he today has not here one loyal friend,",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5359,
            "text": "neither any food saving foul pus,",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5360,
            "text": "that none excepting the sinners eat.'",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5361,
            "text": "No! I swear by that you see",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5362,
            "text": "and by that you do not see,",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5363,
            "text": "it is the speech of a noble Messenger.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5364,
            "text": "It is not the speech of a poet (little do you believe)",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5365,
            "text": "nor the speech of a soothsayer (little do you remember).",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5366,
            "text": "A sending down from the Lord of all Being.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5367,
            "text": "Had he invented against Us any sayings,",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5368,
            "text": "We would have seized him by the right hand,",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5369,
            "text": "then We would surely have cut his life-vein",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5370,
            "text": "and not one of you could have defended him.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5371,
            "text": "Surely it is a Reminder to the godfearing;",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5372,
            "text": "but We know that some of you will cry lies.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5373,
            "text": "Surely it is a sorrow to the unbelievers;",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5374,
            "text": "yet indeed it is the truth of certainty.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5375,
            "text": "Then magnify the Name of thy Lord, the All-mighty.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 70,
        "name": "سُورَةُ المَعَارِجِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Ma'aarij",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Ascending Stairways",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5376,
            "text": "A questioner asked of a chastisement about to fall",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5377,
            "text": "for the unbelievers, which none may avert,",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5378,
            "text": "from God, the Lord of the Stairways.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5379,
            "text": "To Him the angels and the Spirit mount up, in a day whereof the measure is fifty thousand years.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5380,
            "text": "So be thou patient with a sweet patience;",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5381,
            "text": "behold, they see it as if far off;",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5382,
            "text": "but We see it is nigh.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5383,
            "text": "Upon the day when heaven shall be as molten copper",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5384,
            "text": "and the mountains shall be as plucked wool-tufts,",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5385,
            "text": "no loyal friend shall question loyal friend,",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5386,
            "text": "as they are given sight of them. The sinner will wish that he might ransom himself from the chastisement of that day even by his sons,",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5387,
            "text": "his companion wife, his brother,",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5388,
            "text": "his kin who sheltered him,",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5389,
            "text": "and whosoever is in the earth, all together, so that then it might deliver him.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5390,
            "text": "Nay, verily it is a furnace",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5391,
            "text": "snatching away the scalp,",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5392,
            "text": "calling him who drew back and turned away,",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5393,
            "text": "who amassed and hoarded.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5394,
            "text": "Surely man was created fretful,",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5395,
            "text": "when evil visits him, impatient,",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5396,
            "text": "when good visits him, grudging,",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5397,
            "text": "save those that pray",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5398,
            "text": "and continue at their prayers,",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5399,
            "text": "those in whose wealth is a right known",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5400,
            "text": "for the beggar and the outcast,",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5401,
            "text": "who confirm the Day of Doom",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5402,
            "text": "and go in fear of the chastisement of their Lord",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5403,
            "text": "(from their Lord's chastisement none feels secure)",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5404,
            "text": "and guard their private parts",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5405,
            "text": "save from their wives and what their right hands own, then not being blameworthy",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5406,
            "text": "(but whoso seeks after more than that, they are the transgressors),",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5407,
            "text": "and who preserve their trusts and their covenant,",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5408,
            "text": "and perform their witnessings,",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5409,
            "text": "and who observe their prayers.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5410,
            "text": "Those shall be in Gardens, high-honoured.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 502,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5411,
            "text": "What ails the unbelievers, running with outstretched necks",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 503,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5412,
            "text": "towards thee on the right hand and on the left hand in knots?",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 503,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5413,
            "text": "What, is every man of them eager to be admitted to a Garden of Bliss?",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 503,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5414,
            "text": "Not so; for We have created them of what they know.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 569,
            "ruku": 503,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5415,
            "text": "No! I swear by the Lord of the Easts and Wests, surely We are able",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 503,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5416,
            "text": "to substitute a better than they; We shall not be outstripped.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 503,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5417,
            "text": "Then leave them alone to plunge and play until they encounter that day of theirs which they are promised,",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 503,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5418,
            "text": "the day they shall come forth from the tombs hastily, as if they were hurrying unto a waymark,",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 503,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5419,
            "text": "humbled their eyes, overspreading them abasement. That is the day which they were promised.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 503,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 71,
        "name": "سُورَةُ نُوحٍ",
        "englishName": "Nooh",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Noah",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5420,
            "text": "We sent Noah to his people, saying, 'Warn thy people, ere there come on them a painful chastisement.'",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5421,
            "text": "He said, 'O my people, I am unto you a clear warner,",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5422,
            "text": "saying, 'Serve God, and fear Him, and obey you me,",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5423,
            "text": "and He will forgive you your sins, and defer you to a stated term; God's term, when it comes, cannot be deferred, did you but know.''",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5424,
            "text": "He said; 'My Lord, I have called my people by night and by day,",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5425,
            "text": "but my calling has only increased them in flight.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5426,
            "text": "And whenever I called them, that Thou mightest forgive them, they put their fingers in their ears, and wrapped them in their garments, and persisted, and waxed very proud.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5427,
            "text": "Then indeed I called them openly;",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5428,
            "text": "then indeed I spoke publicly unto them, and I spoke unto them secretly,",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5429,
            "text": "and I said, 'Ask you forgiveness of your Lord; surely He is ever All-forgiving,",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 570,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5430,
            "text": "and He will loose heaven upon you in torrents",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5431,
            "text": "and will succour you with wealth and sons, and will appoint for you gardens, and will appoint for you rivers.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5432,
            "text": "What ails you, that you look not for majesty in God,",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5433,
            "text": "seeing He created you by stages?",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5434,
            "text": "Have you not regarded how God created seven heavens one upon another,",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5435,
            "text": "and set the moon therein for a light and the sun for a lamp?",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5436,
            "text": "And God caused you to grow out of the earth,",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5437,
            "text": "then He shall return you into it, and bring you forth.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5438,
            "text": "And God has laid the earth for you as a carpet,",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5439,
            "text": "that thereof you may thread ways, ravines.'",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 504,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5440,
            "text": "Noah said, 'My Lord, they have rebelled against me, and followed him whose wealth and children increase him only in loss,",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 505,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5441,
            "text": "and have devised a mighty device",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 505,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5442,
            "text": "and have said, 'Do not leave your gods, and do not leave Wadd, nor Suwa', Yaghuth, Ya'uq, neither Nasr.'",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 505,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5443,
            "text": "And they have led many astray. Increase Thou not the evildoers save in error!'",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 505,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5444,
            "text": "And because of their transgressions they were drowned, and admitted into a Fire, for they found not, apart from God, any to help them.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 505,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5445,
            "text": "And Noah said, 'My Lord, leave not upon the earth of the unbelievers even one.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 505,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5446,
            "text": "Surely, if Thou leavest them, they will lead Thy servants astray, and will beget none but unbelieving libertines.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 505,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5447,
            "text": "My Lord, forgive me and my parents and whosoever enters my house as a believer, and the believers, men and women alike; and do Thou not increase the evildoers save in ruin!'",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 571,
            "ruku": 505,
            "hizbQuarter": 228,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 72,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الجِنِّ",
        "englishName": "Al-Jinn",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Jinn",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5448,
            "text": "Say: 'It has been revealed to me that a company of the jinn gave ear, then they said, 'We have indeed heard a Koran wonderful,",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5449,
            "text": "guiding to rectitude. We believe in it, and we will not associate with our Lord anyone.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5450,
            "text": "He -- exalted be our Lord's majesty! has not taken to Himself either consort or a son.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5451,
            "text": "The fool among us spoke against God outrage,",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5452,
            "text": "and we had thought that men and jinn would never speak against God a lie.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5453,
            "text": "But there were certain men of mankind who would take refuge with certain men of the jinn, and they increased them in vileness,",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5454,
            "text": "and they thought, even as you also thought, that God would never raise up anyone.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5455,
            "text": "And we stretched towards heaven, but we found it filled with terrible guards and meteors.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5456,
            "text": "We would sit there on seats to hear; but any listening now finds a meteor in wait for him.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5457,
            "text": "And so we know not whether evil is intended for those in the earth, or whether their Lord intends for them rectitude.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5458,
            "text": "And some of us are the righteous, and some of us are otherwise; we are sects differing.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5459,
            "text": "Indeed, we thought that we should never be able to frustrate God in the earth, neither be able to frustrate Him by flight.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5460,
            "text": "When we heard the guidance, we believed in it; and whosoever believes in his Lord, he shall fear neither paltriness nor vileness.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 572,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5461,
            "text": "And some of us have surrendered, and some of us have deviated. Those who have surrendered sought rectitude;",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5462,
            "text": "but as for those who have deviated, they have become firewood for Gehenna!''",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5463,
            "text": "Would they but go straight on the way, We would give them to drink of water copious,",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5464,
            "text": "that We might try them therein. And whosoever turns away from the Remembrance of his Lord, He will thrust him into chastisement rigorous.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5465,
            "text": "The places of worship belong to God; so call not, along with God, upon anyone.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5466,
            "text": "When the servant of God stood calling on Him, they were wellnigh upon him in swarms.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 506,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5467,
            "text": "Say: 'I call only upon my Lord, and I do not associate with Him anyone.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 507,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5468,
            "text": "Say: 'Surely I possess no power over you, either for hurt or for rectitude.'",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 507,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5469,
            "text": "Say: 'From God shall protect me not anyone, and I shall find, apart from Him, no refuge,",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 507,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5470,
            "text": "excepting a Deliverance from God and His Messages. And whoso rebels against God and His messenger, for him there awaits the Fire of Gehenna; therein they shall dwell forever.'",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 507,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5471,
            "text": "Until, when they see that which they are promised, then they will know who is weaker in helpers and fewer in numbers.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 507,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5472,
            "text": "Say: 'I do not know whether that which you are promised is nigh, or whether my Lord will appoint for it a space;",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 507,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5473,
            "text": "Knower He of the Unseen, and He discloses not His Unseen to anyone,",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 507,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5474,
            "text": "save only to such a Messenger as He is well-pleased with; then He despatches before him and behind him watchers,",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 507,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5475,
            "text": "that He may know they have delivered the Messages of their Lord; and He encompasses all that is with them, and He has numbered everything in numbers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 573,
            "ruku": 507,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 73,
        "name": "سُورَةُ المُزَّمِّلِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Muzzammil",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Enshrouded One",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5476,
            "text": "O thou enwrapped in thy robes,",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5477,
            "text": "keep vigil the night, except a little",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5478,
            "text": "(a half of it, or diminish a little,",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5479,
            "text": "or add a little), and chant the Koran very distinctly;",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5480,
            "text": "Behold, We shall cast upon thee a weighty word;",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5481,
            "text": "surely the first part of the night is heavier in tread, more upright in speech,",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5482,
            "text": "surely in the day thou hast long business.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5483,
            "text": "And remember the Name of thy Lord, and devote thyself unto Him very devoutly.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5484,
            "text": "Lord of the East and the West; there is no god but He; so take Him for a Guardian.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5485,
            "text": "And bear thou patiently what they say, and forsake them graciously.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 574,
            "ruku": 508,
            "hizbQuarter": 229,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5486,
            "text": "Leave Me to those who cry lies, those prosperous ones, and respite them a little,",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 29,
